title: pineapple casserole
directions: Drain pineapple.
Mix flour and sugar.
Add juice to make a paste.
Mix well with pineapple and grated cheese.
Pour mixture in casserole dish.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Cut apart chicken.
Place rice at bottom of pan.
Add soup and seasonings.
Fill water to top of rice.
Lay chicken on top. Season chicken.
Bake at 350° about 1 1/2 hours.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oats; set aside to cool.
Cream the brown sugar, white sugar and Crisco.
Add the flour, soda, salt and spices; mix well, then add the oats mixture.
Mix thoroughly. Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 25 minutes.
Add topping; return to oven to brown lightly.

title: sunset salad
directions: Dissolve jello and salt in boiling water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Chill until thickened, then stir and pour into 6-cup mold or 10 individual molds.
Serve with crisp greens and mayonnaise.
Makes 10 servings.

title: stuffed bell peppers*
directions: Mix meat, rice, onion, garlic, basil, cumin, salt and pepper. Add about 1/4 of tomato sauce and mix well.
Stuff peppers, leaving 1/2-inch space at top.
Place in large saucepan.
Mix remaining tomato sauce with enough water to come 1/2-inch from top of bell pepper.
Add bay leaves, salt and pepper.
Bring to boil; cover and cook on low heat for 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 8 servings.

title: easy frosting
directions: Beat all ingredients together and frost cake.

title: crab dip
directions: Combine ingredients and bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350° or until top is light brown. Let stand 5 minutes.
Will thicken.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Combine gelatin and boiling water, stirring 2 minutes or until gelatin dissolves. Chill until mixture is the consistency of unbeaten egg white. Stir in cranberry sauce, celery and pecans. Spoon mixture into lightly oiled individual molds or 4-cup mold. Cover and chill until firm. Unmold onto a lettuce-lined plate and garnish with fresh cranberries, if desired.

title: cabbage and spinach
directions: With a sharp knife, core and coarsely shred cabbage.
In Dutch oven over high heat, heat 2 tablespoons of salad oil.
Add cabbage, salt and sugar and cook, stirring frequently, until cabbage is tender-crisp, about 5 minutes.
Add spinach; cook 1 minute longer, stirring constantly.

title: potato soup supreme
directions: Peel and boil potatoes in a minimun of water.
If you wish, chop up and add celery.
Chop up bacon to fry and add a large chopped onion; fry with the bacon.
Brown bacon well and also the onions.
Drain off all the grease and then put back 4 tablespoons of bacon grease.
Add flour and make a roux.
Mash the potatoes in the cooking water or drain off and use milk or part milk.
Add the roux to the mashed potatoes.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Return bacon and onions to soup.

title: creamy ginger dressing
directions: In a small mixing bowl, combine sour cream, honey, lemon juice and ginger.
Let stand at least 15 minutes to let flavors blend. The dressing will thicken slightly if refrigerated overnight.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread the rolls in a 10 x 15-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool.
Mix the cream cheese, mayonnaise, basil and vegetable seasoning; spread over crust.
Spread the chopped vegetables on top of cream cheese mixture.
Sprinkle with cheese on top, if desired.

title: vegetable party squares
directions: To form crust, open and press rolls into an 11 x 17-inch pan and bake at 350° until browned, 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: peas and hash casserole
directions: Brown and cook onion and beef in hot shortening, stirring to separate beef into small pieces.
Season with salt and pepper. Drain peas, reserving 1/2 cup liquid.
Add peas, reserved liquid and drained potatoes.
Heat until vegetables are hot.

title: bean stew
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Mix all ingredients in crock-pot and cook on low for 4 to 6 hours.

title: dutch apple bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla and beat.
Add dry ingredients alternately with orange juice and then fold in apples and nuts.
Bake in buttered loaf pan at 350° for approximately 55 minutes.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Use 2 to 3 heaping teaspoonfuls per cup of hot chocolate.

title: pepper stew
directions: Roll stewing beef in flour (seasoned to your likeness) and brown in a skillet.
After breaking up the tomatoes, empty both cans into a saucepan (including the juice).
Chop up the onion. Add one beef bouillon cube and one cup of water.
Cut the peppers in narrow strips.
Add the onion, bouillon, water and peppers to the tomatoes in the saucepan.
Simmer for two hours or longer (the longer the better).

title: double decker pastry
directions: Sift together flour and next 4 ingredients.
Add butter, shortening and next 3 ingredients.
Divide dough into 3 portions. Roll out first piece as for pie and place on bottom of a greased cookie sheet, 10 1/2 x 15 1/2-inch.
Spread the nut mixture over this (the 2 1/2 cups nuts and 1/2 cup sugar mixed together.)
Save a little of this nut mixture for the top.
Roll out second layer of dough and place on top of nuts.
Spread this with the fruit filling and sprinkle the nut mixture you saved.
Roll out third portion of dough and cut into strips like lattice work.
Place criss-cross over fruit filling.
Brush lattice work with beaten egg.

title: brenda's famous breakfast casserole
directions: Beat eggs until smooth.
Add all ingredients except 1/2 cup [cheese.
mix well.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes or until center is firm.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and place in oven until melted.
Allow to cool 5 minutes; cut into squares and serve.
Optional:
Diced fresh tomatoes are great in casserole.
Garnish with parsley or tomato wedge.

title: standing prime rib
directions: Place roast in shallow cake pan.
Mix marinade according to directions on back.
Pour over roast and marinate 30 to 45 minutes, turning and covering a few times.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Place roast in shallow open pan, rib bones down.
Do not add water. Roast meat, using a thermometer for internal temperature:
rare 140°, medium 160°, well 170°.
The ideal temperature is 155° (about 35 minutes per pound).
Remove from the oven and let stand 15 minutes before carving.
Carve top down to bone and then release along bone.
Can use drippings for gravy.
Baste often with remaining marinade.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt margarine; add onion and cook until clear.
Add soup, cheese, broccoli and rice.
Mix thoroughly; heat through.
Pour into casserole and bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°, uncovered.

title: crunch cake
directions: Put all ingredients in a mixing bowl and beat at medium speed for 12 minutes.
Pour into a greased and floured large tube pan. Bake at 350 degrees for one hour.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Combine sugar, butter and milk in saucepan.
Bring to a full boil, stirring constantly.
Continue to boil 5 minutes over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in chocolate chips until melted.
Add Marshmallow Creme, nuts and vanilla. Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool at room temperature.
Cut into squares.

title: best shortcakes
directions: Blend flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Cut in 3 tablespoons butter until fine particles.
Beat egg and add half and half and 2 tablespoons softened butter.
Toss with fork, knead very gently on floured surface.
Roll 1/4-inch thick, cut and spread with softened butter. Top with remaining rounds.
Sprinkle top with sugar.
Bake 14 minutes at 400°.

title: meringue
directions: Cook first three ingredients, cool slightly.
Add to egg whites and beat until stiff and glossy.

title: chocolate wet cake
directions: Cream sugar, Crisco and butter together.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each egg.
Add flour, milk and flavor. Beat well.
Bake at 325° for about 35 minutes in long baking pan.

title: chili cheese log
directions: Beat the chili seasoning, cream cheese and salsa together. Shape into roll.
Top with nuts and Monterey Jack cheese.
Serve with crackers.

title: cheesy potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes until tender.
Drain and add milk and rest of the ingredients.
Boil in saucepan.

title: berry syrup
directions: Put 10 white Kleenex tissues in 2 quarts of boiling water. Let stand 1 minute.
Break tissue into pieces with fork.
Pour into a strainer; shake to remove water.
Makes 1 cup of pulp.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Blend sugar and cornstarch and set aside.
Put Milnot and milk in a 3-quart saucepan.
Add salt to egg yolks, beat lightly and add to milk.
Stir well, then add sugar and cornstarch.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a boil and thickens.
Boil for another minute or two, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and add butter and vanilla.
Stir until butter is melted and blended into mixture.
Stir in 2 cups coconut and immediately pour into pie shells.
Top with whipped cream and toasted 1/4 cup coconut or make meringue from leftover egg whites, top with raw coconut and bake.

title: savory pepper steak
directions: Cut steak in strips.
Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Coat meat strips.
In large skillet, cook meat in hot oil until browned on all sides.
Drain tomatoes, reserving liquid.
Add tomato liquid, water, onion, garlic and bouillon to meat.
Cover and simmer about 1 1/4 hours, until meat is tender.
Uncover, stir in Worcestershire.
Add green pepper strips.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
If necessary, thicken gravy with mixture of flour and water.
Add drained tomatoes, cook about 5 minutes more.
Serve over hot rice.
Serves 6.

title: tuna vegetable supper
directions: Separate cauliflower and cook with carrots until tender-crisp. Drain.
Saute onion in butter until tender.
Combine onion, soup, milk and tuna.
Mix well.
Place cauliflower and carrots in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Pour soup mixture over and top with crackers.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: mayo moist cranberry-orange bread
directions: Grease and flour
2 loaf pans (8 x 4-inch).
In a large bowl, combine
flour,
cranberries, sugar, nuts, baking powder and salt. In
a
small
bowl,
beat	egg, orange peel, orange juice and mayonnaise	until
smooth;	stir into flour mixture just until moistened.	Spoon
into
pans.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes. Cool
in
pans
for
minutes.	Remove from pans; cool completely.
Will be easier to slice on second day. Makes 2 loaves.

title: marinated cucumbers
directions: Toss together gently.
Cover and marinate for at least 30 minutes prior to serving.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni until done. Add green onions, diced tomatoes, boiled eggs, onion, diced cheese and mayo. Season with salt and pepper.

title: macaroon pie
directions: Mix cracker crumbs, dates, pecans and sugar.
Beat until stiff egg whites and baking powder.
Fold both mixtures together and pour into well-buttered 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Refrigerate.
Top with whipped cream.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit well.
Add marshmallows and coconut.
Add sour cream to fruit mixture and mix well.
Chill 24 hours in a glass dish.

title: salad dressing cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in a loaf pan which has been greased and lined with waxed paper for 30 minutes or until done.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Mix oil, sugar and egg.
Add dry ingredients with pumpkin. Add vanilla and fold in nuts.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: moist chocolate cake
directions: Beat together butter, sugar and eggs for 1 minute.
Mix together in separate bowl the boiling water, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Let cool and add to butter mixture.

title: peanut butter oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Blend Jif, Crisco and sugar.
Add milk, vanilla and eggs; mix well.
Stir in combined dry ingredients, then add rolled oats and raisins and mix thoroughly.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased baking sheets.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes or until cookies are lightly browned around edges. Cool on cookie sheets 2 to 3 minutes, then remove to racks to finish cooling.

title: black walnut cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening; gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy and sugar is dissolved.
Add egg yolks; beat well.
Combine buttermilk and soda; stir until dissolves. Add flour to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk mixture, beginning and ending with flour.
Stir in vanilla.
Add walnuts and coconut; stir well.
Beat egg whites with cream of tartar until stiff peaks form.
Fold egg whites into batter.
Pour into Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool completely and frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: pecan pralines
directions: Combine the sugar, water and vinegar; cook to 236°, stirring occasionally.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients together in the order given.
Add last the baking soda in the water.
Bake for 1 hour in a 350° preheated oven in angel food cake pan.

title: mock shrimp cocktail
directions: Mix horseradish and ketchup together.
Start with 2 tablespoons horseradish, add more if you like it "zippier!"
Pour over cream cheese.
Refrigerate until 1/2 hour before serving. Serve with crackers.

title: broccoli casserole with rice
directions: Saute onion and celery in oleo.
Combine all ingredients in casserole dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: italian potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Peel and cut potatoes lengthwise into wedges (about 6 to 8 per potato) and drop into a bowl of cold water.
Combine bread crumbs and grated cheese.
Do not dry the wedges before coating them well with the crumb mixture.
Place them in a shallow 9 x 13-inch baking dish, sprinkling any remaining crumbs on top.
Top potatoes with sliced tomatoes and onion rings.
Sprinkle with oregano, salt and a generous grinding of pepper.
Drizzle with oil just before baking.
Bake, uncovered, 1 hour and 10 minutes or until potatoes are brown, but still have some crunchiness.

title: ryan's carrot meatballs
directions: (Ryan hates carrots, but he loves these!)

title: quick jam pastry
directions: Cut cream cheese and butter into biscuit mix.
Add milk and mix thoroughly.
Knead dough.
Roll out to size of cookie sheet. Grease pan and invert dough onto pan.
Slit 1-inch strips 1/4 of the way into the center on both long sides of dough.
Spread jam on center 1/2 of dough.
Fold slitted dough into center.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Drizzle with icing after it has cooled. Slice along slits and down the center.

title: buttercream icing
directions: Cream the butter and shortening with mixer.
Add vanilla. Gradually add sugar, 1 cup at a time, beating well.
Icing will appear dry.
Add milk; beat at high speed until light and fluffy. (Can be refrigerated for 1 week in an airtight container.)

title: gypsy
directions: Sprinkle sherry over ladyfingers.
After sprinkling ladyfingers with sherry, layer custard, then whipping cream, then sprinkle almonds.
Repeat.
Do a day ahead.
Season custard with a small amount of sherry.

title: italian pannettone
directions: Scald milk; stir in sugar, salt and butter.
Slightly cool. Measure warm water into a bowl.
Dissolve yeast into warm water. Stir in milk mixture.
Stir in eggs and 2 cups flour.
Make smooth batter.
stir in fruits, nuts and anise.
Now, add more flour to make stiff dough.
Turn onto lightly floured board.
Knead until smooth and elastic.
Cover and let rise in a greased bowl (about 1 hour).
Punch down, cover and rise 1/2 hour again.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Put sugar, cocoa, butter and milk in saucepan and bring to a boil for 2 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add oatmeal, peanut butter and vanilla.
Drop from spoon on wax paper.
Let cool, then cover.

title: salsa
directions: Note:
Need one (16 to 24-quart) kettle
and pint jars.

title: bourbon balls
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except granulated sugar.
Roll mixture into 1-inch balls.
Roll balls in the granulated sugar. Place in covered container and refrigerate for a few days before serving for maximum flavor.
Makes approximately 2 dozen.

title: stevie c's apple crisp
directions: Slice apples and arrange in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix remaining ingredients into a crumb consistency.
Put 2 tablespoons of water in with apples.
Pour crumb mixture over apples.
Poke some of the crumbs down around apples.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour, until apples are soft.
Serve warm and topped with ice cream, if you desire.

title: italian zucchini crescent pie
directions: Cook zucchini and onion in margarine for about 10 minutes. Stir in parsley, salt, pepper, garlic powder, basil and oregano. Combine eggs with cheese and stir into zucchini mixture.

title: hawaiian stuffed chicken
directions: For stuffing, combine toast, pineapple, peanuts and cinnamon. Lightly flatten chicken to uniform thickness.
Place about 1/2 cup stuffing across center of each chicken breast; fold ends to center and secure with toothpick.
Lightly brown chicken in oil on all sides.
Combine ginger ale, ketchup and pepper; pour over chicken. Simmer, uncovered, 12 to 14 minutes, basting occasionally. Remove toothpicks and serve with yellow rice mold.
Garnish with endive, spring onions, bell pepper, parsley and cherry tomatoes. Serves 4 to 5.

title: tuna, macaroni and cheese
directions: Melt butter over medium heat and then add flour, stirring until smooth.
Add milk and continue stirring until a smooth white sauce is formed.
Cut cheese in cubes and gradually add to the sauce until all the cheese is melted.

title: flank steak
directions: Tessie, my mother-in-law, prepared a few dishes which were quite special.
It took a lot of effort to get the recipe, because Tessie did not measure things, but somehow they always came out great.
The chicken in the recipe should be a fryer, fresh, with skin and bones.
If your family does not like picking over the chicken, you can remove the skin and bones, but only after cooking.

title: carrot cake
directions: Stir sugar, oil and eggs to blend well.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Mix in carrots and nuts.
Bake in greased and floured loaf pan 55 minutes at 375° or until cake tests done.

title: aloha punch
directions: Combine orange juice, water, pineapple and juice, lemon juice and liquid artificial sweetener in serving container.
Just before serving, add ice cubes and ginger ale.

title: coon hunters' supper
directions: In large steam pot, with 2 inches water, break corn cobs in half and stack upright in bottom of pan.
Quarter new potatoes and layer over top of corn.
Quarter onions and layer over top of potatoes.
Cut carrots in sticks or slices and layer over onions. Slice smoked sausage in discs and layer over carrots.
Cover with lid to pot and bring water to rolling boil.
Let ingredients steam for 20 minutes or until everything seems to be soft.
Serve as complete dinner.

title: one alarm chili
directions: Brown ground chuck.
Add remaining ingredients.
Make a paste of 1 1/2 teaspoons cornstarch and 1 cup water; add for thickening. Simmer 1 hour.
To increase the alarm, increase the cayenne.

title: special k bars
directions: Mix Karo and brown sugar in saucepan. Bring to boil, then add 1 cup of peanut butter. Pour hot mixture over the Special K or Rice Krispies, then press in a 9 x 13 pan. Next, melt the chocolate and butterscotch chips and spread over the bars.

title: cinnamon cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs.
Sift dry ingredients; mix well.
Roll dough in a ball size of a walnut.
Roll in mixture of 2 tablespoons of sugar and 1 tablespoon of cinnamon.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°.

title: strawberry trifle
directions: Clean and slice strawberries.
Mix well with orange juice and set aside.
Keep a few berries aside to garnish.
Reserve 1 cup Cool Whip.
Mix remaining portion with pudding.
Set aside.

title: coconut pie(forms its own crust)
directions: Combine flour and sugar.
In a separate bowl, combine eggs, vanilla, coconut and milk.
Grease a large pie plate with butter, then place remainder in the liquid mixture.
Mix the liquid ingredients with the flour and sugar, then pour into pie plate. Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: lime pie
directions: Combine thawed limeade with the can of milk until smooth. Fold in Cool Whip and pour into pie shell.
Refrigerate overnight or all day before slicing.
Very good and easy to make.
(Limeade may be substituted with lemonade for a good lemon pie.)

title: best-ever baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients and simmer in crock pot on low for about 4 hours.

title: roasted garlic mashed potatoes
directions: Place garlic on a square of aluminum foil; drizzle with oil, and wrap in foil.
Bake at 425 degrees for 30 min.
remove from oven, and set aside.
Cook potatoes in boiling water to cover 15-20 mins. or until tender;
drain and transfer to a large mixing bowl.
Add butter and remaining ingredients;
beat at med. speed until fluffy.
Cut off pointed ends of garlic;
squeeze pulp from garlic cloves, and stir into mashed potato mixture.
Serves 8.

title: spinach dip
directions: Defrost spinach and gently squeeze excess water from spinach. Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle crushed corn flakes on top of potato mixture and top with pats of butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fiesta salad bowl
directions: Combine tomato, pepper, olives, onions and Catalina dressing. Cover and refrigerate 2 hours. Drain, reserving marinade.
Place greens, cucumbers, marinated vegetables and corn chips in salad bowl.
Toss. Serve with reserved marinade.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream butter and peanut butter.
Add sugars, beat well.
Add beaten eggs.
Add flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Mix well. Chill dough well; form into balls.
Place on cookie sheet. Flatten with fork dipped in flour.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: banana breeze pie
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Add condensed cream and lemon juice; mix well.
Slice bananas into crust.
Pour cream cheese mixture over bananas.
Chill several hours.
Slice and enjoy!

title: pink punch
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add cold water and juices. Just before serving, add ginger ale.
Serves 35 to 40.

title: royal icing
directions: In large bowl with electric mixer at high speed, beat all ingredients 7 to 10 minutes or until stiff peaks form.
Use immediately.

title: glazed sausage balls
directions: Combine sausage, egg, cracker crumbs, milk and sage - mix well.

title: baked corn pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Lightly grease 1 1/2-quart oblong pan.

title: waye spaghetti sauce
directions: Simmer at least 2 hours (tomato sauce, garlic, salt and oregano).
Cook hamburger meat; then add to sauce.

title: ice cream sandwiches
directions: Simply spread ice cream on flat surface of any large cookie. Cover with another cookie of same size.
Wrap in foil and freeze until ready to serve.

title: coffee cake no. 2
directions: Combine egg, sugar, milk and shortening.
Add flour sifted with baking powder and salt.
Mix well and pour into greased, floured 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.

title: crab spread
directions: Thoroughly mix everything but crab and cheese.
Stir in crab meat and 1/2 of the cheese.
Put in greased casserole dish and bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Top with remaining cheese and return to oven until cheese melts, about 5 minutes. Spread on Ritz crackers to eat.
Yields 25 to 35 appetizer servings.

title: buttered carrots and corn
directions: Cover carrots with
water
and
cook until tender.
Add the corn, salt, sugar
and butter; cook over a slow fire for 5 to 10 minutes.
Serve hot.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cream puffs
directions: Heat water and butter to boil; stirring over heat 1 minute. Add flour and stir until ball forms.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, until smooth.
Drop 1/4 c. of dough 3 inches apart on baking sheet.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 400° until golden brown.
Cool away from draft.
Cut off tops, pull out soft dough.
Fill with whipped cream or prepared pudding.
Replace tops and dust with powdered sugar.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: potato soup
directions: Melt oleo butter.
Add flour and stir until smooth.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Add onions and cook until tender. Add broth and stir.
Add potatoes, salt and pepper to taste. Bring to boil and cook 15 minutes (until potatoes are done).
Stir in milk and heat thoroughly.

title: pineapple nut cake
directions: Whip the cream cheese and butter together.
Add vanilla and enough sugar to make spreadable.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Stir all ingredients together and pour into pan.
Bake about 40 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.
Frost cake.

title: catfish stew
directions: In a large Dutch oven, fry fat meat and chopped onion. Add tomato sauce, water, Texas Pete, catsup, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil and add sliced potatoes. Continue to cook on low heat for about 30 minutes. Add catfish to the pot.
Bring to a quick boil and cut heat to low.
Cook for 20 to 30 minutes or until fish is done. Serve on rice or bread.

title: miniature sesame almond drumsticks(luscious little buttery chicken wing drummettes)
directions: Combine all ingredients except butter and chicken. Dip chicken in melted butter. Coat with crumb mixture. Place chicken on greased baking sheet. Bake in preheated 350° oven 35 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: oreo cookie cake
directions: Blend together and spread on bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Combine bacon, grease and vegetables in 2 cups of water and cook until tender.
Mix milk and cornstarch, blend into soup and continue to cook until soup is thickened.
Serve nice and hot with bread or rolls.

title: easy fondant
directions: Cream Crisco with one-half the sugar.
Blend in unbeaten egg whites.
Gradually add remaining sugar, mixing to make a smooth mixture stiff enough to mold.
Form immediately into bonbons. Makes 4 dozen.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Brown ground meat and season with onion and jalapenos.
Mix the remaining ingredients together.
Add meat mixture to the cornbread mixture.
Heat enough oil to cover bottom of casserole dish.
Pour mixture into hot oil.
Cook at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: beefed-up casserole
directions: Brown
beef,
onion
and chili.
Drain grease.
Stir in tomato sauce and garlic salt.
Simmer while preparing Bisquick dough. Combine 1/2 cup cheese, sour cream and egg.
Mix well. Fold in beef
mixture.
Line 9 x 13-inch baking dish with 3/4 of
the Bisquick
dough.
Pour
beef
mixture.
Put
rest
of Bisquick scattered
on top.
Sprinkle remaining cup of cheese on top of dough and casserole.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until Bisquick is browned.

title: gates of spain vegetable dip
directions: Combine mayonnaise, curry powder, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, steak sauce, pepper, celery, salt and hot pepper sauce in a bowl.
Mix well.
Serve with raw vegetables of choice.

title: pistachio jello salad
directions: Mix pudding and pineapple together.
Fold in Cool Whip and marshmallows.
Refrigerate.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add oil, egg and milk.
Pour batter into greased 8 or 9-inch pan.
Bake about 15 minutes at 475°.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Sauce:
Add tomato sauce, paste, oregano, parsley, onion, garlic and maple syrup in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer 30 minutes, stirring every so often.

title: ultimate brownies
directions: Bake brownies according to directions.
Remove from oven when finished.
Arrange marshmallows on top of hot brownies.
Return to oven for 5 minutes or until marshmallows are puffy and golden. Cool on wire
rack.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown hamburger in pan.
Pour off excess grease.
Add chili mix seasoning, ketchup and barbecue sauce.
Turn on low and let simmer, stirring occasionally, until thoroughly mixed.
Serve with hamburger buns.

title: easy pie crust
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients (beaten). Makes 5 crusts.

title: pagoda 7 house salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients with a wire whisk.

title: california potatoes
directions: Break potatoes into a large bowl.
Mix sour cream, salt, pepper, onions, cheese and soup together.
Mix with potatoes. Pour melted butter into the mixture and mix well.
Pour all into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Mix the crushed corn flake crumbs and the 1/2 stick of melted butter together and then spread on top of the potatoes.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes or until bubbly.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli.
Saute onion in butter until tender.
Add soup, milk and cheese; cook over medium heat until cheese is melted. Add broccoli and cooked rice.
Put mixture in a 2-quart casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add other ingredients in order listed.
Mix well.
Put in container with lid.
Refrigerate until ready to use.
Put in buttered muffin pans.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.
Makes 24 rolls.

title: tomato-lentil soup(for microwave)
directions: Combine onion, garlic and water in a 3-quart casserole.
Cook, covered, on Full power for 2 to 4 minutes, or until onion is tender.
Add lentils, salt, pepper and 4 cups water.
Cook, covered, on Full power for 20 to 30 minutes, or until lentils are tender.
Stir halfway through cooking time.

title: col's spicy barbecue sauce
directions: In a large skillet, add the butter and heat on medium until melted.
Add the onion and garlic and cook while stirring until lightly browned.
Stir in the remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Store the sauce in a covered container in the refrigerator after each use.
Sauce goes well on beef, chicken or pork.
If using pork, try adding 1 to 2 tablespoons of curry powder.
Makes 4 to 5 cups.

title: bambi-beef loaf(good hot or cold)
directions: In large mixing bowl, crush crackers.
Add onions and 1 cup milk and stir until mixed.
Add meat and mix well.
Add remaining milk and seasonings.
Mix well.
Place in greased loaf pan and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: apple-tuna salad
directions: In large salad bowl, combine lettuce, apple, mandarin orange sections, tuna and walnuts; toss together.
Combine mayonnaise, soy sauce and lemon juice; mix well. To serve, add dressing to salad; toss gently.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Mix flour, salt, frozen butter and Crisco in food processor to size of small peas.
Add ice water and process to clean bowl. Refrigerate in plastic bag.

title: creamy crabmeat canapes
directions: Combine softened cream cheese, horseradish, lemon juice and seasonings, mixing well until blended.
Stir in crabmeat and cucumber.
Split French bread loaves.
Spread each half with oleo; top with crabmeat mixture.
Sprinkle with parsley.

title: chaco's sour cream banana bread
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar, beaten egg and sour cream; mix thoroughly.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with bananas. Add lemon juice.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 375° for 50 minutes.
Cool.

title: myrtle's biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a mixing bowl; stir well. Pour on a well floured surface.
Knead as little as possible; just enough to be able to handle dough.
Cut with a biscuit cutter and place on a well oiled pan.
Oil tops of biscuits.
Bake at 450° to 500° for 12 minutes on bottom rack.
Move to top rack and brown top of biscuits.

title: french onion bread
directions: Mix yeast, sugar and 2 cups flour.
Mix one of the cups of water heated to hot with soup mix.
Let stand until cool; add rest of water.
Stir in the shortening until melted.
Add to this the flour mixture.
Beat 2 minutes, adding gradually about 3 1/2 cups flour or until very stiff dough.
Knead until smooth.
Put in a greased bowl; turn to grease top.
Cover; let rise in warm place until double, about 30 minutes.

title: fudgemallow raisin candy(microwave)
directions: Microwave chocolate and peanut butter in 2-quart bowl on Medium power, 2 to 3 minutes or until melted, stirring after each minute.
Fold in marshmallows and raisins.
Pour into foil-lined 8-inch square pan.
Chill until firm.
Cut into squares.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Drain
pineapple;
reserve juice.
Mix flour and sugar. Add juice.
Add
pineapple and cheese, mixing well.
Put in a small (1 quart or 1 1/2 quart) casserole dish.
Mix butter and crackers. Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes until brown.
Good!!!
Serves 6 to 8.

title: red potatoes with parmesan cheese
directions: Wash and cut up red potatoes.
Add margarine to microwave-safe pan.
Add potatoes with 1/2-inch of water.
Cover with cling wrap and cook minutes on high.
Add margarine and parsley and sprinkle grated Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 6 to 7 minutes or until golden brown on top.

title: egg dip
directions: Mix the cream cheese and other ingredients in the order given. Serve with chips.

title: ma's bran muffins
directions: Pour boiling water over 1 cup of bran cereal and let stand. Mix sugar, oil and eggs and alternate with buttermilk and sifted dry ingredients.
First, add bran mixture, then remaining bran. Cover tightly and store in refrigerator for a minimum of 12 hours or a maximum of 6 weeks.
Preheat oven to 400° and let mixture thaw (approximately 25 minutes).
Grease muffin tins and spoon mixture into tins full 2/3 full.
Bake for 18 minutes.
For smaller muffins, bake for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 24 muffins, depending on size.
Great for breakfast!

title: rye boat dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Ream out round loaf of rye bread.
Put dip in the reamed out bread loaf.
Use pieces of bread to dip with.
When all bread pieces are gone, slice remaining bread like a pizza.

title: teriyaki marinade
directions: Mix all together.
Let meat marinate for at least 1/2 to 1 hour; longer if necessary.
Great for beef:
kabobs, chuck steaks, family steaks.
Also good for chicken.

title: butterscotch
directions: Mix sugar and water in a porcelain saucepan.
Add butter and simmer, without stirring, until a spoonful tested in cold water becomes brittle.
Turn into well buttered pans and set aside to cool.
Cut into squares with a buttered knife before the candy hardens.

title: apple squares
directions: Sift together flour, 1/3 cup sugar and salt. Cut in butter until it becomes fine particles.
Press on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Arrange apples over base. Sprinkle with lemon juice, 1/3 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Combine remaining sugar, egg, milk, vanilla, walnuts and coconut.
Spoon over apples. Return to oven at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: crazy slurpee
directions: Blend together in blender for 2 minutes.
May be frozen and re-used.

title: oven fried chicken thighs(microwave)
directions: Wash chicken thighs; pat dry.
Combine bread crumbs, potato flakes and garlic salt. Beat egg and half and half.
Dip chicken pieces in egg mixture.
Coat chicken with crumb mixture.
Place chicken thighs in a micro-safe baking dish.
Microwave at High for about 10 minutes, turning once and rotating dish.
Sprinkle with melted butter and oil.
Microwave for another 10 minutes until chicken is done.
Test for doneness by piercing with a fork. If juice runs out clear, chicken is done.
Serves 4.

title: chihuahua dip
directions: Cover bottom of 8 x 10-inch baking dish with the beans.
Mix together avocado, sour cream, mayonnaise and seasoning as the second layer.
Top with layer of tomatoes, onions and cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with taco chips.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt oleo in cobbler pan.
Pour batter in pan.
Pour in peaches; do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mexican casserole - weight watchers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Brown ground chuck and onion (drain, rinse off and pat dry with paper towel). Stir in beans, tomato sauce, taco seasoning and water. Heat all together with ground chuck. Spray the bottom of a baking dish and layer half of the tortillas on the bottom. Top with half of the meat mixture, then half of the cheese. Repeat all layers once more, ending with cheese. Bake approximately 30 minutes. Yields 8 servings; 4.5 points per serving.

title: bobotie
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Peel and slice the onions thinly. Fry lightly in hot oil and if uncooked meat is used, fry with the onions until slightly cooked and crumbly.
Soak the bread in the milk and squeeze out the milk.
Mash the bread.

Mix all the ingredients except 1/2 cup milk, 1 egg and the lemon leaves. Spoon the mixture into a greased ovenproof dish, roll up the leaves and insert them in an upright position in the meat mixture. Bake for 1 hour if uncooked meat is used and for 45 minutes if cooked meat is used.
Beat the remaining egg with 1/2 cup milk and pour over the meat 30 minutes before the end of the cooking time. Serve with rice and chutney.

title: bishop whipple pudding
directions: Beat eggs until stiff. Add sugar gradually, then mix other ingredients. Mix and beat well. Pour into buttered pan and bake in slow oven at 300° for 35 minutes. Serve with whipped cream.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix well and cover with soup. Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pudding and pineapple well.
Add marshmallows, nuts and Cool Whip.
Turn into 11 x 7-inch glass pan.
Chill.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook on low heat for 1 hour.
Simmer until right consistency. Add meat balls, hot or sweet sausage 1 hour after cooking, just before the simmering stage starts.

title: country fried steak
directions: Cut steak into individual pieces and place in large bowl with Italian dressing.
Coat well.
Can be used right away or left to marinate.
When ready to make, coat with flour and fry in oil. Browning both sides, cook until done.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate in boiling water; cool.
Cream margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, and beat well after each.
Add melted chocolate and vanilla; mix well.
Sift flour, salt and soda.
Add alternately with milk to chocolate mixture; beat well.
Beat until smooth.
Fold in whites.
Pour into 3 layer pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool; frost top only.

title: tamale casserole
directions: Brown onion in oil.
Do not drain tomatoes or corn.
Combine all ingredients.
Bake in a greased 4-quart deep casserole, covered, for 50 minutes, then remove cover and bake 10 more minutes or until "set" at 350°.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Drain pickles.
Slice or cut in chunks.
Combine ingredients. Bring to boil.
Pour over pickles; stir often for 3 days.
Keep refrigerated.
Keeps well.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly and pour into pie shells. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: apple bread
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients.
Stir in apples.
Pour into greased bread pan.
Mix last 4 ingredients and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: miracle custard pie
directions: In blender, combine milk, eggs, sugar, flour, butter, vanilla, salt and cinnamon.
Cover and blend about 10 seconds or until mixed (do not overblend).
Stir in coconut.
Pour into a greased 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until knife inserted in the middle comes out clean.
Cool, then chill.

title: dreamsickle cake
directions: Add envelope of orange kool-aid to cake mix and bake according to package directions.
Poke holes in cake when done.
Mix one box of orange jello as directed.
Pour over cake.
Refrigerate to cool.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in muffin tins at 400° for 20 to 22 minutes.

title: mock chicken almond
directions: Simmer together first 4 ingredients until onions are soft. In a separate pot or pan, prepare the noodle soup per directions on box using 5 1/2 cups of boiling water.
Add the uncooked rice. Stir until mixed well.
Add the mushrooms (pieces may be used). Combine all ingredients except almonds and bake in 9 x 13-inch dish at 375°
for 40 minutes, covered with foil.
Last 10 minutes, uncover.
Sprinkle almonds over mixture and finish baking.

title: marinade for beef or pork
directions: Mix all ingredients and marinate beef or pork.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 6 hours before cooking.
Yields 2 cups.

title: fig cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350 until done.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Put thin sliced onions in 13 x 9 casserole dish. Mix together all ingredients except crackers and margarine. Spread over onions. Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Dice chicken.
Cook in skillet until done.
Set aside.
In skillet, cook stick margarine and onion.
Add cream of mushroom soup, broth, garlic powder and 8 ounces Velveeta cheese.
Add chicken.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Serve over noodles.

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients in bowl in order given.
Place in 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle brown sugar and cinnamon to taste over top. Dot with additional butter.
Bake in 350° oven for about 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Pour melted butter over sugar and mix.
Add eggs one at a time and beat until foamy.
Add salt and lemon juice.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: fudge icing
directions: Mix all ingredients in a saucepan and bring to a boil. Boil for 1 minute. Remove from heat and cool. Spread on two 9-inch layers or 24 cupcakes.

title: salt rising bread
directions: Take 1 cup sweet milk and let come to a boil.
Thicken with meal.
Cover and set in warm place. Stir well before going to bed. Next morning, add 1 cup sweet milk, 1 cup boiling water, 1 tablespoon salt and pinch of soda.
Thicken with flour; keep warm. After it rises well, fix flour as for biscuits and make up.
Add 1 tablespoon sugar and a little salt.
Pour in yeast.
Add three pieces of shortening size of small egg.
Knead until smooth.
Make into loaves.
Put in well-greased pan and when it rises to almost full, bake in moderate oven for 1 hour.
When done, rub top with butter.

title: quick  baked beans
directions: Combine beans, sugar, onion and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour into casserole dish and top with cheese and bacon.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: healthy fruit salad
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Chill.
Other fruits in season may be added such as blueberries, strawberries, etc.

title: apple cranberry casserole
directions: Mix apples and cranberries and place in greased casserole dish.
Pour sugar over fruit.
In separate bowl, mix oatmeal, brown sugar, butter and flour.
Sprinkle this over sugar.
Top with pecans.
Bake 300-325 degrees for 1 hour.

title: mama byrd's apple pie
directions: Use one pie crust for bottom and one for top.
Keep top crust frozen until ready to use.
Peel and core apples; slice into pie shell.
Sprinkle allspice, sugar and flour over apples. Dot with margarine (use 1/4 stick).
Cover with top crust.
Slice holes in top crust, dot with remaining margarine and sprinkle with sugar (1 teaspoon).
Bake 10 minutes at 425°. Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: millionaire's pie
directions: Mix together and pour into crust.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli.
Drain.
Add butter, mushroom soup, Cheez Whiz and rice.
Bake in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with crackers.
Brown.

title: sausage stuffing
directions: Cook and stir onion and celery in margarine in 10 inch skillet until onion is tender. Stir in about 1/3 of the bread cubes. Turn into deep bowl. Add remaining ingredients, toss. Stuff turkey just before roasting.

title: baileys irish cream
directions: Put all of the ingredients, except liquor and whole milk in the blender. Fill with milk until it reaches 1 quart.
Add liquor and blend.

title: sausage quiche
directions: Bake pie crust until it is lightly brown.
Cool.
Brown sausage and onion.
Drain and put in pie shell.
Mix eggs and half and half together and pour over onion and sausage.
Put grated cheese on top and bake at 350° until done.

title: holiday coffee cake
directions: Prepare and bake mix according to package directions.
Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
After 15 minutes in oven, remove and sprinkle on nuts, sugar and cinnamon.
Pour melted butter or margarine over mixture.
Continue baking until done, 15 to 20 minutes.
Yields 14 portions.

title: marinated black-eyed peas
directions: Drain peas; add remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate in covered container for at least 24 hours.
Remove garlic bud.
Will keep 2 weeks.
Great for New Year's.

title: dough-it-yourself-for-crafts(not to be eaten)
directions: Blend salt and flour in bowl, adding water, little at a time. Knead dough 7 to 10 minutes until firm.
Place in plastic bag to keep from drying out.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together at one time.
Shape into a ball. Roll in chopped pecans.
Refrigerate.

title: banana poppy seed dressing
directions: In a small bowl, finely mash the banana.
Add sour cream, sugar, poppy seed, lemon juice, mustard and salt. Chill for at least 30 minutes. Arrange salad greens and fruit on a platter or individual salad plates.
Serve with dressing.
Yields 1 3/4 cups.

title: watergate salad(this is for a large size salad.)
directions: Fold pudding into Cool Whip until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Chill for at least 2 or 3 hours (can also sit overnight).
Just before serving, add 1 cup chopped maraschino cherries.

title: spicey low fat chicken
directions: Mix apricot and mustard, brush over chicken to coat. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cook rice as directed, also cook vegetables. Place rice on platter, put chicken on top of rice. Pour chicken juices on top.
Place vegetables around rice.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Mix cocoa and sugar in saucepan.
Blend in evaporated milk. Add butter and salt.
Stir until boiling.
Remover from heat and add vanilla.
The more the sauce is stirred, the smoother it is.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Cover bottom of flat, greased baking dish with chipped beef, snipped with kitchen shears. Arrange breasts over chipped beef. Mix soups and sour cream; pour over all.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 275°, uncovered, for 3 hours.

title: cooked mayonnaise for chicken salad
directions: Cook in top of double boiler and stir constantly.
When thickened, take off and add salt and red pepper.

title: fruit cake
directions: Stir fruit and nuts to mix.
Sprinkle flour over fruit and nuts and mix well to separate fruit.
Add sweetened condensed milk and mix thoroughly with wooden spoon.
Grease loaf pan, line with brown paper, then grease the brown paper.
Spoon batter into pan, packing to fill evenly.
Put small pan of water in oven while baking cake. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Remove from pan and place on rack.
Cool slightly before removing brown paper.
When cake is cool, wrap tightly in heavy foil.
Keeps and freezes well.

title: wisconsin fish chowder
directions: Fry bacon until
golden
brown.
Add
onions, potatoes, salt, pepper and water.
Cover
and
cook over moderate heat 5 to 10 minutes.
Add
the	boned fish.
Cover; continue cooking until potatoes are done, about 10 to 12 minutes.	Add the milk and heat thoroughly.
Thicken
slightly
with
flour and water mixture.

title: pizza quiche
directions: Beat
together
the
half and half, oregano, garlic and eggs. In
pastry crust, place pepperoni and Mozzarella.
Pour egg mixture
over
them.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Spoon hot pizza sauce over each serving.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: easy cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese at room temperature.
Beat in large bowl; add chopped onions, beef and Worcestershire sauce.
Form into ball.
Refrigerated, this will keep several days.
Serve with crackers.

title: quick chocolate cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together with a spoon.
Do not use mixer.
Form into 1 inch balls.
Roll in powdered sugar and place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 12 minutes.
Cool before removing.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook and drain spaghetti.
Add all other ingredients and mix.

title: broccoli cheese bake
directions: Cook broccoli according to package and drain. Place broccoli in a baking dish. Combine cheese, onion and soup. Spread mixture over broccoli. Top with crushed crackers. Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: dinner party perfect chicken
directions: Combine flour and salt.
Melt margarine.
Dip each chicken piece in margarine; dredge in flour mixture.
Place chicken in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan, lined with foil.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Spoon 1/2 the glaze over chicken; bake 10 minutes longer.
Spoon remaining glaze over chicken; bake 20 minutes longer, or until tender.
This may be baked ahead and reheated at serving time.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook and drain spaghetti.
Add the butter, Parmesan cheese and eggs.
Put in a 9-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle top with Mozzarella cheese, then add spaghetti sauce.
Sprinkle more Parmesan cheese on top and bake about 1/2 hour at 350°.
Let set a few minutes before cutting in wedges to serve.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Melt margarine in baking pan or dish.
Combine flour, sugar, milk and vanilla.
Pour over melted margarine in pan or dish; do not stir.
Drop strawberries into batter; again, do not stir. Bake at 350° until done.
Good hot or cold.

title: german fried potatoes
directions: Stir Tabasco into salad oil in large skillet.
Heat.
Add onion, thinly sliced potatoes and fry covered, turning occasionally until potatoes are tender and golden.
Sprinkle with salt.
Yields 6 servings.

title: tuna burgers
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients, except buns.
Fill buns with tuna mixture.
Place each sandwich on square of aluminum foil; fold foil over sandwich and seal securely.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake 20 minutes or until heated through.

title: potato casserole
directions: Put potatoes and onions in a baking dish.
Mix in a bowl soup, milk and pimento cheese.
Pour this over potatoes and onions.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until tender.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Mix beef, bread crumbs, egg, milk, onion and salt.
Brown mixture; drain.
Add garlic, flour, oregano and basil.
Stir in tomato paste and tomato soup.
Heat to serving temperature.
Cook spaghetti according to package directions; toss with melted margarine and add to casserole dish.
Pour beef mixture; top with cheese.
Bake until brown in a preheated 350° oven.
Serve hot.

title: lentil and mushroom soup
directions: Heat oil in heavy large saucepan over medium heat.
Add onion and saute until golden.
Add garlic and stir 2 minutes.
Add 6 cups water, lentils, carrots, mushrooms, celery, bay leaf and rosemary and bring to boil.
Reduce heat to medium, cover and simmer until lentils and vegetables are tender, adding more water if soup is too thick, about 45 minutes.
Discard bay leaf.
Add tomatoes and simmer 5 minutes.
Season to taste with salt.

title: pork chop skillet
directions: In large skillet, brown chops in oil over medium heat.
Remove chops; saute onions and green peppers in oil.
Stir in tomatoes, water, seasonings, rice and 1 cup cheese.
Add chops; cover and simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Top with remaining cheese; cook until cheese melts.

title: chocolate fudge pie
directions: Whisk together eggs and sugar in a large bowl. Add margarine, cocoa, flour, salt and vanilla, stirring until blended. Stir in pecans and spoon into lightly greased 9-inch pie plate. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pickled beets
directions: Boil beets until tender; peel.
Slice and set aside (if small leave whole).
Mix all other ingredients and bring to a boil.
Add cooked beets and simmer 15 minutes.
Pack in sterile jars and cover with liquid.
Seal at once.
Yields 8 pints.

title: english pea casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and cover with cheese.
Bake at 350 degrees for 15-20 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: merry cheese cakes
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Add sugar and mix thoroughly.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating until well blended.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla.
Line muffin pans with paper baking cups, then place one wafer cookie in each cup. Fill cups approximately 2/3 full.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until set.
Top with pie filling.
Chill until serving time.
Makes 20 cheese cakes.

title: chicken salad sandwiches
directions: Combine first four ingredients and blend.
Spread between slices of bread or croissants, topping with lettuce leaf.
Makes 4 sandwiches.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni until done.
Rinse and drain well.
In a large bowl, with macaroni, add remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate.

title: bread pudding
directions: Combine milk and eggs.
Pour over bread cubes.
Add remaining ingredients and stir.
Pour in 8-inch round baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: mini-morsel meringues
directions: Beat egg whites, salt and cream of tartar in small mixer bowl until soft peaks form.
Gradually add sugar; beat until stiff peaks form.
Gently fold in morsels, 1/3 at a time.
Drop by level tablespoonfuls onto greased baking sheets.
Bake in preheated 300° oven for 20 to 25 minutes until meringues are dry and crisp; cool for 2 minutes.
Remove from baking sheets; cool completely on wire racks.
Store in airtight containers.
Makes about 5 dozen cookies.

title: anne's dirt cake(12 to 16 servings)
directions: In bowl 1, mix by hand, melted butter, 10x sugar and cream cheese until smooth.
In bowl 2, mix milk and pudding together. Combine with bowl 1.
Fold Cool Whip into bowl 1 and 2 mixture. Crush Oreos by hand or by food processor until finely mixed.
Put 1/2 to 3/4 of cookies in bottom of large bowl (or a flower pot). Add bowl 1 and 2 mixture and put remaining Oreos mixture on top. Refrigerate until firm.
Don't forget a flower if served in a flower pot; also the gummy worms.
If served in a flower pot, reserve one whole Oreo to cover the hole in bottom of pot so the dirt doesn't run out.

title: slow cooker lasagna
directions: Combine ground beef and spaghetti sauce. Combine egg and cottage cheese. Layer half of the ground beef mixture, the dry noodles, the cottage cheese mixture and the Mozzarella cheese in the slow cooker. Repeat layers. Cover. Cook on high 4 to 5 hours or on low 6 to 8 hours.

title: sweet buns(boller)
directions: Melt butter in small pan.
Add milk, sugar and salt, then egg. Keep at right temperature for the yeast, a little hot to the touch.
Add powdered yeast; stir well and let sit for 4 minutes. Beat in flour to a very stiff dough.
Beat and beat some more. Add raisins.
Let rise until double in volume.
Knead and shape into 30 medium balls (or smaller, if you prefer) and let rise again.
Brush with egg mixed with 1 tablespoon milk and bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve fresh, as is, or with jam or cut in half, buttered with jam or cheese.

title: barbecue brisket
directions: Sprinkle each side of brisket with celery, onion and garlic salt.
Then pour over liquid smoke.
Place in refrigerator, covered, to marinate overnight.
When ready to bake, sprinkle with salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Cover and bake at 275° for 5 hours.
Uncover and add barbecue sauce.
Continue baking 1 hour. Remove meat from pan and let cool 1 hour.
Add water to sauce in pan.

title: trish's sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Stir in egg.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Add milk and vanilla.
Chill in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Roll and cut out or drop from spoon and flatten.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 9 minutes or until golden brown.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Stir in vanilla. Add eggs; stir in dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture.
Stir in oats and coconut and add to mixture.
Bake in greased pan for 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Slice enough cucumbers (with or without peels) to fill a 1 gallon container.
(I use a 4-quart ice cream pail and fill to 1 1/2-inches from top.)
Add onions and green pepper, adjusting to taste.
Stir salt into water until dissolved, then pour over cukes.
Let sit on counter for 1 hour, tossing cukes after 30 minutes.
Drain, but do not rinse.

title: marie's chocolate balls
directions: Melt chocolate pieces and butter.
Remove from heat and blend in egg or Egg Beaters.
Stir in confectioners sugar, nuts and marshmallows.
Blend well.
Shape into balls.
Roll in Angel Flake coconut.
If you like, you can tint coconut any color.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach; rinse and squeeze dry.
Add soup mix to sour cream and mayonnaise; mix together well.
Add spinach, water chestnuts and onions.
Stir together well.
Chill several hours. Serve with crackers.

title: pimento cheese salad
directions: Combine pimento cheese with cream cheese.
Let stand at room temperature until soft.
Add this to Cool Whip.
Add pineapple chunks, mandarin oranges, marshmallows and walnuts.
Let stand in refrigerator several hours or overnight.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Fold sugar into eggs gradually.
Add cream of tartar to egg whites, while beating.
Add nuts and chocolate chips.
Preheat oven to 450°.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheets. Turn oven off and place cookies inside and forget about until cookies and oven are cool.
Overnight is great!

title: stir-fry
directions: Freeze roast, then shave thin.
Cook meat until brown, then add all ingredients.
Simmer until done.
Stir often.
Serve with rice.

title: miniature fruitcakes
directions: In a bowl, combine the first seven ingredients.
Combine egg yolks and vanilla; stir into dry ingredients.
In a small mixing bowl, beat egg whites until stiff peaks form; fold into batter. Fill greased and floured muffin cups two-thirds full.
Cover the muffin tin tightly with heavy-duty aluminum foil.
Bake at 275° for 1 hour.
Uncover; top each fruitcake with cherries.
Bake 5 minutes longer or until a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean.
Cool for 5 minutes.
Run a knife around the edges of each cup; remove to a wire rack to cool completely.
Yield: 1 dozen.

title: lemon party punch
directions: Boil water with sugar for 10 minutes.
Add Jell-O and dissolve. Let cool.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: golf balls
directions: Mix together; roll into balls the size of walnuts.
Chill on a cookie sheet until firm.
Dip balls into 1 large package of melted chocolate chips, then chill.

title: crme brulee french toast
directions: Heat butter, brown sugar and corn syrup in a saucepan until the butter melts and the mixture is smooth, stirring constantly.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cut the bread into 1 inch thick slices. Trim the crust from each slice.

Arrange the bread in the prepared baking dish, cutting some of the bread into pieces so the entire bottom surface of the dish is covered. Beat the eggs, Half & Half, vanilla, Grand Marnier and salt in a bowl using a whisk.
Pour over the bread.
Chill, covered for 8-12 hours.
Uncover and bring to room temperature.
Bake at 350° on the middle oven rack for 40 minutes or until the bread is puffed out and the edges are golden brown.

title: peanut butter crunch cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix first three ingredients until crumbly.
Set aside 2/3 cup.
Add to remaining mixture the water, oil and eggs.
Beat for 2 minutes at high speed, scraping bowl frequently.
Pour into prepared 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle reserved crumbled mixture over the batter. Then sprinkle with the chocolate chips.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes. Cool completely before serving.

title: ranch-style baked beans
directions: In a large skillet, melt butter and brown meat.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into a 2 1/2 quart casserole dish. Bake at 350 degrees for 20 minutes.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown meat, then drain.
Lay hamburger in baking dish.
Layer cooked potatoes, cream of mushroom, onion and then Cheddar cheese. Bake at 300° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Take dressing mix, margarine and enough chicken broth to make mix moist.
Layer in greased casserole dish.
Second layer: mayonnaise, cut chunks of chicken, chopped onion, salt and pepper to taste.
Mix eggs and milk; pour over other ingredients.
If making ahead, refrigerate.
Before baking, pour can of cream of chicken soup over and spread evenly.
Garnish with cornflake crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: toasted pecans
directions: Spread pecans on pan.
Melt butter; pour over nuts.
Bake at 225° for 1 hour.
Stir occasionally.
Remove from oven
and salt.

title: chicken or turkey curry
directions: Cook chicken and remove from bones.
Cook broccoli.
Lay slices (pieces) of meat in baking dish.
Lay broccoli over meat. Mix creamed chicken soup and mayonnaise.
Pour over broccoli. Sprinkle with curry powder and lemon juice.
Sprinkle with grated sharp cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: date nut bread
directions: Mix boiling water, soda and dates.
Cool.
Add eggs, sugar, flour, salt and nuts.
Bake in 2 loaves at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: beef vegetable soup(busy mom version)
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Stir in sauce mix, water, bay leaf, salt, pepper and tomatoes (with liquid).
Heat to boiling, stirring often.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer, stirring occasionally, for 10 minutes.
Stir in noodles and vegetables. Cover; cook 10 minutes longer.
Preparation time:
30 minutes.

title: date balls cookies
directions: Combine margarine, sugar, milk, dates and nuts.
Cook over low to medium heat for 6 minutes.
Add Rice Krispies.
Mix thoroughly and cool slightly.
Roll into balls.
Roll balls into powdered sugar as you make them.
Can be frozen!

title: fruit salad
directions: Put juices of fruit in a saucepan and bring to a boil.
Put pudding in this and cook until well dissolved; let cool.
When cool, add to the fruits and mix well.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown hamburger and onion, then drain well.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 1 to 2 hours.
Serve with cornbread.

title: sausage, egg and cheese brunch dish
directions: Make layers of bread cubes in bottom of well-buttered casserole (or Pyrex).
Cover with half of the grated cheese and all of the meat.
Add remaining bread cubes on top and sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Mix eggs, butter, milk and salt in dish and pour over casserole.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 300 degrees for 45 minutes or until bread is slightly browned.
Casserole freezes well (unbaked) for 3 months.
Serves 8-10.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Saute mushrooms and onion in butter.
Add rice and water and bouillon cubes.
Cook for 15 minutes or until rice is done.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Cut baked potatoes in half.
Scoop out insides.
Reserve shells.
Beat potatoes and butter until creamy.
Beat in milk. Stir in onion, salt and pepper.
Spoon into reserved shells. Sprinkle with cheese.
Arrange in baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes, until heated through.
Sprinkle with paprika and serve.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Combine whipped cream and salad dressing in a large mixing bowl.
Add sugar, orange juice and fruits.
Cover and freeze.

title: monster cookies
directions: Beat butter, cream in the sugars and add eggs.
Stir in vanilla, syrup and peanut butter.
Add oats, chips and M&M's.
Form cookies in regular or monster size.
Bake in 350° oven for 12 minutes.

title: apple dip
directions: In a small bowl, beat cream cheese, brown sugar and vanilla until smooth.
Stir in chopped nuts.
Serve with apple wedges.

title: hot diggity hot dish
directions: Prepare macaroni and drain.
Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Mix well; turn into greased 2-quart baking dish.
Cover and bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: gingerbread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add well-beaten egg, molasses and hot water.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Pour into well-greased baking pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook onion in butter.
Add potatoes and chicken broth.
Cover and simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.
Add milk and cream.
Heat through.

title: crock-pot dressing
directions: Melt butter in skillet and saute onion, celery, parsley and mushrooms. Pour over bread cubes in a very large mixing bowl.
Add all seasonings and toss together well.
Pour in enough broth to moisten; add beaten eggs and mix together well.
Pack lightly into crock-pot.
Cover and cook on High for 45 minutes, then reduce to low for 4 to 8 hours.

title: quesadillas
directions: Place first 6 ingredients in large saucepan with enough water just to cover.
Bring to boil, then lower heat.
Continue cooking until water is reduced.
Remove chicken and shred.
Arrange flour tortillas on a large tray.
Top each tortilla with chicken, Cheddar cheese and cream cheese.
Top with another flour tortilla. Press gently together.
Bake at 325° until cheese melts.
Do not overbake or they will become hard.
Cut each tortilla into 4 equal pieces.
Top with salsa and serve.

title: french onion soup
directions: Preheat frypan.
Melt butter.
Add onions and saute until almost tender.
Add remaining ingredients, except broth.
When well blended, transfer to soup pan.
Add beef broth.
Continue to cook on low heat for about 30 minutes.
To serve, place toast round in soup bowl and sprinkle with cheese.
Pour soup into bowl.
Serve immediately.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread nuts and coconut in the bottom of the pan.
Mix cake mix as directed on box.
Pour cake mix over the nuts and coconut.
Melt margarine and cream cheese together in microwave.
Add powdered 4x sugar.
Spread over the cake mixture and cook all at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: roka cheese dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Serve with chips or fancy crackers.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: toffee bars
directions: Cream together margarine, sugar, vanilla and flour.
Spread onto a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until lightly brown.
Remove from oven and pour chocolate chips over the top. After slightly melted, spread with a knife and top with nuts.
Cut into squares after cooled.

title: easy dumplings
directions: Put undiluted cream of chicken soup in a bowl; stir in sifted flour, small amount at a time, until dough is thickened but still wet.
Pour mixture out onto floured board.
Work in just enough flour to be able to handle.
Roll out thin and cut into strips. Drop into boiling chicken broth.
Cook until done.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Top with almonds and bake at 450° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken and spinach
directions: Bread cutlets in crumbs and cheese.
Lay in baking dish. (Save leftover crumbs.)
Melt butter and saute onion until tender. Mix in flour, then pour milk in all at once.
Cook (stirring) until bubbly.
Cook 1 minute longer.
Add drained spinach and ham to sauce.
Spread on top of cutlets.
Cover with leftover crumbs and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: party turnovers
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In medium skillet, combine soup mix and meat. Brown well and drain.
Blend in cheese.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Lightly brown meat.
Add onion; cook until tender.
Add seasoning, beans and soup.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Mash hot potatoes; add milk and egg.
Add seasoning. Drop in mounds over meat.
If desired, sprinkle with 1/2 cup of shredded process cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken lasagna
directions: Saute onion, pepper and mushrooms until soft.
Heat soup and milk on top of onion and pepper until warm.
Layer in dish: 4 strips lasagna, 1/2 chicken, 1/2 cottage cheese, 1/2 Cheddar, 1/2 Mozzarella, 1/2 Parmesan and 1/2 chicken sauce with pepper and onion.
Repeat.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let set 15 minutes before serving.

title: heath toffee cookies
directions: Mix together shortening, sugar, egg and vanilla.
Blend together.
Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Stir into first mixture.
Add Heath bars.
Blend well into dough.
Drop rounded teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet 2-inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool slightly before removing from baking sheet.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Grease 10-inch casserole; line with peaches.
Cream margarine and 1/2 cup sugar.
Mix together flour, baking powder and salt. Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk and vanilla.
Spoon over peaches.
Mix remaining 1 cup sugar with water; bring to boil and stir until sugar completely dissolves.
Pour over batter. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until top browns.

title: chicken a la mexico
directions: Combine enchilada sauce, soup, chopped onion and garlic salt. Put a thin layer of corn chips on the bottom of a greased 1-quart baking dish. Add a layer of chopped chicken.
Add another thin layer of corn chips and another layer of chicken. Cover with sauce. Top with cheese. Bake approximately 30 minutes in a 350° oven.
Leftover chicken can be substituted for the chicken breasts and would be a good way to use leftovers.

title: raisin cheese ball
directions: Mix these ingredients together.
Dissolve 1/2 pack gelatin in 1/4 cup hot water.
Add to cheese mixture.
Add 1 1/2 cups raisins.
Refrigerate until firm.
Cover with slivered almonds.

title: mamma's tea cakes(this is a recipe susie james used years ago.)
directions: In a large bowl, mix sugar and oleo until creamy.
Add buttermilk and eggs.
Beat thoroughly.
Add soda, baking powder and salt.
Mix well.
Add vanilla.
Add flour to make a stiff dough.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake 1 hour at 350° or until bubbly.

title: peanutty caramel sauce
directions: Microwave all ingredients in medium microwave-safe bowl on High 2 1/2 to 3 1/2 minutes or until smooth, stirring every minute.

title: veal chops with mushroom sauce
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper in a paper bag.
Drop the chops in and shake until each chop is coated with flour.
Heat oil in a heavy skillet with garlic.
Add chops and brown on both sides. Drain off fat.
Mix mushroom soup with paprika, salt and marjoram, and pour over chops.
Cover and cook, stirring occasionally over low heat, about 20 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: punch
directions: Mix.
When ready to serve, add 1 quart ginger ale.

title: evergreen punch
directions: Dissolve sugar and Kool-Aid in water, add pineapple juice. Add ginger ale just before serving.
Serves 80 people.

title: microwave cabbage medley
directions: Toss together in microwave-safe bowl all the ingredients except bacon.
Top with bacon.
Cover tightly with plastic wrap; prick several holes in the top.
Cook on High power for 15 minutes, rotating twice during cooking.
Uncover carefully and toss lightly before serving.
Serves 6.

title: wild rice soup
directions: In a large skillet, saute chicken and onion until chicken is no longer pink and onion is tender.
Drain.

title: spinach with cheese
directions: Melt butter; add chopped onion.
Cover; cook over medium heat for 5 minutes.
Add frozen spinach; add milk.
Cook 5 to 7 minutes. Add cheese.

title: "easy" chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 6 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: flounder fillet florentine
directions: Cook spinach; drain well.
Fold flounder in small bundles. Arrange in shallow 6-cup baking dish.
Pour over water and lemon juice; sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cover tightly.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, or until fish flakes easily.
Remove from oven; drain cooking liquid into measuring cup (should be 3/4 cup). Heat in saucepan.
Combine milk and flour; mix well.
Cook over moderate heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Spread drained spinach around fish; pour sauce over and top with cheese. Bake at 425° until sauce bubbles.

title: tomato-tuna chowder
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, over high heat, heat 2/3 cup water to boiling. Stir in rice.
Heat to boiling. Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer 20 minutes or until rice is tender and all liquid is absorbed.

title: our kids cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugars and eggs.
Mix with dry ingredients. Add coconut, oatmeal, vanilla and chocolate chips. Make into a ball the size of a walnut. Press on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.
Yields 7 dozen.

title: burgundy beef
directions: Cut beef into cubes and roll in flour. Brown on all sides in hot oil. Add garlic and fry low for one minute. Transfer all of this into casserole dish (approximately 2 quarts).

title: cranberry salad
directions: In a large mixing bowl add all ingredients.
Stir with spoon until well mixed.
Spread in a 13 x 9-inch pan and freeze.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Melt the margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cut up chicken and place on bottom of pan in margarine.
Place peas and carrots on top.
Mix the soup, broth, Bisquick, mushrooms and onion together. Pour this mixture over the chicken mixture.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 400° until golden brown, about 45 minutes.

title: oven spanish rice
directions: In saucepan, cook onions and peppers in oil until tender, but not brown.
Stir in spaghetti sauce mix, tomatoes, rice, salt and water.
Simmer for 10 minutes, stirring often.
Pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover; bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes, or until rice is done.
Sprinkle with cheese; allow to melt in oven.

title: fancy margarita
directions: Mix all together. Stir well. Serve on rocks with salt.

title: texas pudding
directions: Cream together first 7 ingredients.
Place cherries in a 9-inch square pan.
Cover with dough mixture. Sprinkle brown sugar over top and add boiling water.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: cajun stew
directions: Boil cabbage and onion down. Brown hamburger and drain. Combine cabbage, onion, hamburger, kidney beans, diced tomatoes, tomato juice, chili powder, salt and pepper to taste. Simmer together for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: pudding frosting
directions: Mix first 2 ingredients and let set.
Then mix together next 4
ingredients
(in
Mixmaster).
Add pudding mixture to this and mix on high until all combined.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Combine beef, egg and seasonings; mix well.
Shape into small balls.
Brown in skillet.
Keep warm until ready to use.

title: mom's zucchini jam
directions: Combine water and zucchini.
Boil 6 minutes.
Drain well.
Add sugar, lemon juice and pineapple. Mix and boil 6 more minutes. Remove from heat and add Jell-O.
Stir well and put into jars or freeze.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix sugar, flour, pineapple, baking soda and salt; pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix brown sugar, nuts and coconut; crumble on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and top with icing.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain.
Add chili seasoning and stir well.
Add beans and tomatoes.
Add V-8 until desired consistency. Simmer for at least 15 minutes.

title: rave review coconut cake
directions: Blend cake mix, pudding mix, water, eggs and oil in large mixing bowl.
Beat at medium speed for 4 minutes.
Stir in coconut and nuts.
Pour into 3 greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Remove and cool on cake rack.
Fill and frost with Coconut Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Drain.
Mix in other ingredients.
Add Miracle Whip, salt and pepper to taste.

title: mexican dip
directions: Peel and mash avocados in bowl with lemon juice, salt and pepper.
In another bowl, mix sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning.
Spread bean dip in 9 x 9-inch serving dish.
Top bean dip with seasoned avocado mixture.
Spread on sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning mixture.
Sprinkle with chopped onion, tomatoes and olives.
Cover with shredded Cheddar cheese. Serve with chips.
Will keep in refrigerator 5 days.

title: picante sauce
directions: Put all the contents in a pot; cook until hot.
Do not boil. Pour into jars and seal.
Put jars back into pot and cook until boils.
Boil for 15 minutes.
Remove from stove and you are done.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place in
a
greased loaf pan or Pyrex glass container.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: glorified banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding and milk with electric mixer.
Add sour cream and Cool Whip.
Layer wafers, bananas and pudding in a 13 x 9-inch dish.
Makes 2 layers.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.

title: apple crinkle
directions: Mix and place in buttered baking dish.

title: pink salad
directions: Mix ingredients as given.
Chill and serve.

title: sliced baked potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes if skin is tough, otherwise just scrub and rinse them.
Cut potatoes into thin slices but not all the way through. Put potatoes into baking dish, placing them in slight fan shape. Sprinkle with salt and drizzle with butter.
Sprinkle with herbs. Bake at 425° for about 50 minutes.
Remove from oven; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake potatoes for another 10 to 15 minutes, until lightly browned, cheese is melted and potatoes are soft inside.

title: congealed salad
directions: Put the first three ingredients into mixer and mix well.
Stir in the last four ingredients.
Cover and keep refrigerated.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook diced potatoes and onion until tender.
Add other ingredients and simmer.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: corn fritters (pan-fried)
directions: Mix and beat 2 minutes; pour batter from a spoon into a frying pan in which melted fat has been placed.
Turn fritters and cook 5 minutes.
Drain and sprinkle with sugar, then serve.

title: chicken spaghetti casserole
directions: Combine chicken, onion, celery and soups; mix well.
Add drained spaghetti; place 1/3 of mixture in casserole.
Top with cheese.
Repeat until
all
is used.
Bake for 30 minutes until cheese is bubbly at 300°.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: mixed pepper salsa
directions: Dice all peppers.
Combine first 5 ingredients in a small saucepan; bring to a boil, stirring until sugar is dissolved. Remove from heat.

title: little pizzas
directions: Roll each biscuit out to about 4 inches in diameter.
Place on baking sheet.
Spread biscuit surface with tomato paste.
Sprinkle with oregano, if desired.
Add pieces of sausage, approximately 6 slices to each biscuit.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake in very hot 450° oven for 5 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: mexican wedding cake
directions: Mix sugar and eggs together.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Use 9 x 13-inch square pan.

title: chocolate top pumpkin pie
directions: Mix sugar, salt, cinnamon, ginger and cloves in a small bowl. Beat eggs in a large bowl.
Stir in pumpkin and sugar spice mixture.
Gradually stir in evaporated milk.
Pour into pie shell. Bake in a preheated 425° oven for 15 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 350°.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean.
Cool for 2 hours.
In a double boiler, melt Ghirardelli chocolate until smooth and completely melted.
Pour melted chocolate over the top of pie and smooth to edges of crust with a spatula.
Let chocolate harden.
Serve with whipped topping. Refrigerate remaining pie.

title: best banana bread
directions: Sift together first 4 ingredients.
Cream sugar and Crisco and then add one egg at a time; beat well.
Add bananas and sour cream.
