Stir in dry ingredients.
Pour into 2 bread pans, greased and floured.
Bake at 350° until toothpick comes out clean, approximately 50 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Beat eggs and mix all ingredients together. Bake at 300° for 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: chocolate-zucchini cake
directions: Cream together margarine, oil and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla and milk.
Mix together all dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Stir in zucchini.
Spoon batter into greased and floured 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle top with chocolate chips.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: chili for hot dogs
directions: Brown beef; add onions and brown.
Add catsup and chili powder. Simmer for 1 hour; stir occasionally and keep covered.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Tear lettuce and put in salad bowl.
Layer celery, eggs, peas, onion and green pepper.
Spread mayonnaise on top.
Sprinkle with cheese and bacon.
Top with tomatoes.
Refrigerate 8 to 12 hours or overnight.

title: easy pasta fagioli
directions: Cook cavetelli in 4 qts. boiling water until al dente, then drain.
Set aside.
Place oil and garlic in large frying pan. Saute until golden brown,
Remove garlic and discard. Add tomato and basil sauce and beans. Saute until hot.
Add the cooked cavetelli.
Stir and let simmer 2-3 mins.
Top with cheese and fresh basil.

title: cherry trifle
directions: Prepare custard mix according to package directions.
Chill until set. Beat custard with a rotary beater until smooth.

title: peach congealed salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water; add pie filling and pineapple.
Let congeal.

title: coney island casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cheese.
Put into a 2-quart baking dish.
Spread cheese over top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: italian lasagna
directions: Mix all ingredients, except Mozzarella cheese.
Layer cooked lasagna, cheese mixture and Mozzarella.
Continue to layer until desired amount is reached.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: easy chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli as directed until tender; drain.
Arrange stalks in a greased oblong baking dish.
Place chicken over broccoli. Combine mayonnaise, soup, lemon juice and curry powder. Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine crumbs and butter; sprinkle over all.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: lois' honey whole wheat loaves
directions: Scald milk; stir in oleo, honey, sugar and salt.
Cool to lukewarm.
Take bowl; add the 1 1/2 cups lukewarm water; sprinkle yeast over water.
Stir to dissolve.

Combine yeast with the milk mixture; add the white flour and 2 1/2 cups whole wheat flour. Mix until smooth with mixer or by hand; add rest of the whole wheat flour and work it until dough leaves sides of bowl.
Turn it out on board and let it rest 10 minutes.
Place in buttered bowl. Turn; cover with damp towel and let rise until double in size, about 1 1/2 hours.
Punch down.

title: low-fat summer pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta until it is al dente.
Drain pasta and run under cold water.
In a large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Toss until well mixed.
Chill in refrigerator until ready to serve.
Less than 1 gram fat per serving.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Beat eggs well; add soda and oil.
Add cake mix and dry pistachio pudding.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350° in buttered Bundt pan.

title: pecan pie
directions: Bake in 325° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: mary's snooty tooty tuna
directions: Combine soup and water.
Add 1 cup noodles, tuna, celery, cashews, onion, salt and pepper.
Toss lightly.
Place in an ungreased baking dish.
Sprinkle remaining noodles over top.
Bake in a 375° oven for 15 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Garnish with orange sections.

title: slumgolean
directions: Peel and slice potatoes; put in bottom of crock-pot.
Add browned hamburger, soups and water.
Peel and slice onion and layer rings on top.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Do not stir!
Cook on low for 8 hours.

title: old-time buttermilk pie
directions: Cream butter (oleo) and sugar; add flour.
Stir in eggs, mixing well.
Add buttermilk, vanilla and nutmeg.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake for 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.
Allow to cool before cutting.

title: chris hyde's chicken
directions: Lay chicken breasts in a baking dish.
Cover with slices of Swiss cheese.
Mix soup and white wine together.
Pour over chicken and cheese.
Cover with stuffing mix.
Pour melted butter or margarine over all.
Bake, uncovered, 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: pineapple pound cake
directions: Grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan; set aside.
Cream the butter and sugar.
Add the eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition.
Sift the flour and baking powder.
Add the flour in small batches to the creamed mixture alternately with the milk, beginning and ending with the flour.
Add vanilla and stir in undrained crushed pineapple and juice; blend well.
Pour batter into pan and place in cold oven.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until top springs back when touched lightly.
Let cake stand for a few minutes in pan before removing.
Combine melted butter, confectioners sugar and drained pineapple until sugar is dissolved.
Spoon over cake while still hot.

title: tina's vegetable mess
directions: Heat oil in a large skillet.
Add squash and zucchini; cook until soft.
Set on paper towels to drain.

title: creamy garlic dressing
directions: Stir ingredients together and mix well.
Cover and chill. Yields one cup.

title: parmesan pepper pull aparts
directions: Grease 9 x 5-inch or 8 x 4-inch loaf pan.
Saute onion and pepper in margarine until tender.
Cool.
Stir in cheese. Separate dough into 10 biscuits.
Partially split each biscuit in half.
Spoon scant teaspoon of mixture into each biscuit.
Gently press edges where split to seal.
Stand biscuits in 2 rows in length of pan.
Drizzle any remaining mixture over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 22 to 28 minutes or until golden brown.
Cover with foil during last 5 minutes to prevent excessive browning.
Cool 3 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix together the first 4 dry ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Add melted margarine.
Add the rest of the ingredients and mix well.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Using a tablespoon, put mixture on cookie sheets.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.

title: tagliarini
directions: Brown onion, garlic and green pepper in oil.
Add beef and brown, stirring frequently.
Add tomato sauce, raw noodles and enough boiling water to cover.
Cook until noodles are done, about 15 minutes.
Add corn, olives and mushrooms.
Put in baking dish. Sprinkle with grated cheese and brown in oven.
This works well as one-dish meal for a party.

title: martin's stew
directions: Mix ground beef, onion soup mix, garlic powder, and bell pepper; pat mixture flat. (Oblong pancake size.) Put diced potatoes in the middle of flattened ground beef. Take ends of meat and pinch together to seal in potatoes. Completely seal the meat roll in the tin foil. Place in baking pan; cook 1 to 1 1/2
hours at 350°. Remove meat roll from foil and top with your choice of topping. (Hot brown gravy, cream of mushroom, cream of chicken soup or grated cheese.)

title: lemon delight
directions: Melt butter.
Add crushed graham crackers; mix well.
Put in 9 x 12-inch cake pan.
Mix pineapple, pie filling, nuts, Cool Whip and Eagle Brand milk together.
Spread over graham crackers. Refrigerate until set.
Sprinkle with crushed nuts if desired.

title: salmon fish cakes
directions: In a medium bowl, combine first 8 ingredients.
Shape into 8 patties.
Put bread crumbs on a plate and coat patties with crumbs.
In heavy 12-inch skillet, heat corn oil over moderate heat for 1 minute.
When hot, add the patties and cook about 3 minutes on each side or until golden brown.
Transfer to a heated platter.

title: my mom's chocolate cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Use two 9-inch layer pans.
Measure all ingredients into a large mixing bowl.
Blend 1 minute at low speed.
Blend 3 minutes on high speed.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes. Cool and frost with favorite frosting.

title: jam cake
directions: Add dry ingredients in a large pan.
Mix wet ingredients together.
Combine all ingredients and mix well. Pour into 2 layer cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Cool chicken and remove bones; set aside.
Mix flour, salt, pepper, egg and milk together.
Roll out on floured surface.
Cut into strips and then into bite size pieces.
Drop into broth (over low heat).
Add additional broth or water, if needed.
After all the dumplings are in the pot, add soups and extra cup of milk.
Let cook slowly for 30 minutes, then add chicken.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Remove skin from chicken, if desired.
Dip each piece in margarine.
Mix dry ingredients in a Ziploc bag and shake each piece to coat.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: potatoes supreme
directions: Place potatoes in a saucepan and cover with water.
Bring to a boil; cover and cook until almost tender.
Drain and cool. Combine soup, 1 1/2 cups cheese, sour cream, onions, salt and pepper; stir in potatoes.
Place in a greased 13 X 9 X 2 baking dish.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350 degrees for 25 to 30 minutes or until heated through.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Place peanuts in
a
baking
pan.
Sprinkle
them
with salt. Heat salted peanuts
at
200° for about 3 minutes until salt lightly clings to
them.
In
a
pot
combine sugar, corn syrup and water.	Cook over low heat stirring constantly until mixture becomes very brittle.
Remove from heat.
Quickly stir in butter and lemon
extract.
Add peanuts.
Pour mixture into a shallow greased pan.
When	cool
enough
to handle, stretch mixture to desired thickness.	Allow
to harden and break into irregular pieces.
Yields 1 to 1 1/4 pounds.

title: taco torte
directions: Brown beef with onion.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce and taco seasoning.
Simmer 15 minutes.
In large casserole, layer tortillas, meat sauce and cheese (ending with cheese on top). Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: fiesta banana cake
directions: Measure flour, baking powder, soda, salt and sugar into sifter.
Place shortening in mixing bowl; stir to soften.
Sift in dry ingredients.
Add 1/4 cup milk and mashed bananas.
Mix until flour is dampened.
Beat 2 minutes in mixer at low speed or 300 vigorous strokes by hand.
Add the eggs, vanilla, nuts and remaining milk.
Beat 1 minute more.

title: cream raisin pie(glenn's favorite)
directions: Cook all together. Add to pie shell. Add top crust. Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: crab cheese fondue
directions: In saucepan over low heat, melt cream cheese in wine, stirring constantly.
Coat Swiss cheese with cornstarch.
Stir crab meat, Swiss cheese, milk, Worcestershire sauce and parsley into wine mixture.
Heat through.
Transfer to fondue pot to keep warm. Spear bread cubes with fondue fork; dip into fondue.
Makes 3 cups.

title: baked chicken reuben
directions: Put chicken in a greased 9x13 pan.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Place drained kraut over chicken and top with Swiss cheese.
Pour dressing evenly over cheese.
Cover with foil and bake at 325 degrees for about 1 1/2 hours.
Sprinkle with parsley. Serves:

title: lime congealed salad
directions: Pour over loaf and bake your usual time.

title: orange congealed salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in one cup boiling water; add gelatin dissolved in a little juice.
Add juice from fruit and enough water to make 3 cups.
Add in this order:
pineapple, orange sections, marshmallows.
Pour in dish and allow to congeal slightly.
Whip cream and add a little sugar, about 1 teaspoon.
Add mayonnaise to whipped cream.
Spread on top of slightly congealed salad and sprinkle with grated cheese.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add all but the cheese.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts and mixture bubbles.

title: easy bake potatoes
directions: Cut unpeeled potatoes in 1 1/2-inch chunks.
Arrange in single layer in shallow baking pan with onion chunks tucked in between. Melt margarine with garlic halves.
Remove garlic; drizzle over potatoes.
Sprinkle layer with salt, pepper and celery seed.
Cover and bake for 45 minutes in 400° oven.
Remove foil, sprinkle with paprika and continue baking for about 20 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chili parlor chili
directions: In a large (4 quart or more) pot add ground chuck, bit by bit, to water and stir until beef separates to a fine texture.
Add all ingredients.
Stir well to blend.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for about 3 to 4 hours.
Stir occasionally. The last hour, spoon off any grease.
May be covered after desired consistency is reached.
Remove bay leaves.

title: jackie b's peanut butter coffee cake
directions: Topping:
Stir together 1/2 cup brown sugar and 1/2 cup flour. Cut in 1/4 cup peanut butter and 3 tablespoons margarine.
When crumbly, add miniature chocolate chips.

title: hot buttered rum
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix with electric mixer; freeze. To serve, use 1 to 2 teaspoons of mixture per cup of boiling water.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Blend in egg and applesauce.
Combine water and soda; set aside.
Sift together all dry ingredients.
Add water and creamed mixture.
Blend in raisins and nuts.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: fresh cauliflower soup
directions: Cut out cauliflower core, remove outer leaves and separate into small florets.
Combine cauliflower in medium saucepan with onion, thyme and chicken broth. Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat. Simmer, partially covered, until cauliflower is tender, about 10 minutes. Remove and reserve about 1/3 of cauliflower.
Transfer remaining cauliflower mixture to food processor or blender. Whirl until smoothly pureed.
In a 3 to 4-quart saucepan, melt butter over medium heat. Stir in flour, salt, nutmeg and pepper.
Cook until bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Gradually mix in half and half. Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture boils. Blend in cauliflower puree and cheese.
Heat, stirring occasionally, until soup is steaming and cheese melts.
Add reserved cauliflower. Cook just until heated through, about 3 minutes.
Serve sprinkled with parsley.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Saute onion in shortening.
Add beef, cook until brown and crumbly; drain.
Add corn and soup.
Pour into greased pie dish. Combine mashed potatoes, milk and egg.
Spoon in mounds over beef mixture.
Bake at 350°
for 30 minutes.

title: baked chicken nuggets
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a plastic bag; shake well.
Cut chicken into 1-inch pieces; dip chicken pieces in butter, and shake a few at a time in breadcrumb mixture.
Place on a lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until tender.
Yields 4 servings.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix margarine and brown sugar and set aside.
To make syrup, mix sugar and water and cook a few minutes; set aside.
Cut shortening into flour; add milk.
Roll dough into a large rectangle.
Spread brown sugar mixture over dough.
Roll up jelly roll style.
Slice dough into 1/2-inch thick slices and place over peaches and cinnamon.
Bake in a 13 x 9-inch dish at 350° until dough is done.

title: caribbean fudge pie
directions: Beat butter and sugar in large bowl until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add chocolate, coffee and rum extract; mix well.
Stir in flour and chopped nuts.
Pour into pie shell.
Decorate top of pie with walnut halves.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes in lower third of oven.
Cool on wire rack.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour or until ready to serve.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: blender spaghetti sauce
directions: In large blender container, blend tomatoes until smooth.
Pour some of tomatoes into another container if your blender is small. To half a blender container of pureed tomatoes, add all other ingredients and puree or blend until smooth.
If you like meat in your spaghetti sauce, brown the beef in a large skillet and drain grease.
Add other ingredients and simmer until desired consistency.
Serve over cooked, drained spaghetti.
Garnish with Parmesan cheese.

title: spaghetti italiano
directions: Brown meat.
Add onion and green pepper; cook until tender and drain.
Add all ingredients, except spaghetti, butter and cheese. Simmer, uncovered, for 1 hour.
Remove bay leaf.
Prepare spaghetti.
Serve with Parmesan cheese.

title: easy chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix all ingredients until well blended. Drop by teaspoonfuls or roll into small balls and place on a cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
An ideal recipe for children!

title: tropical glazed turkey meatballs
directions: Combine ground turkey, 1/4 cup onion, egg substitute and 1/4 teaspoon cinnamon.
Shape into 20 meatballs.
Spray skillet with nonstick cooking spray.
Heat over medium-high heat for 30 seconds.
Add meatballs; cook 2 to 4 minutes until browned, turning frequently.
In small bowl, blend pineapple topping, marmalade, remaining 1/4 cup onion and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add to skillet; stir to coat meatballs.
Reduce heat to low and cover; cook 10 minutes or until meatballs are no longer pink in center and onion is tender.
Makes 5 servings.

title: layered salad
directions: Arrange lettuce in bottom of salad bowl, then in layers, add celery, green pepper, onion, peas. Spread salad dressing or mayonnaise over layer of peas. Sprinkle sugar, then put cheddar cheese over mayonnaise. Refrigerate overnight. Just before serving, sprinkle bacon on top.

title: french onion quiche
directions: Saute onions in butter until golden and soft.
Combine with cheese and put in pie crust.
Combine rest of ingredients and pour over cheese and onions.
Bake in preheated oven at 375° for 45 minutes or until a knife blade, when inserted, comes out clean. Cool slightly to serve.
Serves 6.

title: aunt connie's italian cream cake
directions: In a bowl, sift together the flour, spices, soda, and baking powder.
In a large bowl, cream together the butter and sugar. Add the egg yolks and coconut; mix well.
Add alternately the flour mixture and buttermilk.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Fold in the stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in layers at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: swiss steak
directions: Cut steak into 1 to 1/2-inch strips.
Brown in skillet, turning once.
Slice the peppers and onion.
Put on top of steak, then add puree and 1 can of water.
Simmer at 300° for 30 minutes or until tender.

title: italian beef
directions: Put all ingredients in Dutch oven, covered.
Bake at 300° for 4 hours.
Turn once midway through cooking.
Cool, then slice. Great for company!

title: chicken continental
directions: Dust chicken with flour and brown in butter.
Remove chicken. Stir seasonings, cream of chicken soup and water into drippings. Cook and stir to a boil.
Spread Minute rice (right from box) in 1 1/2-quart shallow casserole dish.
Pour all but 1/3 cup soup mixture over rice.
Stir to moisten.

title: mexican corn bread and beef
directions: Cook and drain beef.
Mix 1 cup cornmeal and soda in a bowl; add the eggs, milk, salt, corn and bacon drippings; mix well. Place remaining cornmeal in a greased skillet and brown.
Pour 1/2 the corn bread mix into skillet and add beef; sprinkle with peppers, cheese and onion.
Pour remaining corn bread mix over onions.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.
(This takes at least a 10-inch skillet or can be placed in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish to bake.)
Makes 6 to 8 servings.
Add a salad and dinner is ready.

title: new orleans corn pudding
directions: Heat butter and sugar in saucepan until sugar is dissolved. Stir in flour and mix well. Remove from heat and gradually stir in milk. Add eggs and baking powder. Mix well. Add corn and spoon into pan. Bake at 350° for 70 minutes or until firm. Combine brown sugar and cinnamon and sprinkle over top of casserole, then drizzle melted butter over top. Return to oven for 5 minutes.

title: chicken casserole with apples and cheese
directions: Cooking Time: 35 to 45 minutes.
Servings: 6.

title: chicken creole
directions: Spray skillet with non stick coating. Preheat pan over high heat.
Cook chicken in hot skillet for 3 - 5 minutes, or until no longer pink.
Reduce heat.
Add tomatoes and their juice.
Add celery, onion, garlic, basil, parsley, green peppers, chili powder, crushed red pepper, and salt.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 10 minutes.
Serve over hot white rice.
Serves 4.

title: pumpkin custard bread
directions: Mix ingredients together, then add pecans.
Fill well-greased floured pan and put into oven at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
It is done when knife comes out clean.

title: italian dip
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer softened cream cheese, Ragu sauce, sprinkled with Italian seasoning.
Follow with sliced pepperoni. Top with cheese.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Serve with chips. Serves 12 or more.

title: gee-gee bars
directions: Mix well (like pie crust).
Pat 2/3 into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with Chocolate Mixture.
Sprinkle rest of crust on top.
Pat down.
Bake at 350° for approximately 25 minutes.

title: pig cake
directions: Blend together.
Bake in 3 layers in 8 or 9-inch pans for 30 to 35 minutes at 325°.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat
and sausage with onion.
Combine with large jar Prego sauce.
Cook	noodles as directed on package.
First layer would be
sauce mixture, layer noodles, then sprinkle on grated Mozzarella	and
Parmesan cheeses.	Repeat until pan is full, ending with
sauce	and
cheeses
on
top.	Bake at 350° until heated through.

title: zucchini saute with basil(like a pesto)
directions: Using a food processor or hand grater, finely shred zucchini. In a mixing bowl, toss zucchini shreds with salt, mixing well. Let them stand for about 10 minutes.
Then pick up small handfuls of zucchini and, working over the sink, squeeze the zucchini tightly to extract as much liquid as possible (much of the salt will go down the drain with the liquid).
Put the zucchini shreds in another bowl and toss with basil.
In a large skillet, heat olive oil with garlic over moderate heat.
As soon as garlic sizzles, add zucchini-basil mixture and saute about 4 minutes. Spoon over cooked pasta and add pepper and Parmesan cheese.

title: biroux(german hamburger)
directions: Brown hamburger meat and drain.
Add spice and mix well.
Add cabbage and onion and cook about 15 to 20 minutes.
(May need to add a little water.)

title: quick vegetable soup
directions: Cook and stir ground beef, celery and onion in Dutch oven until brown; drain.
Stir in potatoes, sauce mix, water and tomatoes with liquid; break up tomatoes with fork.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer, stirring frequently; cook 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: raspberry salad
directions: In large bowl, dissolve jello in boiling water.
Stir in rest of ingredients (except lettuce).
Pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish. Refrigerate until congealed.
Serve on lettuce.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: old fashion chocolate pie
directions: Mix together all ingredients and pour into 2 pie shells.
Bake 45 minutes at 375°.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables by directions on box.
Mix onion, celery and mayonnaise together; add to your vegetables.
Add Cheddar cheese.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Seed persimmons by pressing through a sieve with the water. Add sugar to persimmon pulp, then beaten eggs.
Stir soda into buttermilk and add alternately with the sifted dry ingredients. Lastly, stir in butter.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: yum yum salad
directions: Dissolve Knox gelatine in 1/2 cup cold water.
Put crushed pineapple and sugar in double boiler and heat until sugar is dissolved.
Mix gelatine with pineapple and sugar and let set until thick.
Mix grated cheese, nuts and Cool Whip; mix this with thickened gelatine and pineapple.
Let chill overnight.

title: olive oil pickles
directions: Cover with weak vinegar about 1/3 vinegar and 2/3 water.
Put in kettle or crock and cover.
Let stand for four days.
Stir each morning.
Can on fourth day.

title: cocoa apple cake
directions: Beat together eggs, sugar, margarine and water until fluffy. Sift flour, cocoa, soda, cinnamon and allspice.
Add to creamed mixture and mix well.
Fold in nuts, apples and vanilla until evenly distributed.
Spoon into greased and floured 10-inch loose bottom pan.
Bake at 325° for 60 to 70 minutes until cake tests done.
May use Bundt pan also.
Sprinkle powdered sugar on top of cake.

title: jello dessert
directions: Mix jello with 2 cups boiling water.
Add 1 1/2 cups cold water.
When dissolved, mix pineapple and strawberries into jello. Pour 1/2 of mixture into pan; let set until firm.
Spread sour cream over layer.
Add bananas.
Pour rest of mixture and chill.

title: texas chocolate cake
directions: Mix together, beat well, set aside.
Melt 2 sticks margarine. Add 4 tbsp cocoa and 1 cup water to the melted margarine.
Bring to boil.
Add to the first mixture and beat well.
Place in a greased 9 x 13 baking dish.
Bake 25 minutes or until done on 350°.

title: yummy sausage stir-fry
directions: Cook rice according to package directions and keep warm. Saute vegetables in oil until crisp and tender.
Add sausage and season to taste.
Heat thoroughly.
Mix in 1/2 cup of the Parmesan cheese and serve immediately over the warm rice.
Sprinkle with the remaining Parmesan cheese.

title: crab dip
directions: In saucepan, melt cream cheese and Cheez Whiz.
Add Worcestershire sauce, onion and green pepper.
Fold in crab meat and stir only long enough to mix, but not to break up crab lumps. Serve warm with crackers, bread sticks or raw vegetables.

title: great aunt ruby's buttermilk pie
directions: Combine sugar and flour; add melted oleo and blend well.
Add beaten eggs.
Combine soda and buttermilk; add to first mixture. Stir in lemon juice and grated rind.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into unbaked shell and bake at 375° for 40 to 60 minutes or until brown or almost firm.

title: cranberry-orange nut bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a loaf pan, 9 x 5 x 3-inch.
Mix sugar, shortening and egg thoroughly.
Stir in milk.
Blend in dry ingredients; stir in.
Blend in cranberry halves and nuts.
Pour into pan.
Bake 60 to 70 minutes.
(Crack in top of the loaf is characteristic.)
Cool thoroughly before slicing with a very sharp serrated knife.

title: coconut-pecan cake
directions: Cream together butter, shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Add vanilla. Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Add alternately with buttermilk to creamed mixture; blend well.
Mix coconut and pecans with 1 tablespoon flour and stir in.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Sift the flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt.
Combine juice, rind, shortening and boiling water to make 3/4 cup liquid. Add egg and add to dry ingredients.
Stir only enough to mix. Stir in nuts and cranberries; let stand 20 minutes.
Make shallow in center of pan.
Bake 60 or 70 minutes in a 350° oven.
Yields 1 loaf.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix well.
Store in an airtight container.
Add 3 heaping tablespoons of mix to 1 cup of hot water.
Stir.
Makes a large quantity or make only half of recipe.
Keeps well.

title: rhubarb crisp
directions: Cut rhubarb in chunks into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Then take flour, oleo, sugar and salt and pour over rhubarb.
Then take a bowl and mix all your other ingredients which are flour, sugar, baking powder, eggs, salt and oats.
This will be a crumbly mixture.
Pat on top of rhubarb mixture.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Cook sugar, molasses, syrup, water, salt, butter and vanilla until mixture forms a soft ball in cold water.
Take off stove and pour over popcorn.
Make into balls.
Makes about 20.

title: briam
directions: Pour olive oil in an 11 x 17-inch roasting pan.
Add garlic, onion, zucchini, potatoes and tomatoes.
Mix together and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cover and bake at 350° for about an hour. Uncover and sprinkle with cheese.
Continue baking until potatoes are tender and cheese starts to melt, about 15 to 20 minutes. Makes 6 to 8 servings as a side dish.

title: mother's cornbread
directions: Bake at 400° until brown.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix as any cookie recipe.
Pinch off in small balls.
Place on cookie sheet.
Mash with a fork.
Cook 15 minutes at 350°.

title: fast candy
directions: Combine sugar and corn syrup in a pan.
Bring to boil on medium heat.
Turn heat off and stir in peanut butter.
Add corn flakes which have been crushed after measuring.
Stir until well coated and drop by teaspoonfuls on waxed paper to cool.
Yields 3 to 4 dozen.
Very fast and very delicious.

title: hawaiian pie
directions: Combine flour, sugar and salt.
Add to the scalded milk, gradually, in a double boiler; cook unti thick, stirring constantly.
Pour small amount of mixture over egg yolks.
Return to boiler and cook 3 to 4 minutes longer.
Add butter and a little lemon juice, pineapple and coconut.
Cool.
Pour into pie shell and top with meringue.
For meringue, fold 6 tablespoons sugar into egg whites.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: eggnog cherry pound cake
directions: Cream together on low speed butter, sour cream and sugar until light and fluffy. Beat in eggs. Sift together dry ingredients. Combine eggnog and rum. Alternately add eggnog mixture and dry ingredients to butter and sugar until all are combined. Batter will be very thick. Pour half of batter into greased and floured Bundt pan. Spread cherries on top of batter and top with remaining batter. Bake at 325° for 90 minutes. Cake is done when golden brown and sides pull away from pan. Do not underbake.

title: baked beans
directions: Cook ground beef and onions until brown; drain.
Add catsup, mustard, brown sugar and Worcestershire sauce.
Put beans in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Add meat mixture; stir.
Put wax paper across top.
Microwave on High for 5 minutes.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Dip chicken into melted butter. Roll in dry ingredients.
Place chicken in baking dish sprayed with Pam.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 400°.
Serves 6.

title: ugly duckling cake
directions: Combine cake mix, fruit cocktail with syrup, 1 cup coconut, eggs in large bow.
Blend at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or when cake springs back.
Bring butter, granulated sugar and milk to a boil.
Boil 1/2 minute.
Remove from heat.
Stil in remaining coconut.
Spoon over hot cake in pan.
Yummy.

title: touchdown tea
directions: Combine lemon-flavored ice tea mix and Hi-C Hula Punch.
Blend in vanilla ice cream.
Just before serving, add Sprite.
Serves 40.

title: country market soup
directions: Boil bean mixture gently in remaining ingredients for 3 to 4 hours, adding water, if necessary.
Stir occasionally.
Add salt and pepper, if desired.
Serve with rice and cornbread.
Serves 26.

title: key lime pie
directions: Fold everything together. Pour into baked or graham cracker pie crust. Top with additional Cool Whip if desired.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender or mixer.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Reduce to 350° for 20 minutes or until pie is congealed when slightly shaken.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Combine ingredients in order listed in a blender or mixer bowl.
Blend or beat until onion is incorporated.
Store in glass covered container in refrigerator.
Makes 4 1/2 cups.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix and beat hamburg with 2 eggs.
Add remaining ingredients, except tomato sauce.
Pour tomato sauce on top of formed meat loaf.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes, or until done.

title: yvonne salad
directions: Chop vegetables.
Combine all ingredients and refrigerate.

title: meat loaf wellington
directions: Combine 1/4 cup gravy with hamburg, bread crumbs, egg, onion, salt and pepper; mix together.
Shape into loaf and place in baking pan.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Separate rolls; place them over top and sides of meat loaf, overlapping slightly.
Bake 15 minutes more.
Meanwhile heat remaining gravy to serve with loaf.

title: grandma's scripture cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add beaten egg yolks, honey, milk and 3 cups of flour which has been sifted with spices and baking powder.
Use the remaining flour to flour the fruit.
Add beaten egg whites before fruit and flour is added.
Add floured mixed fruit.
Bake in a greased and floured pan for 60 minutes at 350° until done.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Heat all soups and water to boiling in saucepan.
Grease a 9 x 12-inch pan (sides and bottom).
Spread rice on bottom.
Pour half of soup mixture over rice.
Place chicken parts on top.
Pour rest of soup mix over chicken.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.
Remove foil and bake at 275° for 30 minutes.

title: leftover quiche
directions: Combine rice, 1 ounce cheese and 1 egg and pat into pie pan for crust.

title: refrigerator nut cookies
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and vanilla.
Beat in egg.
Add nuts and dry ingredients.
Knead until smooth.
Shape in a roll; wrap in waxed paper.
Chill well.
Slice to bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: broccoli corn muffins
directions: In a bowl, stir all ingredients just until combined.
Fill greased muffin cups three-fourths full.
Bake at 350° for 20-25 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes before removing from pan.

title: butterhorn dinner rolls
directions: In a large bowl, sprinkle yeast into very warm water; stir until dissolved.
Add beaten eggs, sugar, butter and salt, then beat in 5 cups flour.
On lightly floured pastry sheet, knead dough until smooth and elastic (about 10 minutes).
Place dough in a large greased bowl and refrigerate, covered.
Use a third of dough at a time.
This can be made about a week ahead, if desired.

title: sausage stew
directions: Combine soup, milk, onion and mustard in medium bowl; blend well.
Spread sauerkraut in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Top with uncooked noodles.
Layer noodles with sausage pieces.
Spoon soup mixture evenly over top.
Sprinkle this with Swiss cheese.
Cover pan tightly with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until noodles are tender.
Combine bread crumbs with butter and put on top of casserole and bake for additional 10 minutes or until crumbs are toasty brown.

title: deluxe chicken sandwich
directions: In medium bowl, combine chicken, chopped cucumbers, mayonnaise and dill weed.
Toss gently to mix well.
Cover; refrigerate 2 to 4 hours.
Serve on bottom halves of sandwich buns.
Arrange spinach, tomatoes and chicken filling.
Replace top halves.
Makes 2 sandwiches.

title: potato puffs
directions: In mixing bowl, beat egg yolk.
Add potatoes, cheese, parsley, onion and garlic powder; mix well.
Beat egg whites until stiff; fold into the potato mixture.
Brush eight baking cups with melted margarine.
Spoon potato mixture into cups.
Brush remaining margarine over potatoes.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes until lightly brown.

title: charlie's favorite
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll in small balls; press down with a fork and bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.
This recipe was given to the class in Bible school 25 years ago.

title: blueberry treat
directions: Mix ingredients and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan, saving 1/2 cup for topping.

title: chicken in tarragon cream
directions: In a small bowl, stir together sour cream, tarragon, sugar and cornstarch. Set aside.
Sprinkle chicken breasts with salt and pepper. Dredge in flour, shaking off excess. Heat butter and oil in a wide frying pan over medium-high heat.

When fat sizzles, add chicken breasts and cook until golden (about 3 minutes on each side). Add wine, lemon juice, onion and garlic. Cover, heat and simmer until meat in thickest part is no longer pink when slashed (10 to 15 minutes).
Remove from heat.
Lift out chicken and arrange on platter. Stir sour cream mixture into pan juices. Return to low heat and cook, stirring until sauce bubbles and thickens slightly.
Pour over chicken and rice.
Makes 2 to 4 servings.

title: chicken crescent almondine casserole
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients; top with last 4.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: creamy mushroom soup
directions: Chop half of the mushrooms.
Slice remaining half of mushrooms.
In a 3-quart saucepan over medium heat, melt 2 tablespoons butter; add sliced mushrooms.
Cook until tender. Remove mushrooms from saucepan.
In same pan, over medium heat, melt remaining 3 tablespoons butter and add chopped mushrooms, celery and onions; cook until tender.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper until smooth.
Cook, stirring constantly, 1 minute. Gradually stir in milk, chicken broth, parsley flakes and Worcestershire sauce.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture boils and thickens.
Stir in half and half and sliced mushrooms. Lower heat and cook until thoroughly heated.
Makes 6 (1 cup) servings.

title: pecan balls
directions: Form into balls and bake 25 minutes.
Roll in 10x sugar when cool.

title: gingerbread
directions: Mix all ingredients except eggs.
Mix well.
Beat eggs in a bowl and add to mixture.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix thoroughly.
Pour into pie shell (unbaked).
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 400°.

title: helen rushton's apple pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Combine apples, 1/4 cup sugar and water in large saucepan.
Cook on medium heat until apples soften and become transparent.
Drain apples, reserving both apples and 3/4 cup of liquid.
Combine 1 cup plus 2 tablespoons sugar, flour, cinnamon, nutmeg and vanilla in saucepan.
Add reserved 3/4 cup apple liquid.
Cook on medium heat until mix boils and thickens. Add butter and reserved apples.
Stir until apples are coated. Spoon into pie shell.
Moisten pastry edge with water.
Cover with top crust.
Fold top edge under bottom crust.
Flute with fingers. Cut slits or design for steam to escape.
Cover edge to keep from over browning.
Use foil to cover edges.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°.
Bake for 25 minutes or until crust is golden brown.
Cool to room temperature before serving.

title: cream cheese dip
directions: In a medium bowl, mash the cream cheese up with a fork.
Add a little milk to work with; just keep adding some milk until you get it creamy, but not soupy.
Add your grated pickle, then add sour cream and onion, if you like.
Ready to serve with chips.
Keep refrigerated.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: In a large skillet, combine ground beef, cream of chicken soup, tomatoes, enchilada sauce and olives; simmer about 25-30 minutes. Stir in 1/2 c. Cheddar cheese.
In 9x13-inch baking dish, layer tortillas and sauce mixture, ending with sauce.
Garnish with Cheddar and Jack cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fiesta rice
directions: Brown beef and celery in shortening. Add remaining ingredients. Cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes or until rice is tender. Ready to serve.

title: egg rolls
directions: Reserve 1 tablespoon of egg.
Mix remaining flour, salt and water with fork until all dry ingredients are moistened.
Knead until smooth.
Wrap in plastic wrap.
Refrigerate 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cucumber spread
directions: Mix together cream cheese, onion, mayo & garlic powder.
Peel cucumber, remove seeds, then finely chop into tiny pieces, then press dry.	Add to cream cheese mixture.
Serve on bread or crackers.
Yum!

title: noodle and spinach mold
directions: Saute mushrooms in 1/2 cup butter until tender.
Combine all the ingredients and mix well.
Butter and crumb a 2-quart ring mold.
Place mixture in mold, cover with foil and bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Remove from oven, loosen sides by running a knife along the edge and invert immediately on a platter.
Fill center with whole mushrooms that were sauteed in butter.
Serves 8.

title: old fashioned applesauce cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large mixing bowl.
Pour into greased and floured cake pan, 9 x 13-inch or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool on cake rack.
Serve plain or with a light lemon glaze.

title: pasties - cornish
directions: Cut in shortening until size of peas.
Gradually add next ingredients.
Wrap and chill 1/2 hour.

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Bring peanut butter, stick of butter, water and oil to a boil and take off stove.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let cake cool.

title: people puppy chow
directions: On low heat, melt butter, peanut butter and chocolate chips. Pour cereal into large mixing bowl.
Pour melted mixture over the cereal and mix well.
Pour coated cereal into a large paper bag and sift powdered sugar over cereal mixture.
Shake well to coat.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix well, put in greased shallow casserole dish and bake at 350 degrees for 20 -30 minutes or until bubbly and lightly browned. Serve with Triscuits.

title: chicken pie
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Grease 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
Layer with chicken, sliced eggs and Veg-All.
Mix soup and broth and pour over chicken.
Mix flour, milk and butter and pour over other; don't stir.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until golden brown.

title: creole peas
directions: Cook peas as usual.
Mix all together and cook until bell pepper and onion are tender.

title: patio pancakes
directions: Mix ingredients.
Drop on greased skillet.
Serve with syrup or top with applesauce and cinnamon.

title: quick and easy cookies
directions: Place in large bowl and mix thoroughly with hand.
Roll into small balls and place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.

title: peanut butter pinwheel candy
directions: Cream the margarine and syrup until smooth. Add vanilla and salt. Mix in sugar, 1/2 cup at a time, until well blended.
Knead until stiff and firm.
Pat into a 9 x 12-inch pan.

title: peanut butter roll
directions: Cream together peanut butter and sugar; beat in cream.
Shape in 2 rolls, 1-inch in diameter.
Combine remaining ingredients and pat mixture around roll.
Wrap in waxed paper; chill.
Cut in 1/4-inch slices.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Saute fresh mushrooms slightly. Melt butter in pan and pour soup into it.
Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate in greased glass or ceramic pan.
Bake later in day at 350°
(uncovered) for 1/2 hour.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix all together.
Cook in Bundt pan at 300° until center is done.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Boil macaroni until tender; drain.
Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: hot olive cheese puffs
directions: Blend all ingredients (except olives).
Mix well and wrap 1 teaspoon dough around each olive, completely covering.
Wrap and freeze.

title: sugarless double raisin walnut bread
directions: Mix first six ingredients in a large bowl with a fork. In a small bowl, beat egg slightly with a fork. Blend in buttermilk and oil.
Stir into flour mixture just until flour is moistened.
Pack batter into greased loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°. Cool before removing from pan.

title: sukiyaki
directions: In wok, brown steak or chicken.
After browned, put in a pile in wok.
Add broth.
Add in wok with meat in piles, green onions, bamboo shoots and mushrooms.
(Add liquid in bamboo shoots and mushrooms for flavor.)
After all ingredients are added to wok, simmer until veggies are tender.
Season with soy sauce to taste. Serve over rice.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Place 4 cups of popped corn in a double brown bag (grocery bag).

title: bran muffins
directions: Combine cereal, flour, sugar, soda and salt in large bowl. Make well in center of dry mixture.
Add eggs, buttermilk and oil. Mix just enough to moisten dry ingredients.
Store mix in covered bowl in refrigerator until ready to bake.

title: russian tea cakes
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix butter, sugar and vanilla.
Stir flour, salt and nuts together.
With hands, work in flour mixture until dough holds together.
Form dough into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes until set, but not brown.
While warm, roll in confectioners sugar.
Cool; roll in sugar again.
Makes 4 dozen 1-inch cookies.

title: hawaiian pie
directions: Bring
pineapple,
sugar,
flour,
cherry juice and dry jello to a boil.	Let cool, add nuts and sliced bananas.	Pour into baked pie shells.
Chill.
Cover with Cool Whip.

title: buttery baked chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Spray a cookie sheet with Pam and melt the stick of butter and pour it into the pan.
Beat the eggs in one bowl and combine the crackers, season salt, garlic powder and black pepper in another bowl.
Dip the chicken breast into the eggs first and then coat it very well with the cracker mixture.
Bake for 30 minutes, turn the breasts over and bake for another 30 minutes.
The chicken will be buttery, crunchy and delicious.

title: jerusalem artichokes(as an appetizer)
directions: Wash the Jerusalem artichokes well and crisp in ice water. Sprinkle with salt and pepper to season.
Eat out of the hand as you would radishes.

title: lemon pepper roast
directions: With pastry brush, coat whole tenderloin with Kitchen Bouquet. Coat completely with lemon pepper.
Bake in very hot oven (425°) for approximately 1 hour, more or less depending on degree of "doneness" desired.

title: tomato gravy
directions: Melt butter in large skillet over medium heat. Add shallots and saut until tender. Stir in tomatoes. Bring to a boil and simmer, stirring constantly, 2 to 3 minutes. Stir in whipping cream, tomatoes, sugar, bouillon and pepper. Simmer, stirring often, for 3 minutes or until thickened.

title: "tootsie's" coconut cake
directions: Put everything in bowl in order given.
Beat until thick and creamy, about 10 minutes.
Put in tube pan.
Place in cold oven. Turn heat to 350°.
When it reaches temperature, bake for 40 minutes or until tester comes out clean.

title: never fail rolls
directions: Cream together Crisco and sugar. Add egg and salt.
Mix yeast in warm water.
Add flour alternately with yeast mixture to Crisco batter until easy to work on board.
Knead remaining flour into dough.
Let rise until double, about 1 1/2 hours.
Punch down. Make into rolls.
Rise again.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Saute butter and onions in skillet. Add soup, Cheez Whiz and water.
Stir until well blended and melted.
Add rice to mixture and stir.
Fold in thawed broccoli and stir.
Pour into casserole dish.
Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Can be frozen the day before or freeze for later use. Serves 6 to 8.

title: peggy's mexican meat loaf
directions: Mix ground chuck, onion, egg, crackers and 1/4 cup picante sauce.
Separate into 2 halves.
Spread one half in bottom of loaf pan.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top.
Pour 1/2 cup picante sauce on top over cheese.
Cover cheese and sauce with second half of meat mixture.
Be sure to seal in all cheese.
Garnish top with swirls of ketchup and slices of bell pepper.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Pour off fat drippings.

title: dixies
directions: Mix oleo and sugar.
Add eggs; mix well.
Slowly add flour and salt.
Mix well.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Mix well and put in a lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven. Cool slightly.
Dust with powdered sugar.
Cut into squares.

title: jello cake(quick and easy)
directions: Bake cake as directed on package. Poke holes into cake with a fork.
Mix jello with 2 c. of boiling water on stove.
Pour jello over hot cake.
Refrigerate.
When cake is cooled, frost with Cool Whip.

title: low-fat soup
directions: Throw together in large pot and cover with water.
Cook until all is tender.

title: never fail chocolate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients adding boiling water last.
This will be very thin, but will make 1 large 2-layer or 3 small layers.
Bake at 350°.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Melt butter; add cocoa, sugar, eggs and flour.
Beat well. Add nuts and coconut.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and spread Marshmallow Creme while cake is hot.

title: all in one dish pork chop dinner
directions: Slice potatoes and onions thinly.
In a casserole dish put potatoes and onions.
Season with salt and pepper.
Arrange string beans on top.
Mix soup according to directions and pour part over potatoes and beans.
Add bits of cheese.
Put seasoned pork chops on top.
Put rest of soup on chops and garlic powder.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
(Use portions of ingredients that are right for your family.)

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

Mix meat with onions, eggs and crackers; roll into medium-size meatballs. Refrigerate for 30 minutes. Fry meatballs in cooking oil until done. Drain excess grease by putting meatballs on a few paper towels and placing them in warm oven for 10 minutes.

title: dick's chicken chili
directions: Saute onions and garlic in margarine.
Add chicken and all other ingredients.
Cook until hot, then simmer on low at least 40 minutes so spices can meld.
Serve over rice or with tortilla chips.

title: simple chicken rice casserole
directions: Grease casserole dish.
Put in rice and onion soup mix.
Place chicken on top.
Pour on soup and water.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: strawberry jello dessert
directions: Mix crackers, sugar and butter together.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
While cooling, melt marshmallows and milk in double boiler.
Pour over crust and chill until firm.
While chilling, mix strawberry jello as directed on package.
When dissolved, add strawberries and chill until syrupy, then pour over marshmallow mixture.
Return to refrigerator until firm.

title: sunday chicken
directions: Grease a large 8 x 13-inch dish.
Place instant rice in first. Heat soups and milk and pour over rice.
Lay chicken over that mixture.
Sprinkle the dry onion mix over the chicken.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours and 15 minutes.

title: chicken bake
directions: Prepare macaroni according to package directions.
Drain. Saute pepper and onions in margarine, add mushrooms and cook until onions and pepper are tender.
Combine macaroni, cheese, onion mixture, soup, milk and pepper.
Mix well.
Stir in chicken and olives.
Pour in baking dish.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and top with almonds.
Bake, uncovered, for 10 minutes.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Dissolve soda in 1 cup water.
Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
It will be very thin.
Pour into 11 x 13-inch pan or 2 layer pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix together the cheeses, eggs, seasonings and cream in a large bowl. Layer mushrooms, meat, vegetables and onions alternately with the egg mixture. Sprinkle with a little extra cheese on top if desired. Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until quiche is solid and crust is golden brown.

title: lemonade ice cream pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip, frozen lemonade mix and milk.
Pour into pie crusts.
Cover and freeze 8 hours or overnight.
Serve frozen.

title: hickory beans
directions: Cook for 40 minutes at 325°.
Stir occasionally.
(The top will crisp over when done.)

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine thawed green beans with soup and 1/2 can onions.
Pour in casserole dish and place in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Remove from oven and put remaining onions over casserole.
Return to oven for 5 to 10 minutes to brown onions.

title: punch
directions: Chill all ingredients thoroughly.
Mix juices and just before serving, add ginger ale and sherbet.
Serves 40 to 50.

title: luscious fruit delight
directions: Whip condensed milk; add remaining ingredients and stir. Cover and chill until ready to serve.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: country captain chicken
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Remove chicken skin; coat chicken with mixture of flour, salt and pepper.
In Dutch oven or roaster, brown chicken in melted shortening.
Remove from pan.
To pan drippings, add onions, ground beef and garlic.
Saute until lightly browned.
Add water, ketchup and thyme and mix well.
Add chicken, coating each piece with sauce.
Cover and bake 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Remove chicken from sauce and place on platter with rice.
Add carrots to sauce and pour over chicken. Sprinkle with almonds.
Serves
6 to 8.

title: cocktail hotdogs
directions: In a 2 qt saucepan, heat jelly and mustard. Add wieners and smokies. Mix well. Cook over low heat until hot, about 5 minutes, stirring frequently.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Arrange lettuce in bottom of deep large bowl.
Layer the following ingredients:
celery, green bell pepper, onions and peas.
Do not toss.
Spread mayonnaise over the peas.
Sprinkle with sugar and then cheese.
Cover and refrigerate at least 4 hours.
Toss and sprinkle with bacon bits just before serving.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cheesy cocktail swirls
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine cream cheese, onion, bacon and milk; mix well.
Separate dough into 4 rectangles; firmly press perforations to seal.
Spread about 2 tablespoons cheese mixture on each rectangle.
Roll up, starting at longest side.
Cut each roll into 8 slices.

title: seven layer salad
directions: First Layer: In large bowl, chop or tear lettuce.

title: hot mustard sauce
directions: Mix mustard and oil in a bowl.
Add 2 tablespoons water.
Stir until it is a smooth paste.
Stir sugar, cornstarch and salt in a wok.
Add 1/2 cup water and vinegar; thoroughly blend.
Cook at 225°.
Stir constantly until mixture thickens.
Gradually add to mustard mixture; stir until blended.
Refrigerate.
Bring to room temperature before serving.
Stir before serving.

title: cauliflower and broccoli salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sugar, vinegar, salt, and pepper in large bowl.
Add vegetables and toss to mix.
Makes 10 cups.

title: beans and sausage
directions: Mix all together and simmer 30 minutes. Serve over rice.

title: crunchy hot chicken salad
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients; toss gently and set aside. Combine mayonnaise and water; beat with wire whisk until smooth. Pour over chicken mixture; stir well.
Add eggs, and toss gently. Spoon into a greased 2-quart shallow baking dish, cover and refrigerate 8 hours or overnight.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Sprinkle with potato chips and cheese; bake an additional 5 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: orange julius
directions: Blend in blender until ice is crushed.
Serve immediately garnished with orange slices.

title: tagliarini
directions: Brown garlic, onions and oil; remove from pan.
Brown ground chuck; drain grease.
Add and simmer 30 minutes the corn, olives, liquid and tomatoes.
Cook noodles as directed.
Combine all ingredients in baking dish(es).
Cook at 375° about 25 minutes. Cover with grated cheese.
Bake about 15 minutes longer until cheese is melted.
Serves 16.

title: hamburger divine casserole
directions: Saute onions in some margarine and set aside.
Boil, drain and rinse noodles with cold water.
Brown meat and add tomato paste, Worcestershire sauce, Tabasco sauce, salt and oregano.
Mix sour cream and sauteed onions.
Add cottage cheese and softened cream cheese.
Grease either 2 (1-quart) baking dishes or 1 (2-quart) dish.
Put 1/4 of noodles in each dish.
Pour melted margarine over noodles.
Add 1/2 cheese mixture with onions to each dish. Add remaining noodles and top with meat mixture.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes.
Freezes well and serves 8 to 10.

title: pickled peaches
directions: Drain peach juice into saucepan.
Add enough vinegar to bring to your own taste; should be tangy.
Add spices (the ground ones will darken the peaches, but tastes fine). Add sugar to taste. Simmer for 5 minutes.
Taste and adjust.
If too sour, add a little water to dilute vinegar.
Add peach halves and heat to boiling. Pack in a jar or plastic container.
A jar with lid works best.
Refrigerate for 1 week if whole spices were used, less if ground spices were used.
This recipe may also be made with fresh peaches, just add more sugar.

title: uncooked play dough
directions: Mix flour and salt.
Gradually add water and oil, allowing time for the oil to be absorbed into the mixture.
Knead the dough until the mixture forms a ball.
Add flour if the dough becomes too sticky.

title: artichoke spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° until blended. Spread on crackers or bread as an appetizer or snack.

title: favorite pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Preheat griddle to 375°.
Pour batter into 4-inch circles and cook for approximately 2 to 3 minutes on each side.
Butter immediately.

title: peanut butter cremes
directions: Beat together first 6 ingredients, then stir in 1 cup more sifted confectioners sugar.
Add more if needed to make firm tiny balls.
Roll each ball in peanuts.
Place on waxed paper and refrigerate.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix all ingredients in one bowl.
Before baking, mix some sugar and cinnamon together.
Roll the cookie dough into small balls and roll in the sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for about 15 minutes or a little longer if needed.
The top should be a little puffy, but not hard.

title: taco dip
directions: Blend first 3 ingredients.
Spread on serving plate.
Add vegetables on top.
Serve with tostados.

title: chicken-broccoli
directions: Cook broccoli until slightly tender; drain well.
Make sauce of the mayonnaise, soup and lemon juice, not heated but mixed.
Place a thin layer of the sauce in the bottom of a buttered 2-quart baking dish, then add broccoli, a thin layer of sauce, the chicken next, then remaining sauce.
Top with cheese and crumbs.
Bake until bubbly at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, flour, melted margarine, vanilla and salt.
Mix thoroughly.
Blend in buttermilk.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender. Drain. Add butter, salt, pepper and milk. In a bowl, beat eggs; add onions, cheese
and bread. Put all ingredients in dish for oven and bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes. Cube about 4 pieces of wheat bread; spread melted butter over bread and toast in oven. Put on top of casserole.

title: pumpkin-spice cake
directions: Combine eggs, oleo and pumpkin in a mixing bowl. Add cake mix. Beat on medium speed for 2 minutes. Stir in 3/4 cup nuts. Pour into a greased 9 x 13 pan. Sprinkle with butterscotch chips and remaining nuts. Bake at 350° for
35 to 40 minutes or until toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean. Cool on a wire rack. Yield: 12 to 15 servings.

title: texas cole slaw
directions: Put all vegetables in mixing bowl and toss lightly.
In another bowl (or blender) combine remaining ingredients.
Beat until blended and smooth.
Pour dressing over vegetables; toss lightly, cover and refrigerate overnight.
This keeps 5 to 7 days.

title: potato salad dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients and whip until all are blended.
Pour over potato salad.

title: macaroni shrimp salad
directions: Cook macaroni in salted water and the oil.
Rinse and cool. Add shrimp, onion, celery seed, and chopped boiled eggs, leaving one to slice on finished salad.
Mix in salad dressing to desired moistness.
Top with sliced egg and sprinkle with paprika.
Best if made the night before and let set.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: In a 2-quart microwave container with handle (2-quart glass measuring bowl is ideal), put sugar and Karo.
Stir with wooden spoon.
Microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Remove.
Add peanuts (2 cups of nuts makes a very nutty candy, I used 1 1/2 cups).
Stir. Microwave on High 4 minutes.
Remove, add butter and vanilla; stir.
Microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Remove, add soda and stir and immediately pour on greased foil.
Spread out quickly.

title: broccoli and ham soup
directions: In a 3-quart glass microwave-safe casserole dish, combine onion, garlic and butter.
Microcook at High for 3 minutes or until onion is tender.
Stir in ham, broth, broccoli, undrained tomatoes, water, macaroni and nutmeg.
Cover and cook on High for 15 minutes or until boiling, stirring once to break up broccoli. Continue cooking on Medium for 8 minutes or until broccoli and macaroni are tender.
Garnish with Parmesan cheese, if desired. Makes 6 servings.

title: low-fat baked apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Coat bottom and sides of 2-quart casserole with nonstick cooking spray.
In bowl toss apples in lemon juice.
Pour into casserole dish and sprinkle with sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Stir to coat apples.
Combine remaining ingredients in bowl and spread topping over apples.
Bake until top is golden brown, about 30 minutes.
Serve with low-fat topping if desired.

title: tuna or salmon croquettes
directions: Put corn flakes in blender or food processor.
Process to fine crumbs and remove to shallow bowl.
Beat egg well; add onion and Worcestershire sauce.
Drain tuna well and mix thoroughly with egg mixture.
Add crushed corn flakes and salt and pepper to taste; stir in.
Form balls 1 1/2-inches in size.
Cover well with crushed corn flakes, pressing flakes firmly.

title: love light yellow 2-egg chiffon cake
directions: Heat oven to 350° (moderate).
Oil lightly and dust with flour 2 (8 x 1 1/2-inch or 9 x 1 1/2-inch) layer cake pans or 1 (13 x 9 1/2 x 2-inch) oblong pan.
Beat egg whites until frothy.
Gradually beat in 1/2 cup sugar.
Beat until stiff and glossy.

title: heavenly fruit and rice dessert
directions: Cook rice according to package directions. Rinse with cold water.
Combine rice, pineapple chunks, cherries, orange sections and sweetened condensed milk in a large fruit bowl.
Top salad with coconut.
Cover with plastic wrap and chill for 15 minutes or until ready to serve. Makes 8 servings.

title: peach bread
directions: Puree peaches and 6 tablespoons of sugar in the blender (mixture should yield 2 1/4 cups). Combine dry ingredients.
Set aside.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix ingredients and bake for 30 minutes in 350° oven.
cool cake and add Topping

title: twinkie cake
directions: Mix pudding according to package directions; let set 5 minutes, then pour over Twinkies.
Layer on top of pudding the pie filling, then the Cool Whip and top with chopped nuts.

title: hot jimmy deans
directions: Brown meats together and drain grease.
Add cheese and heat until melted.
Add seasonings; mix and spread on sliced party rye. When frozen, put in plastic bags.
When ready to serve, bake on cookie sheets at 400° for approximately 10 minutes.
Watch closely!

title: scripture cake
directions: Follow Solomon's advice for making good boys and girls (Proverbs 23:14).
Bake in loaf pan at 375° for 45 to 60 minutes or until wooden pick comes out clean.

title: breakfast before
directions: Cube bread to cover the bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Beat 12 eggs; add salt and pepper to taste.
Add milk.
Brown and drain sausage.
Add browned sausage to egg mixture.
Pour this mixture over the bread.
Top the mixture with the cheese and place in the refrigerator overnight.
In the morning, bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until done.

title: microwave fruit salad
directions: Pour pudding mix into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Stir in juice from pineapple and mandarin oranges to make 1 cup liquid. Microwave on High, uncovered, for 4 minutes, stirring after 2 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Cool for 15 minutes before adding pineapple and oranges.
Stir.

title: caramel corn
directions: Boil together all except popcorn and soda for 5 minutes, then add soda.
Pour over popped popcorn.
Bake in oven at 200° for 1 hour.
Stir once in a while.

title: debbie heuring's cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients except for 1 cup nuts.
Form into large ball and roll into the remaining nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: sour milk wacky cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients into cake pan.
Make 3 holes in dry ingredients.
Put one teaspoon vanilla in one hole, 5 tablespoons oil into second hole and 1 tablespoon vinegar into third hole. Pour 1 cup sour milk on top and mix well.

title: international coffee(economy version)
directions: Use blender, adding small amounts until fine.
Use 1 teaspoon per cup of hot water.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Beat cake mix, oil, eggs and sour cream in large bowl on medium speed 2 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally. Spread half of batter in pan, 13 x 9, greased. Stir together brown sugar, pecans and cinnamon. Sprinkle over batter. Carefully spread with remaining batter. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until deep golden brown. Drizzle a powdered sugar glaze over cake.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt oleo, chocolate chips and peanut butter in microwave on 70% power for 1 minute.
Stir, then microwave until melted, about 1 more minute.
Put cereal in a very large bowl.
Pour melted chocolate mixture over cereal.
Stir.
Put one cup powdered sugar in bag, paper or plastic.
Put cereal mixture in bag.
Put one more cup powdered sugar in bag over cereal.
Shake.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Make into small balls; bake until done, about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: almond balls
directions: Roll into balls and roll in confectioners sugar.
Serve.

title: muffuletta sauce
directions: Mix well and marinate for 24 hours.
Keep refrigerated.

title: briciole stuffed steak
directions: Prepare stuffing according to package.
Lay steak flat and spread stuffing on top.
Combine cheeses and sprinkle on top of stuffing.
Top with mushrooms.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together and form ball.
Roll in chopped nuts.

title: top hot beef bake
directions: Mix crumbs, milk, egg, meat, cottage cheese, horseradish, salt and pepper.
Spread in greased baking pan (8 x 8 x 2-inch).
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour.

title: julie's chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
Spray bottom of 9 x 13 pan. Cook stovetop stuffing according to package directions and layer on bottom of pan.
Drain cans of chicken and spread over stuffing. Mix soups and sour cream and spread over chicken.
Sprinkle with shredded cheese and bake for 40 minutes.
Take out and sprinkle with more shredded cheese and Ritz crackers.
Bake for 10-15 minutes, until crackers are browned.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix powdered sugar and peanut butter until crumbly.
Put 3/4 of the mixture in a cooled baked pie shell and top with pudding. Top that with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle remaining peanut butter mixture on top.

title: easy potato dish
directions: Brown the hamburger and onion.
Drain.
Place in the bottom of a deep dish pie pan.
Add a layer of frozen peas.
Combine soup and milk and pour over the peas.
Add a layer of Tater Tots.
Sprinkle cheese over the top and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: orange fruit salad
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate.

title: party beets with pineapple
directions: In saucepan, combine first 3 ingredients.
Stir in pineapple with syrup.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and bubbles.
Add butter and lemon juice; stir.
Add beets and heat thoroughly.

title: speedy chinese plum sauce
directions: On low heat, cook until melted.
A lovely glaze or accompaniment to pork, ham, chicken or spareribs.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Soften cream cheese to room temperature.
Add sugar gradually, beating until creamy.
Add salt and vanilla and enough cream to bring to spreading consistency.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Real butter makes it taste better.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix the ingredients.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together for crust.
Spread into 9 x 13 baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes.
Mix together cream cheese and 1 cup sugar.
Stir in Cool Whip and spread on cooled pretzel crust.
Dissolve jello in boiling water (2 cups).
Stir in frozen berries and let stand for 10 minutes.
Pour over cheese mixture and chill.

title: mexican rice
directions: Cook and stir onion and peppers in hot butter for about 2 minutes until tender, not brown.
Add remaining ingredients except rice.
Bring to full boil, breaking down tomatoes with spoon. Stir in rice.
Cover; remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes. Fluff with fork.
Makes 4 servings.

title: raspberry jello salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Add water to make 2 cups of juice.
Bring to a boil and pour over jello.
When dissolved, add cold water.
Mix pineapple and pie filling into jello mixture and refrigerate in a 9 x 13-inch pan until set.
Cream the sugar, cream cheese and sour cream.
Spread over jello and sprinkle chopped nuts on top.

title: old english date pie
directions: Line a 9-inch pie pan with pastry.
Sprinkle sliced dates into pastry.
Combine remaining ingredients, except coconut, and beat with rotary beater.
Pour over dates.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 300° for 30 minutes and sprinkle coconut for the last 10 minutes.

title: vegetable bar or pizza
directions: The night before making vegetable bar, mix together the first 4 ingredients and place in refrigerator until ready to make the bar.
Place crescent rolls onto a cookie sheet and press together with edges up.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Let cool. Spread the cheese mixture on cooled rolls and layer with next 6 ingredients.
Sprinkle top with shredded cheese.

title: brown sugar chess pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add beaten eggs and other ingredients.
Do not beat at high speed.
Pour into two pie shells or 10 to 12 individual cheese tarts.

title: angel pie(yields one 9-inch pie)
directions: Mix cornstarch and 3/4 cup sugar in saucepan.
Add boiling water, stirring constantly.
Cook until thick and clear.
Add salt to egg whites and beat until stiff.
Add 3 tablespoons sugar and vanilla, beating until whites are creamy.
Pour hot cornstarch mixture slowly over egg whites, beating constantly.
Cool slightly and fill pie shell.
Cover with whipped cream, then sprinkle with chocolate or nuts.
Chill 2 hours.

title: sensational salsa
directions: Chop in small pieces. Mix. Then top with squeeze of lemon. Salt to taste.
Or blend in blender.

title: chocolate chip kiss cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Remove wrappers from Kisses.
In a large mixing bowl, beat butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla until well blended.
Add flour; blend until smooth.
Stir in mini chips.
Mold scant tablespoon of dough around each Kiss, covering completely.
Shape into balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool completely.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: crabmeat shrimp casserole
directions: Put ingredients together; grease casserole.
Bake in 350° oven for 1/2 hour or until heated through.
Lovely luncheon dish with a green salad.

title: neiman-marcus cake
directions: Combine powdered sugar, cream cheese and eggs.
Mix well and pour over cake batter in cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: peanut butter sauce for ice cream
directions: Combine sugar, water, corn syrup and salt in a saucepan; boil for 1 minute.
Remove from stove and add the peanut butter.
Stir. Enjoy.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Grate the zucchini.
Put everything in mixing bowl; beat until well mixed with hand mixer.
Grease and flour bread pans.
This makes two loaves of bread.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: honeybear brownies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Blend in honey or syrup and vanilla.
Add eggs one at a time and beat well after each addition.
Combine flour, cocoa and salt.
Gradually add to creamed mixture.
Add nuts and pour into 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: nine bean soup
directions: Sort and wash bean mix.
In large kettle, cover beans with 6 to 8 cups water.
Bring to boil; boil 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Cover and let stand 1 hour.
Drain.
Add 2 quarts cold water and ham.
Bring to boil.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours or until beans are tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Simmer 20 to 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Makes about 3 quarts.

title: lemon party pie
directions: In a saucepan mix lemon pudding, sugar and 1/2 cup water. Blend in egg yolks, 2 1/2 cups of water and cook as directed on pudding box.
Blend in lemon juice and butter.
Cool 5 minutes, stirring twice.
Pour into cooled, baked 10-inch pie shell.

title: chili cornbread
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
In another bowl, beat eggs lightly.
Add buttermilk, butter and creamed corn.
Blend with dry ingredients; pour one third of batter into a 9-inch pan.
Pour in one half of chiles and one half of the cheese.
Pour remaining batter in pan and top with rest of chiles and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Slightly beat eggs.
Add sugar, milk (substitute part with half and half or evaporated milk).
Add vanilla and salt.
Put in crust. Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake in hot oven (400°) for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 300° and bake until firm or when knife blade placed in center comes out clean, approximately 1 hour.

title: pepperoni bread
directions: Roll bread dough thin (about 10 x 18 inches).
Brush on 2 tablespoons butter; sprinkle on seasonings.
Top with pepperoni, then cheese.
Roll up and seal ends.
Brush with remaining 1 tablespoon butter.
Bake on greased cookie sheet in 350° oven for 3 minutes.

title: baked bean-hamburger casserole
directions: Saute in skillet the bacon (cut in pieces) and the onion until lightly done (not crisp).
Brown the hamburger with the bacon and onion.
Put canned beans in casserole or bean pot with remaining ingredients stirred together.
Add meat-onion-bacon mixture.
Bake for 1/2 hour at 375°.

title: baptist pudding
directions: Mix flour, butter, and pecans together and press into a 9
X 13 inch pan.
Put in the oven and bake at 350 for 20 minutes (crust should be brown).

title: melt in the mouth cookies(suggest triple recipe)
directions: Cream the butter; add sugar, vanilla and egg.
Beat until light.
Add dry ingredients and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon (approximately size of hickory nuts) onto ungreased cookie sheets. Bake in hot oven (400°) for approximately 5 minutes.
(Do not overbake.)
Cool on cookie sheet 1 to 2 minutes. Remove to wire rack.

title: cranberry cabbage salad
directions: Combine cabbage and carrot in a large bowl.
Combine grapefruit juice, honey and spices for dressing.
Pour dressing over cabbage mixture and toss until well combined.
Cover and chill 1 to 2 hours.
When ready to serve, grate apple and add to salad with cranberries.
Makes 3 servings; 105 calories and 1 g fat.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Boil sweet potatoes in jackets until tender; drain.
Remove skins and mash with oleo.
Combine with sugar, vanilla, cinnamon, nutmeg and eggs; beat for 5 minutes.
Place in unbaked pie crust and bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Makes one 9-inch pie.

title: date nut balls
directions: Melt margarine and mix with sugar, coconut and dates.
Simmer a few minutes.
Take from heat and add Rice Krispies.
Make into small balls.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: broccoli and rice
directions: Saute onion in butter until clear.
Cook broccoli according to directions; drain.
Mix broccoli with soup and cheese.
Add onion. Stir in rice.
Season and mix well.
Put into greased casserole and top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Casserole can be made ahead and frozen.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Butter pie plate.
Cook covered with wax paper on High (10) in microwave for 9 to 11 minutes, turning after 5 minutes.

title: holubtsi (cabbage rolls)
directions: Core cabbage.
Place head in deep pot of boiling water.
Let stand until leaves are soft and pliable.
Remove from water; separate leaves.
Return head to boiling water if inside leaves require softening.
Pare down hard center rib on each leaf.
Add salt and rice to boiling water.
Cover; turn off heat.
Let stand until rice absorbs all water.
In large frying pan, saute onion in bacon drippings until tender.
Add pork and beef.
Cook until lightly browned.
Combine with rice.
Cool slightly then add beaten egg, garlic salt and pepper.
Line bottom of large baking dish with cabbage leaves.
Place heaping tablespoonful of the meat mixture onto a cabbage leaf.
Roll once, tuck in sides and roll completely. Arrange rolls in layers in casserole.
Season each layer with salt and pepper.
Pour tomato juice over rolls.
Cover with 2 or 3 large cabbage leaves.
Cover tightly.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour. Uncover; continue baking and basting for another 1/2 hour.
Serve hot with chopped crisp bacon, sour cream or tomato juice.

title: la pazada
directions: Brown meat with onion and bell pepper.
Drain.
Add seasonings, soup and tomatoes.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Place layer of tortillas on bottom of 10 x 13-inch dish.
Spoon 1/2 mixture on top.
Spread with grated cheese.
Place another layer of tortillas; spoon remaining mixture on top.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly, about 20 minutes.

title: prize none such mincemeat cookies
directions: Crumble the mincemeat and add the other ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart on a greased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: kiwi, star and strawberry fruit bowl* * * * *
directions: Luncheons may be as fancy or as simple as you prefer.
For a ladies luncheon, use plenty of flowers, your prettiest china and linen.
Sugared white grapes interspersed with sugared violets and leaves make a pretty centerpiece.
Just beat the egg whites until foamy.
Dip grapes, violets and leaves in the whites and place on waxed paper.
Sprinkle lightly with finely granulated sugar.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Mix and put in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole. Top with cheese and buttered bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: party chicken
directions: Flatten chicken breasts between waxed paper with rolling pin. Top each breast with dried beef. Roll to enclose filling. Wrap with bacon and secure with toothpick. Arrange in baking dish.
Mix sour cream with remaining ingredients in a bowl.
Pour over chicken.
Bake, covered, at 275° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Yields 8 servings.

title: pumpkin nut bread
directions: Assemble doughmaker.
Sift dry ingredients into large mixer bowl.
Quickly add all remaining liquid ingredients.
Mix with doughmaker at setting #12 only until dry ingredients are moistened. Bake in 2 greased pans in preheated 350° oven for one hour.
Let cool 5 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool on wire rack.
While warm, brush with butter and sprinkle with cinnamon-sugar mixture.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Put
rhubarb
in
shell.
Sprinkle with flour and sugar over rhubarb.
Beat eggs with 1 tablespoon water and pour over rhubarb. Dot
with butter.	Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then at 375° for 40 minutes.
Let cool and serve.

title: pecan pie
directions: Bring syrup to a boil in a 1 1/2-quart saucepan.
