Boil gently, uncovered, for 8 minutes.
Cool about 15 minutes.
Sprinkle nuts in pie shell.
Cream butter.
Blend in sugar, flour and salt.
Add eggs, syrup and vanilla; mix well.
Pour into shell.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes, or until pie is completely puffed across top and browned.

title: sausage biscuit bites
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In 10-inch skillet over medium-high heat, cook sausage, stirring to separate meat.
Drain on paper towel.
In large mixing bowl, stir soup.
Stir in milk, baking mix, cooked sausage and parsley.
Mix thoroughly.
Onto ungreased cookie sheet, drop about 2 teaspoons batter 1 inch apart.
Bake 12 minutes or until crisp and golden.
Makes about 60 appetizers.

title: tuna and apple salad
directions: In a large salad bowl, combine lettuce, apples, oranges, tuna and nuts.
Toss together.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook noodles in boiling water for 20 minutes.
Drain.
While noodles cook, combine soup, milk, water and cheese in medium saucepan.
Heat to boiling point, stirring frequently to prevent scorching.
Combine noodles, chicken, pimento, peas and carrots in large mixing bowl.
Pour cheese sauce over ingredients and mix. Place noodle mixture into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Melt butter or shortening; remove from heat.
Add brown sugar; mix well.
Add egg, vanilla and flour mixture.
Bake in a greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Do not overbake.

title: ora mabry's coconut pie
directions: Beat all together.
Put in 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake until crust is brown and pie is firm at 275°.

title: pork chop bake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Brown chops and drain.
Butter a 2-quart baking dish.
Arrange potatoes, mushrooms and chops.
In a small bowl, mix water and soup.
Pour over potatoes/mushrooms/chops. Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes, covered with foil.

title: marinated cabbage
directions: Bring vinegar, sugar, pepper, salt and mustard to a boil.
Add 1 cup vegetable oil while hot.
Pour over
cabbage mixture. Refrigerate after cools.
Better to let marinate a day or two.

title: sugarless fruit 'n' nut squares
directions: On a sheet of waxed paper, sift flour, baking soda and cinnamon; set aside.

title: chicken or tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles; drain.
Cook onions and green pepper in hot fat until tender.
Add flour and blend.
Add milk and cook over low heat until thick, stirring constantly.
Stir in chicken soup.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole. Garnish with almonds.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: swedish lace cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Melt butter in a small pan over low heat.
Remove from heat.
Add oatmeal; mix well.
Set aside.
In a small bowl, beat egg and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add oatmeal mixture and flour sifted with baking powder.
Stir until well blended.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased sheets.
Place 3 inches apart.
Bake 5 to 6 minutes.
Cool on baking sheet 1 minute.
Remove.
Makes 40.

title: savory veal chops
directions: Sprinkle veal chops with seasoning and pepper.
Coat large skillet with cooking spray.
Add oil and place over medium high heat until hot.
Add veal to skillet.
Cook 3 to 4 minutes on each side until browned.
Drain veal on paper towels.
Wipe skillet dry.
Add water, bouillon granules, wine and garlic to skillet. Bring to a boil, stirring to dissolve bouillon.
Reduce heat and simmer for 2 minutes.
Place onion in bottom of 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish; top with veal chops.
Pour wine mixture over veal. Sprinkle with mushrooms and rosemary.
Cover and bake for 25 minutes until tender.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Serve immediately.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: blueberry-pineapple salad
directions: Mix drained juices from blueberries and pineapple.
Take out 1 cup and set aside.
Pour remainder of juices into 2-cup measure and add enough cran-raspberry juice to make 2 full cups.
Bring to a boil.
Add the gelatin, previously soaked in water, and the fruit jello powder.
Stir well to be sure jello and gelatin are dissolved.
Add the reserved 1 cup of juice, the drained blueberries and pineapple and stir well.

title: fresh fruit salad
directions: If large fresh fruit are used, cut them into large pieces and set aside.

title: hungarin golosh
directions: Brown ground beef, onions, green pepper in 2 Tbsp. bacon grease until green pepper and onion are tender.
In boiler cook macaroni until done, drain and rinse.
Add beef mixture to macaroni and add tomatoes and soup.
Heat and season with salt & pepper.

title: cupcake cones
directions: Make cake mix according to box directions.
Place batter into each cone 3/4 full.
Put cones into a muffin pan to bake.
Bake according to box directions for cupcakes.
When cooled, ice them with frosting and add sprinkles.

title: scramble
directions: Mix oil and sauce together.
Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 250° for 2 hours, stirring every 15 minutes. Store in cans, tins, jars or plastic bags.

title: broccoli lasagna
directions: Mix together cottage cheese, eggs, salt, garlic salt and parsley.
In a buttered glass dish, place 2 or 3 layers of the following in the order shown:
noodles, cottage cheese mixture, broccoli, Monterey Jack cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Top with bacon strips. Bake at 350° until lasagna bubbles.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: mocha cheesecake
directions: Combine wafer crumbs, butter and sugar.
Butter sides and bottom of an 8-inch spring-form pan.
Press crumb mixture evenly onto bottom of pan.
Melt chocolate over hot, but not boiling, water.
Stir until smooth.
Beat the cream cheese until soft and smooth.
Add eggs, one at a time, to the cream cheese.
Gradually add sugar, mixing until well blended.
Add melted chocolate, instant coffee and salt.
Stir until blended.
Turn mixture into prepared pan.
Bake cake at 350° in center of oven for about 40 minutes or until cake center is almost set.
It will firm when chilled.
Let cheesecake cool on counter for about 45 minutes. Cover and chill for at least 4 hours or overnight.
Remove sides of pan.
Garnish with chocolate leaves and/or fresh raspberries or your choice of garnishes.

title: lemon tarts
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Beat until smooth. Line cupcake pan with cupcake papers.
Put vanilla wafers in bottom of each cupcake paper.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes. Cool, then add pie filling.
Store in refrigerator.

title: pizza on a muffin(low-fat)
directions: Spread pizza sauce on each half of muffin.
Add veggies to individual liking.
Sprinkle cheese.
Broil under broiler until cheese melts.

title: corn salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill several hours before serving.

title: party chicken
directions: Grease baking dish.
Line bottom with chopped beef.
Wrap chicken with bacon and arrange in baking dish.
Mix sour cream and soup.
Pour over chicken and let set overnight.
Bake at 275° for 3 hours.

title: "killer" cupcakes
directions: For Cupcakes:
Gently melt 4 ounces semi-sweet chocolate with butter.
Add vanilla.
In large bowl, beat 4 eggs until thick; add 1 1/2 cups sugar.
Beat in flour.
Fold in chocolate mixture. Spoon into 2 standard muffin tins with paper liners, each about 2/3 full.

title: cream cheese tarts
directions: Cream first three ingredients together and divide by teaspoon. Shape in muffin pans.
Beat egg and add sugar, butter and vanilla.
Fill the unbaked tarts with broken pecans.
Spoon mixture on top.

title: crunchy potato wedges
directions: Peel potatoes and cut into quarters.
Combine butter and garlic, mixing well.
Dip potatoes into butter, then into crumbs, coating on all sides.
Sprinkle with salt.
Place on lightly oiled baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 45 to 55 minutes or until done. Pour leftover butter over potatoes while cooking.

title: singapore noodle chicken stir-fry with sesame oil
directions: In a medium bowl, mix the ginger, curry powder, 1 tablespoon of the soy sauce and 1 teaspoon of the sesame oil.
Add the chicken and mix well.
Set aside to marinate for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: lime-garlic chicken
directions: Marinate for at least 20 minutes.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.
(I heat the juice and add to jello.)

title: manicotti casserole
directions: Boil noodles and drain.
Beat eggs, Ricotta cheese and parsley.
Cook and crumble hamburger; drain off grease.
Cook peas.
Mix eggs and Ricotta cheese mixture into noodles and add 2/3 spaghetti sauce.
Add Mozzarella cheese, cooked peas and cooked hamburger.
Put into a large casserole dish; top with remainder of sauce, Parmesan cheese and olives.
Cover.
Bake for 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine and mix together in bowl.
Pour into baking dish.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Beat in flour and sugars until well blended.
Add butter and gently stir in chips and walnuts.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: best in the south beans
directions: Brown beef; fry bacon, sausage and onion.
Drain off excess fat.
Combine with other ingredients.
Stir well.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 12 servings.

title: sour cream enchiladas
directions: Brown hamburger; mix together soup, sour cream and green chiles.
Quick fry tortillas.
Pour small layer of soup mixture in bottom of pan.
Fill tortillas with cooked meat, onions and cheese and place in pan.
Pour remaining soup mixture over tortillas. Cover pan with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: uncooked fruit cake
directions: Heat Pet milk; add marshmallows.
Stir in a double boiler until melted; add crushed graham crackers, raisins, candied fruit and nuts.
Press into a loaf pan.
Best if made 2 or 3 weeks in advance.
Keep refrigerated.
May be frozen.

title: apple pie cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In 3 quart saucepan, melt butter over medium heat. Remove from heat. Blend in sugar and egg. Add remaining ingredients, mix until blended. Turn into greased and floured 9 or 10-inch pie pan. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until top springs back when touched lightly. Serve warm or cold; cut in wedges and top with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: spicy french dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender.
Process until smooth.
Store in refrigerator until ready to serve.
Shake well before serving. This is a great light dressing for tossed salad.

title: fig preserves cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add oil, eggs and buttermilk; beat well.
Add preserves, pecans and vanilla; mix well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch sheet pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Make sauce; pour over cake while still warm from oven.

title: cheesy ham casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients except 1/2 cup cheese and croutons.
Spoon into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and croutons.
Bake 30 minutes or until thoroughly heated.

title: red raspberry cake
directions: Mix together the cake mix, flour and jello.
Combine water and oil; add to dry ingredients.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until done.
Let cool.

title: fruit tart
directions: Mix Bisquick and 1/3 cup sugar.
Cut in margarine until crumbly.
Mix in egg until soft dough forms.
Pat dough in 12-inch pizza pan.
Bake until edges just begin to brown, 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Mix in large bowl the yeast with warm water until dissolved. Then add sugar, melted Crisco and butter.
Add buttermilk; mix all ingredients, then add self-rising flour until thickness of biscuit dough.
Cover; place in refrigerator for at least 1 hour.

title: tuna fish casserole
directions: Mix all together in casserole dish.
Top with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: peach pie
directions: Cook water, sugar and cornstarch until clear and add peach Jell-O; stir well and cool.
Put sliced or diced peaches in baked pie shell.
Pour Jell-O mixture over peaches and refrigerate.

title: moist coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on box, using 9 x 13-inch sheet pan.
Mix other ingredients together and heat to boiling.
Poke holes in cake all across.
Pour milk mixture over cake.

title: frozen cabbage salad
directions: Boil vinegar, water and sugar several minutes. Cool until completely cool. Shred cabbage. Sprinkle 1/2 teaspoon salt over it and let set 1 hour. Stir occasionally. Squeeze out juice well. Dice celery and green pepper into cabbage. Add celery seed and mustard seed. Add dressing, package and freeze.

title: marcia's apple crisp
directions: Layer apples in pan.
Sprinkle cinnamon, salt and water over top.
Mix flour, sugar and butter, melted in microwave; sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with Cool Whip or ice cream and serve warm.

title: mark's french toast
directions: Heat large skillet to medium temperature; add butter.
Beat eggs in bowl.
Add milk and whip.
Dip bread in milk quickly. Place bread in buttered pan.
Turn bread when lightly golden brown.
Serve buttered with syrup.

title: spinach lasagna
directions: Combine mix, paste, sauce and water; heat until boiling. Remove from heat.
Combine eggs, cottage cheese, salt, spinach and 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese.
Mix well and set aside.
Spread 1/2 cup tomato sauce mixture in greased 9 x 13-inch dish.
Place 1/2 of noodles over sauce, 1/2 of spinach mixture and 1/2 of Mozzarella. Repeat layers until all ingredients are used.
Sprinkle with remaining Parmesan cheese.
Cover dish securely with aluminum foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving. Makes 8 to 10 portions.
May be put together the night before and put in refrigerator.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Over low heat, melt bark and chips.
When completely melted, add peanuts.
Drop by teaspoon on smooth surface or wax paper and let harden.
(I use Spanish peanuts.)

title: prairieland pot roast
directions: Season meat with salt and pepper.
Brown in 1/4 cup dressing in Dutch oven over low heat; add remaining dressing and water.
Cover; simmer 2 hours.
Add onion, carrots and potatoes.
Cover and continue simmering 1 hour or until meat and vegetables are tender. Remove meat and vegetables.
Add flour to water; add this to stock where meat has cooked; stir constantly until thickens.
Serve this with meat and vegetables.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: graham bread
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well and bake in 2 (9 x 5-inch) pregreased loaf pans 1 hour at 350°.
Test with toothpick like cake.

title: lush cake
directions: Bake cake and cool.
Bake in sheet cake pan (greased) at 350° for 25 minutes.
Make pudding; let set.
Cream cheese until light and fluffy with electric mixer.
Add Cool Whip and beat again. Add pudding and beat.
Drain pineapple well.
Spread pudding, Cool Whip and cheese mixture on cooled cake.
Sprinkle pineapple, coconut and nuts on.
Any fruit may be used (strawberries, peaches, mandarin oranges).
How about chocolate cake with bananas and nuts, drizzled with chocolate sauce?

title: beet pickle
directions: Cook beets until tender;
peel the beets.
Boil remaining ingredients and add cooked beets.
Pack into jars and seal.

title: taco salad
directions: Toss with French dressing 1 1/2 pounds ground beef browned with 1/2 chopped onion and seasoned with taco seasoning and 1 bag Doritos (crushed).
Mix all together just before serving.

title: chicken breast and broccoli with cheese sauce(serves 4.)
directions: Simmer chicken in salted water 1 hour.
Cook broccoli 5 minutes.
Cut broccoli in half lengthwise; place in baking dish with flat side up.
Place chicken on top of broccoli.

title: barbecue beef or pork
directions: Cool roast and shred.
Add
barbecue sauce and carrots. Add sugar to taste.
Add water	if
necessary and may add more barbecue sauce if desired.	Heat and serve on bun.

title: microwave chocolate pie
directions: Mix in microwave bowl, the sugar, flour, salt and cocoa.
Add slightly beaten egg yolks.
Slowly add milk and stir well. Microwave on High for 2 minutes and stir. Repeat until filling is of the desired consistency.
Add butter and vanilla.
Stir well. Pour into baked pie shell.
Beat egg whites until stiff, adding 3 tablespoons sugar while beating.
Spread on pie fillings and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: snowballs
directions: Cream butter and sugar together; add eggs and vanilla.
Blend in flour, baking soda and baking powder alternately with sour cream and mix in coconut.
Chill for several hours.
Make into 1-inch balls, roll in colored sugar and bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Yields 6 dozen.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Melt butter in a 13 x 9-inch glass baking pan in oven.
Sprinkle crumbs over butter and pat down.
Pour sweetened condensed milk evenly over crumbs.
Top with remaining ingredients.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes, until lightly browned. Cool; cut into bars.

title: sausage pie
directions: Mix sausage, cracker crumbs, onion, green pepper, salt and 1/2 can tomato soup.
When mixed well, line a 9-inch pie pan with mixture.
Combine cooked rice, cheese, rest of the tomato soup, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Fill the sausage shell with this mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix together and bake at 400°.
If you double this, use one big can of cream-style corn.

title: french salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients in a blender, good and tasty for salads.

title: instant hot chocolate mix #2
directions: Mix ingredients together well and store in jars or airtight containers.
To serve, mix 1/3 dry mix to 2/3 cup water.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Roll into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.

title: hamburger buns
directions: Dissolve dry yeast in warm water and set aside.
Bring water and sugar to boil for 5 minutes.
When cooled to lukewarm, add oil, salt and eggs.
Stir in yeast mixture.
Measure 12 cups flour after sifting and add to liquid mixture.
Set aside by 2 p.m. Knead down at 6 p.m.
At 10 p.m. shape into buns and put on tins. Leave, uncovered, and bake in morning around 5 to 6 a.m. in a 350° oven for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: mulraney madness
directions: Saute onion, garlic and mushrooms until brown.
Add kielbasi; let cook about 10 minutes.
Boil rigatoni; do not cook all the way.
Layer rigatoni, sauteed items, kielbasi and cheese in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, until cheese is melted.

title: steak mushrooms
directions: Cut round steak in strips.
Flour, salt and pepper; brown in skillet.
Place in a baking dish.
Spread mushrooms, onion slices and garlic.
Simmer 40 minutes.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: sarma
directions: Combine meat, rice, onions, parsley, 1 can tomato sauce and salt and pepper as desired in a large bowl.

Mix well by hand. Soak grape leaves in cool water to cover about 30 minutes, then rinse and dry, spreading between layers of paper towels to drain. Place each grape leaf on clean work surface, glossy side down. Place 1 heaping teaspoonful of filling in center of leaf at widest part.
Pull stem end over to cover filling. Fold in both sides, then firmly roll toward point of leaf. Repeat with remaining leaves.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix and beat for 1 minute; add a little water, if needed, to make a slightly soft batter.
Bake at 500° until brown.
A black skillet is best.

title: blueberry sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan.
Cook and stir over medium heat for 4 to 5 minutes or until thickened.
Makes about 2 cups.
Serve on pancakes, waffles, ice cream, puddings, pound cake or angel food cake.

title: spicy rice and chicken
directions: Cook the chicken.
Saute onion and pepper.
Prepare rice as directed on the package.
Add diced chicken, onion, pepper and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Mix well and serve.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Combine chicken, softened cream cheese, onion and salt.
Fry tortillas in 1/4 inch oil until tender.
Fill tortillas with chicken mixture, roll and place seam-side down in 11 3/4 x 7 1/2-inch baking dish.
Heat cheese spread, 1 cup tomatoes and milk over low heat.
Stir until cheese spread melts.
Pour sauce over tortillas; place remaining tomatoes on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sour cream muffins
directions: Cream butter.
Stir in sour cream.
Gradually add biscuit mix, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Spoon into lightly greased miniature muffin pans, filling 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, or until lightly browned.
(Muffins if made in regular muffin tins need to bake for 20 minutes.)

title: pound cake
directions: Sift flour; measure and add soda.
Combine Crisco and sugar. Add eggs and beat well.
Add buttermilk and flour mixture alternately and then vanilla.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: watergate salad
directions: Thoroughly mix pudding and pineapple.
Add whipped topping, marshmallows and pecans (may want to add coconut).
Chill in refrigerator.

title: easy party m & m cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugars, eggs, and vanilla thoroughly.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Add dry ingredients gradually to creamed mixture, mix well.
Stir in 1/2 cup m&m candies; reserve remaining candies for decorating.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Peel and boil potato until soft enough to mash.
Combine with salmon, onion, parsley, egg and seasonings in a large bowl.
Beat on low speed of electric mixer until well blended.
Shape into croquettes, any size you wish, and fry in 1/2 inch oil in a heavy skillet until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Blend together mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar.
Mix well and serve at room temperature.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Fry bacon; drain. Return 4 tablespoons fat to skillet. Add celery, onion, flour and salt. Cook gently until tender.
Add sugar, vinegar, pepper and water. Bring to boil and pour over potatoes in baking dish. Cover and heat for at least 30 minutes at 350°. Serves 12. Can also be heated in crock-pot.

title: cream cheese bars
directions: Butter 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix cake mix, 1 egg and butter to form dough; press into pan.
Mix cream cheese, sugar, eggs and pecans; spread on batter dough.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: oreo cookie cake
directions: Crush Oreo cookies
with
cream.
Reserve
1/2	cup for topping.
Mix the
rest
of
the
cookies
with melted butter. Press cookie mixture in
bottom
of
an
8	1/2 x 13-inch pan. Beat cream cheese and
add	8 ounces of Cool Whip.	Beat until smooth.
Spread over cookie mixture.
Mix pudding according to directions.
Let set for
minute.
Spread over cream cheese mixture.
Spread 8 ounces of Cool Whip over pudding.
Top with 1/2 cup of crushed cookies.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: hot chicken salad appetizer
directions: Mix together all ingredients except 1/2 cup of shredded cheese and potato chips.
Save these for topping.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle cheese and potato chips over the top.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve with pita bread, cut in quarter size wedges or small rye bread.

title: poached fish berg-style
directions: Cut a circle of waxed paper to fit a 10-inch skillet.
Tear a small hole in the center.
Set aside.
Sprinkle fish with salt and pepper.
Saute onion with some butter in the skillet until golden brown.
Top with the fish, tomatoes and parsley.
Add the lemon water or white wine.
Lay the paper circle on top.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and cook over high heat 5 to 10 minutes.
Remove cover and paper.
Pour cream around the fish.
Mix 1 tablespoon softened butter with the flour and stir into the cooking liquid, moving skillet in a circular motion to blend until sauce thickens. Spoon sauce over fish and sprinkle with parsley.
Serve from skillet or arrange on a platter with the sauce.
Serves 6.

title: lace cookies
directions: Put foil on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 11 to 15 minutes. Let cool completely before taking off foil.

title: low country boil
directions: In a large boiler, combine sausage, potatoes, crab boil and plenty of water.
Boil about 45 minutes.
Add corn and onions; boil until these ingredients are nearly done.
Add shrimp and boil until they are done (about 4 or 5 minutes).
After bringing to a boil again, you may add crab legs, when you add shrimp, if you have them.

title: tasty chocolate chip cookies
directions: *Measure and blend in a blender to a fine powder.

title: rice-broccoli casserole
directions: Saute chopped onion and celery in butter or margarine until tender.
Cook Minute rice according to box directions.
Mix together onion, celery, rice, soup, Cheez Whiz, broccoli and almonds.
Pour into casserole; bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: dirt cake
directions: In
a
large
bowl,
combine confectioners sugar, cream cheese and
butter.
Fold
in
Cool Whip.
Add pudding.
Break cookies into large crumbs.
Layer cookies and pudding mixture alternately, ending
with
pudding.
For interest or fun, put gummi frogs
and worms in layers with a few sticking out top. Also, use a flowerpot
(plastic)
or
sand bucket for the container.
Great for youth groups.

title: rice and artichoke salad
directions: Cook rice by instructions.
Add pepper, onions, celery and drained artichokes.
Combine artichoke juice, curry and mayonnaise. Mix all together and chill.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Mix
pecans and coconut;
spread into 9 x 13-inch dish. Mix cake mix according to directions on box.
Pour batter over nut mixture.
Melt
margarine and cream cheese together.
Add 10x sugar.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: buttered breadsticks
directions: Place butter in 13 x 9 x2-inch baking pan; place in preheated oven (400°) to melt.
Combine biscuit mix, sugar and milk in mixing bowl.
Stir with fork until soft dough is formed.
Beat dough vigorously until stiff but not sticky.
Dust board.
Knead gently for about 10 times.
Roll to 12 x 8-inch rectangle.
Cut dough in half lengthwise with floured knife; cut each half crosswise into 16 strips.
Dip each strip in melted butter in pan, turning to coat both sides.
Arrange in baking pan in two rows. Bake for about 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve warm. Yields 32 breadsticks.

title: coconut delight
directions: Crumble crackers and reserve 1 cup for topping.
Mix remaining crackers with melted margarine.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: peanut butter bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Beat eggs with milk and peanut butter. Mix all together.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: fran's lemon icebox dessert
directions: Line bottom of 9 x 12-inch dish with graham cracker crumbs. Mix condensed milk and lemon juice thoroughly and pour in a layer over the crumbs.
Spread layer of Cool Whip over lemon mixture. Garnish with a few graham cracker crumbs.
Chill overnight. Serves 12.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cream the sugar, shortening and eggs.
Add milk. Alternate dry ingredients and bananas.
Last add nuts, beating well. This makes 1 sheet pan or two loaf pans. Grease pans. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes. Serve plain or with whipped cream.
Bananas are better if real ripe.

title: neiman-marcus cookies
directions: Cream eggs, sugars, vanilla and oleo.
Mix in flour, soda, powder, salt and oats.
Stir in chocolate and nuts.
Bake 10 minutes at 375°.
Makes 112 cookies.

title: pepperoni pizzazz
directions: Cook pasta according to the directions.
Combine 2 1/3 cups of spaghetti sauce, mushrooms, Parmesan cheese, garlic powder, salt, pepper, red pepper flakes, black olives and pepperoni. Drain pasta and add to sauce mixture, mix well.
Transfer to 3 quart baking dish.
Combine tomato sauce and remaining spaghetti sauce and pour on top.
Cover and bake at 350 degrees for 40 to 45 minutes or until bubbly.
Sprinkle with mozzarella cheese and bake uncovered for 5 to 10 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Let stand for 5 minutes before serving.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Mix all but Velveeta.
Put in pan.
Layer top with sliced Velveeta.
Bake, uncovered, at 350°
for 1 hour.
Stir occasionally 3 to 4 times.

title: linguini with clam sauce
directions: Slice mushrooms and fry in olive oil with garlic.
Add clams with sauce and olives.
Cover; simmer for 1/2 hour, stirring occasionally.
Add cream; simmer until it thickens slightly.
Cook linguini according to package directions.
Serve clam sauce over hot linguini.

title: peanut butter and jelly sandwich on wheat bread
directions: Spread peanut butter on 1 slice of bread and jelly on the other.
Put together.
Calories 330; fat 16.5 gm; sodium 340 mg; carbohydrates 38 gm; protein 11 gm.

title: butterball coffee cake
directions: Heat
oven
to
Grease
9 x 1 1/2-inch round cake pan. Melt butter in saucepan.
Mix in a bowl 3/4 cup sugar and 1 tablespoon cinnamon.
Divide a can of 10 flake biscuits into 20 parts.
Dip each biscuit into melted margarine and roll into cinnamon
and
sugar mixture.
Fold over and lap in pan to make circle.
Sprinkle nuts over biscuits.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.

title: easy chicken tetrazinni
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter. Add soups, cheese, pimento, chicken, salt and pepper; blend well. Sprinkle with garlic salt. Simmer 30 minutes. Serve over rice. Six to eight servings.

title: hardee's biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients for 30 seconds.
Blend in shortening for 3 minutes.
Add buttermilk and mix 30 seconds.
Roll dough on floured board to 1/2 inch thick.
Cut with 3-inch cutter.
Yields 16 biscuits.
Bake at 425° until brown.

title: chicken ring
directions: On a cookie sheet, lay triangular shaped rolls in a circle with points outward so it looks like a sun. Mix remainder of ingredients in a bowl. Fold up points to form a ring. Bake as directed on tube.

title: peggy's frozen oreo chocolate dessert
directions: Mix cookies and margarine and press down in bottom of 13 x 9 inch pan.
Spoon ice cream over crust and place in freezer.
Mix remaining ingredients in saucepan over medium heat until melted. Cool and pour over ice cream.
Freeze.
Add cool whip and pecans, if desired.
Let sit out about 5 minutes before serving.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni until tender.
Drain.
Add milk, salt, black pepper, margarine and cheese.
Heat until cheese melts.
Stir often.

title: crunchy chewy popcorn
directions: Melt butter with peanut butter.
Pour mixture over popcorn. Sprinkle raisins in, tossing to coat evenly.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: chocolate peanut butter balls
directions: Cream butter and confectioners sugar together.
Add peanut butter and vanilla and mix well.
Form into small balls.
Lay on wax paper on baking sheet and chill in refrigerator.
Melt chocolate morsels and paraffin wax together on low heat, stirring until melted to thin mixture.
Use toothpick to dip each ball into chocolate to cover.
Lay out on wax paper to dry.

title: 10 can casserole
directions: Mix first 10 ingredients.
Pour into a large baking pan.
Top with onions the last 15 minutes.
Bake at 350° until bubbly, about 45 minutes.
Serves up to 15.

title: coconut pie
directions: Make jello pudding according to directions; add margarine. Cool and add browned coconut.
Save some coconut for top of Cool Whip.
When good and cool, add filling to baked pie crust.
When ready to serve, put entire container of Cool Whip on top of filling and sprinkle the coconut on top.

title: sad cake
directions: Grease and flour oblong pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: turkey burger
directions: Preheat broiler.
In medium bowl, mix ground turkey, horseradish, apple, onion, salt and dried parsley flakes with hands.
Shape turkey mixture into four 1-inch thick patties. Spray rack in broiling pan and place patties on rack.
Broil patties 4 minutes.
Turn patties; broil 6 minutes until cooked through.

title: chicken divine
directions: In 9 x 13-inch casserole dish space broccoli evenly.
Place pieces (bite size) of chicken over broccoli.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, curry and lemon juice; pour over chicken.
Mix crushed Ritz crackers and melted butter; scatter over all; add grated cheese. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: all season bread(makes two loaves)
directions: Combine flour, soda, salt, baking powder, cinnamon and nuts; set aside.
Beat eggs lightly in large mixing bowl; add sugar, oil and vanilla and beat until creamy.
Drain pineapple, reserving juice if called for in instructions for specific fruit or vegetables.
Stir in pineapple and prepared fruit or vegetable. Add dry ingredients, stirring only until dry ingredients are moistened.
Spoon batter into 2 well-greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for one hour or until done.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pans.
Cool on racks.

title: squash pie
directions: Beat eggs; add spices, sugar, milk, salt and squash.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes, them at 350° until custard is set-about 50 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Mash bananas and blend in eggs.
Add lemon juice to banana mixture.
Add to butter and sugar.
Alternate adding dry ingredients with milk to banana and sugar mixture, blending well after each addition (use low speed if using a mixer).
Stir in nuts, then pour batter into a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan greased on the bottom.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: hampton herbs pasta salad
directions: Mix Miracle Whip and dill.
Salad can be layered or tossed. Save some shredded cheese for the top.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
In 9 x 13-inch baking pan, spread the jar of dried beef on bottom of pan.
Then put chicken breasts on top of dried beef.
Pour chicken soup mixture over and cover.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.
Remove cover last 15 minutes to brown.
Prepare rice (Minute rice) and put on serving platter or put rice on each plate and put breast and mixture over it.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour alternately with buttermilk. Beat well.
Stir in coconut and extract.
Pour into a 10-inch tube pan, greased and floured.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes. Top with glaze.

title: baked salmon in sour cream
directions: Arrange salmon steaks in baking dish.
Mix all of the other ingredients except parsley.
Pour over salmon.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until salmon flakes.
Sprinkle with parsley.

title: skillet supper
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add vegetables in layers in order given. Salt and pepper each layer.
Pour water over all.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: garlic sticks
directions: Cut buns in quarters lengthwise.
Combine oleo and salt; brush both sides of buns.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Toast in oven at 450° for 8 minutes.

title: creamy seafood soup
directions: Combine all ingredients and heat.
Garnish with parsley, if desired.

title: apple salad
directions: Mix well all ingredients and chill.
Makes a large amount.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Add all ingredients together; blend into a mixture.
Bake on lightly greased cookie sheet in a 400° preheated oven for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Scald milk and margarine.
Thoroughly mix with dry ingredients.
Cool 10 minutes.
Mix in eggs.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: darrel dunton's special dressing for greens, fruit, vegetables
directions: Beat the sugar and all seasonings with the eggs.
Then very slowly drizzle in the oil on second speed.
Makes thick dressing, thin with vinegar on slow speed.
Makes about a gallon.
Keep refrigerated.
May have to thin again with vinegar as you take it out of refrigerator.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Place bones and meat in large pot, add water.
Bring to boil, skim surface of liquid if desired.

Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, onions, parsley, salt, basil, pepper, garlic powder and bay leaves. Bring to boil, reduce heat and simmer for 1 1/2 hours. Add carrots and celery, cover and simmer 1/2 hour longer or until meat is tender.
Remove bones and meat, cut meat into bite size pieces and return meat to soup.
Add kidney beans and macaroni. Simmer, covered, 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve with cheese on top.

title: fruit cobbler(especially fresh dewberries or peaches)
directions: Mix in baking dish the first 5 ingredients.
Bring to boil fruit, oleo and sugar.
Mix together.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: gourmet chicken
directions: Melt butter in large roasting pan.
Spread brown rice in bottom of pan.
Stir in slivered almonds.
Lay chicken pieces on rice.
Heat soups and water separately; add sherry to hot soup mixture.
Pour mixture over chicken.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake uncovered for 3 hours at 275°.
Yields 10 servings.

title: harvard carrots
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch.
Add vinegar and water.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Add butter.
Add carrots and let stand over low heat 5 to 10 minutes.
(If sauce is too thick, add a little water.)

title: linguine with ham(microwave)
directions: Mix oil, garlic and onion in 3-quart casserole.
Cover tightly and microwave on High 4 to 5 minutes or until onion is tender. Stir in remaining ingredients except lemon peel.
Cover tightly and microwave 5 to 8 minutes, stirring after 3 minutes, until heated through.
Sprinkle with lemon peel; toss.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken different
directions: Grease 8 x 13-inch baking pan.
Mix rice with can soups and milk or water.
Heat and stir until well blended.
Pour soup mixture into pan.
Place chicken pieces over soup; sprinkle with the dry onion soup mix and cheese.
Seal with a piece of foil over the top.
Bake in 350° oven for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: fluffy white icing
directions: Combine sugar, syrup, salt and water in saucepan.
Stir well. Cook until hard ball forms in water.
Remove from heat.
In large mixing bowl, beat egg whites until soft peaks form.
Add syrup in a thin steam while beating.
Add vanilla.
Beat until peaks hold shape.
Spread on cool cake.

title: pecan and peanut butter candy
directions: Melt bonbons in microwave for 2 minutes.
Add peanut butter and pecans and stir together.
Spread on cookie sheet.
Freeze for 3 minutes and cut into squares.
Serve.

title: spinach pie
directions: Combine ingredients and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: apple juice dressing(low-fat)
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Blend or process until smooth. Cover and refrigerate several hours.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine water, sugar and garlic.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Let stand 2 hours before using. Let stand overnight and its even better.

title: hot oyster dip
directions: Saute onion, celery, pepper and garlic in butter.
Chop oysters and add to mixture.
Add mustard, red pepper, Worcestershire and lemon juice.
Toast bread, crumble and add to mixture.
Beat egg in milk and add to mixture.
Mix in parsley and green onion tops.
Serve with Ritz crackers.
Serves 25.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Cream together sour cream and cream cheese; combine remaining ingredients; mix well and chill.

title: melting moments(cookies)
directions: In medium bowl mix flour, cornstarch and powdered sugar.
In separate large bowl with mixer at medium speed, beat butter until smooth.
Add flour mixture and mix until combined.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Shape in 1-inch balls.
Place about 1 1/2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with lightly floured fork. Bake in a 300° oven for about 20 minutes or until edges are lightly brown.
Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: frozen cherry delight
directions: Combine pie filling, milk, pineapple, lemon juice, coconut and nuts.
Stir until well mixed.
Add Cool Whip and fold together. Pour into large Tupperware container and freeze.

title: chili dip
directions: Mix and bake for 30 minutes at 350°, stirring once.

title: barley burger soup
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 4-quart pot and simmer for 1 hour.
Adjust seasonings as desired.

title: play dough for children
directions: Mix.
Cook slowly and stir until mixture forms a soft dough. Store in covered container.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Brown ground chuck.
Add onion; steam for a few minutes.
Pour off grease.
Add Manwich; stir and simmer for about 10 minutes. While steaming, press 4 of the crescent rolls into bottom of 9-inch baking dish like a pie crust (be sure to come up on the sides of the dish).
Pour meat mixture in pie crust.
Cover meat mixture with sliced cheese.
Press remaining 4 crescent rolls on top of cheese as a top crust.
Bake at 350° until golden brown. Cool a few minutes before slicing.

title: basic muffin mix
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt and add to it the remaining ingredients.
Use one cup of berries (your choice).
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: greek lemon soup
directions: Bring broth to a boil; add rice and simmer until rice is done. Beat eggs and lemon juice separately with a little broth.
Then pour into chicken broth.
Season to taste.

title: honey pecan cookies
directions: Cream the shortening, sugar and honey. Add egg and beat well. Mix flour and soda and add to creamed mixture. Add vanilla and blend.
Add nuts. Roll into small balls, then roll in sugar. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: delicious easter eggs
directions: Cream together margarine and cream cheese.
Add 10x sugar, salt, vanilla and fresh coconut.
Place in refrigerator to chill. Shape into eggs (put in 5 to harden for peanut butter eggs; add 1 1/2 cups peanut butter instead of coconut or peppermint to taste).

title: apricot pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake for 1 hour at 325° in a Bundt pan.

title: rice and peas
directions: Heat 4 tablespoons of butter in heavy 3-quart saucepan; saute onion and parsley 5 minutes.
Add rice; saute, stirring occasionally, for 5 minutes.
Add 2 cups water; bring to boil. Reduce heat and simmer, covered, without stirring 14 minutes or until liquid is all absorbed.

title: graham rolls
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into well-greased pans.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: zucchini squash
directions: Mix all ingredients well and dot with margarine.
Bake one hour.

title: spinach salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender; beat for 1 minute or shake vigorously.
Makes 1 1/4 cups.
Pour over fresh spinach.
Add 5 slices bacon, fried crisp and crumpled and 2 hard-boiled eggs, sliced.

title: honey pecan pie
directions: Mix honey and eggs.
Cream sugar, dry milk and margarine; add to honey mixture.
Stir in pecans.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: cream cheese pies
directions: Beat cream cheese until fluffy. Add powdered sugar. Mix well. Add Cool Whip. Mix well. Divide into 2 graham cracker crusts. Put pie filling on top. Cool several hours before serving.

title: pineapple milk sherbet
directions: Combine all ingredients, adding milk last.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Pour in tray and freeze until mush; remove to bowl and beat with rotary beater.
Return to tray and finish freezing. If evaporated milk is chilled and whipped before sherbet is mixed, it may be frozen without beating.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Combine cocoa, sugar and flour in iron skillet.
Gradually add milk and stir while cooking.
Cook until gravy is thickened, add butter and vanilla flavoring.
This is great to pour over hot, buttered biscuits.
Yields 4 servings.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix and store in a closed jar.
Use 1 to 2 1/2 teaspoons mix to one cup hot water.

title: irish cream pie
directions: Bake 5 minutes at 400°. Cool.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Combine Cool Whip, lemonade, Eagle Brand and a few drops of food coloring; whip until well blended.
Pour into crust. Refrigerate at least 4 hours before serving.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; add remaining ingredients and simmer a few minutes before serving on buns.

title: southern squash casserole
directions: Wash squash and slice, then cook in salt water for 10 minutes. Drain and wash the squash.
Mash the squash and place in a medium bowl.
Stir in remaining ingredients.

title: sixty-minute rolls
directions: In a large bowl, thoroughly mix 1 1/2 cups flour, sugar, salt and dry yeast.
Combine milk, water and margarine in a saucepan. Heat over low heat until very warm.
Gradually add to dry ingredients and beat 2 minutes.
Add 1/2 cup of the flour and beat.
Stir in enough additional flour to make a soft dough.
Turn on lightly floured board and knead until smooth and elastic, about 5 minutes.
Place in a greased bowl.
Cover and place bowl in pan of warm water.
Let rise 15 minutes.
Turn out on board.
Divide in half and make into rolls.
Cover and rise 15 minutes.
Bake at 400° for about 12 minutes or until done.

title: country crust bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir in sugar, eggs, oil and enough flour to beat smooth.
Mix in additional flour to make a soft dough.
Knead on floured surface and place in greased bowl and let rise in warm place until double in size.
Punch down. Divide in half and knead.
Place in bread pans.
Cover and let rise to top.
Heat oven to 350° and bake 35-40 minutes or until brown.
Brush with butter.

title: biscuit casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown meat with onion and drain off fat.
Add stewed tomatoes, chili powder and picante sauce and simmer for about 20 minutes uncovered.
Combine sour cream, 1 cup cheese and egg and mix well.
After meat mixture simmers, add sour cream mix.
Remove from heat.
Spray a 9 x 9-inch pan with Pam. Tear 5 of biscuits in half and press into bottom of pan; bake for 10 minutes.
Take out of oven; put meat mixture in and tear remaining 5 biscuits in half.
Place on top of meat; top with remaining cheese and bake for 25 minutes.

title: garlic cheese grits
directions: Cook
grits
in water until well done. Remove from heat and add cheese, butter and salt.
Beat eggs in milk.
Add milk mixture to
grits
mixture,
after cooling grits first.
Pour into 2 quart bowl and bake for one hour at 350°.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.
Delicious as brunch dish.

title: cherry almond chocolate cake
directions: Mix batter ingredients together by hand. Pour into greased 9 x 13 pan. Bake for 40 to 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: royal pecan pie
directions: Cut shortening into flour and salt until particles are size of peas.
Sprinkle in water, 1 tablespoon at a time, tossing with fork until all flour is moistened.
Gather into ball; shape into flattened round on floured cloth covered board.
Roll pastry 2-inches larger than inverted pie pan.
Fold into fourths and put in pie pan, then unfold and flute edges.
Decorate edges with excess dough.

title: cake dessert
directions: Mix cake mix as directed and spread in 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake until
done
(approximately
minutes).	Cream
cream cheese with
to
1/2 cup milk and spread over cake.
Mix pudding with milk as needed.
Add crushed pineapple and spread over
cream cheese.
Spread
Cool
Whip
over pudding mix and sprinkle with coconut and/or chopped nuts if desired.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: In a 2-quart microwave casserole dish shred a layer (1/2 inch deep) of cabbage, a layer of raw potatoes (1/4-inch slices) and a layer of onions (1/8-inch slices).
Add salt and pepper to taste. Cheese may be added if desired.
Dot with margarine.
Seal with Saran Wrap.
Cook on High power for 10 minutes.
Serves 4 people.

title: salami pie
directions: Mix cheeses and eggs together. Pick salami slices apart, stir them into cheese mixture. Press crescent dough into a 9 x 13 pan. Spread mix on top. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: fast fixin' chocolate chip cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix ingredients 2 minutes until blended.
Spread batter evenly in pan. Bake 35 to 45 minutes until toothpick near center comes out clean. Cooled cake may be sprinkled with powdered sugar.

title: refrigerator slaw
directions: Grate or shred cabbage, onion and bell pepper.
Mix salt and sugar and spread over top of grated mixture.
Let stand 1 hour. Mix vinegar, oil, celery seed and 2 tablespoons sugar.
Bring to a boil and let cool.
Pour over cabbage mixture.
Will keep in refrigerator for 1 week.

title: coconut toastie candy
directions: Combine syrup, sugar and cream.
Cook until "clicks" in cold water.
Mix corn flakes, coconut and nuts and pour syrup mixture over.
Spread in buttered dish.
Cool and break into pieces.

title: "very good" pie crust
directions: With fork, mix together first 4 ingredients in a large bowl. In a small bowl, beat remaining ingredients together.
Add to first mixture and blend well with fork.
With hands, mold dough into a ball and chill at least 15 minutes before rolling.
Dough may be stored in refrigerator up to 3 days or frozen until ready to use.
Makes 4 pie shells or 1 double and 2 shells or 2 double pies.

title: pizza crust
directions: In large bowl, mix yeast, flour, sugar and salt.
Stir in water and corn oil.
Knead about 3 minutes.
Place in greased bowl.
Cover and let dough rise double.
Punch down; divide in half.
Roll out on lightly floured surface into a 13-inch circle. Place on pan; form edge.
Add toppings before baking.
Makes 2 pizzas.

title: peach cobbler
directions: In a 350° oven, melt margarine in baking dish.
Combine flour, milk and sugar; pour on top of margarine.
Add peaches.
Do not stir.
Bake approximately 35 minutes or until desired brownness.

title: dorothy's rice balls
directions: Cook rice and let cool.
Mix all ingredients except egg. Shape into balls (golf ball size). Roll in bread crumbs, then in beaten egg, then in bread crumbs again.
Be sure rice balls are completely coated in bread crumbs. Prepare all the rice balls. Deep fry in hot oil until brown and remove with slotted spoon. Let cool.
May be frozen and reheated.

title: easy pancakes
directions: Preheat griddle to about 400 degrees or when a drop of water will sizzle. Cook one side until bubbles from then flip to other side. Serve hot.

title: strawberry-fig preserves
directions: Put together in large, heavy pot and cook over medium heat for 25 minutes, stirring occasionally to prevent sticking.
Pour into sterilized jars.
Run a knife around inside of jar to get any air bubbles out.
Wipe tops of jars off and seal immediately.
You may use other flavors of jello:
apricot, raspberry or cherry.

title: chocolate fudge pie
directions: Mix sugar and melted oleo; add eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour, cocoa and salt.
Add to sugar mixture.
Add pecans.
Pour into well-greased Pyrex dish or uncooked pie shell.
Cook at 325° for 30 minutes.
Top with whipped topping.

title: lemon blueberry cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Butter and flour two 9-inch cake pans. Line bottoms with parchment paper. Sift first four ingredients. Beat butter until fluffy. Add sugar, beating until blended. Beat in lemon and peel, then eggs one at a time. Continue to beat until blended. Beat in dry ingredients, alternating with buttermilk. Fold in berries. Transfer to pans. Bake approximately 40 minutes; test. Cool in pans on rack.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Combine soup, Veg-All and chicken.
Salt and pepper to taste. Place in pie crust and top with other crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until crust is golden brown.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Bake in bundt pan on 350° one hour. Sprinkle top of cake with sugar and cinnamon.

title: make ahead breakfast
directions: Beat eggs; stir in milk, salt and pepper.
Cook in melted butter, stirring until set, but still moist.
Cool.
When cool, stir in sour cream.
Spread into a 7 x 12-inch (2-quart) shallow baking dish.
Top with bacon and cheese.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 300° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: ham stuffed eggs
directions: Cut eggs in half lengthwise; remove yolks.
Mash.
Stir in ham, celery, mayonnaise, salt, garlic salt and pepper.
Stuff whites with mixture.
Chill.
Yields 24 appetizers.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease an 11 x 7 or 9-inch square baking dish.
Mix ingredients in a large bowl.
Top with sprinkling of Parmesan cheese.
Bake until brown, about 30 minutes.
This is actually quite good.

title: no fail biscuits
directions: Break egg into cup and fill to 1 cup mark with milk.
Crumb together flour, baking powder, salt, sugar and shortening. Slightly beat egg and milk and add to crumb mixture.
Roll and cut into biscuits and bake at 450° for 12 minutes.

title: chicken breast scampi
directions: Cut raw boneless chicken breasts into approximately 2-ounce chunks (like huge shrimp).
Place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Melt butter in a saucepan over low heat; add garlic, scallions, parsley, dill, sweet basil, salt and pepper.
Cook on low heat until butter is melted, then pour over the chicken breast pieces.

title: e. g.'s mexican cornbread
directions: In skillet or microwave, brown ground beef, chopped onion and bell pepper.
Now pour Heinz 57 and Worcestershire sauce over meat, salt and pepper.
Allow to simmer for 10 minutes.
Chop up jalapeno pepper and drained corn very fine.
A food processor is great for this.
Mix up your cornbread batter and add corn and jalapeno peppers to mix.
Pour 1/2 cornbread mix in baking dish; drain meat and pour on top of cornbread mix.
Sprinkle cheese on meat.
Pour remaining butter on top of cheese and meat.
Place in preheated oven (350°) and bake for 30 to 45 minutes, when golden brown take out and serve.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Melt butter.
Add eggs, salt, cottage cheese, broccoli, onion and Jiffy corn bread mix.
Mix well.
Pour in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Spread well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until brown.
Cut in squares and serve.
This freezes well.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix in order listed and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 55 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix together onion, chilies, olives, chicken, soups and sour cream for sauce.
Place some chicken sauce and cheese in each tortilla.
Makes 12 or more.
Place in casserole dish or 9
x 13-inch oblong pan sprayed with Pam.
Add remaining sauce on top and cover with grated cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes. Cover
loosely
with
foil.
Bake for 10 minutes and eat.

title: holiday punch
directions: Combine all ingredients and simmer 30 minutes.
Strain and serve.
May be kept warm in crock-pot set on low temperature. Store in refrigerator.
Serves 20.

title: coconut dream pie
directions: Prepare Dream Whip with 1 cup of milk as directed on package, using a large mixer bowl.
Add remaining milk and the pie filling mix.
Blend, then beat at high speed for 2 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally.
Fold in coconut.
Spoon into crust.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Chill at least 4 hours, then serve.

title: sage biscuits
directions: Put flour, baking powder, salt and sage in medium bowl and stir to mix.
Cut in shortening and add onions and milk.
Drop by spoonful on cookie sheet.
Before putting biscuits in oven, put a piece of bacon on top of each one.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.

title: crispy tomatoes
directions: Cut tomatoes into 1/2-inch slices.
Dip into corn meal, making sure both sides are well covered.
Heat enough olive oil in a large frying pan to just cover bottom of pan.
Add pepper, then quickly fry tomato slices until just crisp on outside (about one to two minutes per side, depending on thickness and how hot pan is). Remove to paper towel to absorb any excess oil.
Serve immediately.

title: banana split cake
directions: Press the first 2 ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix 2 sticks oleo, powdered sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Beat 15 minutes in pan, stirring constantly.
Cut bananas; lay on graham crackers in pan.
Pour on mixture.
Drain pineapple; put on top of creamed mixture.
Whip Dream Whip; spread on top of pineapple.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Refrigerate 4 to 5 hours.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Mix and spoon onto cookie sheet with foil.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Slice cheese in thin slices.
Beat eggs in a small flat bowl, adding salt and pepper.
Wash and dry the eggplant and cut into 1/4-inch slices.
Dip the eggplant in the egg mixture and brown in oil about 10 minutes.
Drain on paper towels.
Place a row of eggplant in the bottom of a 3 or 4-quart casserole.
Then place cheese slices to cover the eggplant and sprinkle Parmesan cheese. Pour part of the tomato sauce over this.
Alternate layers to the top of the dish.
Optional: Sprinkle sesame seed about each layer. End up with cheese layer on top of casserole.
Pour leftover egg mixture on top of casserole. Cover and bake 45 minutes at 325°. Let stand for about 15 minutes before eating.

title: graham cracker pudding
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and vanilla; add egg yolk and beat well.
Stir in fruit and nuts.
Mix together crumbs and baking powder; add 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternating with milk.
Fold in egg white.
Fill 6 greased 6 ounce custard cups.
Bake at 350°
for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve warm with lemon sauce or whipped cream.

title: graham popovers
directions: Mix flour and salt.
Beat eggs light.
Add milk and butter slowly.
Add flour and mix well.
Beat 1 minute with electric beater.
Mix should be like heavy cream.
Place in buttered muffin tins 1/3 full.
Bake 20 minutes at 450°.
Reduce oven to 350° and finish baking 15 more minutes.
Remove from tins.
Serves 8 to 12.

title: basic vinaigrette dressing
directions: Shake well.
Contains 32 calories per tablespoon.

title: zucchini (apple) cobbler
directions: Mix the flour, sugar and oleo until crumbly. Pat half in 9 x 12 pan. Mix half of remaining flour mix with zucchini. Pour into crust. Sprinkle the last of the flour mix on top and sprinkle with cinnamon. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: charlie brown cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar well.
Add beaten egg.
Mix and gradually add flour and cream of tartar.
Add vanilla.
Add nuts last.
Roll dough into small balls and bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 300° to 325° until just beginning to lightly brown around edges.

title: grandma zimmerman's chocolate marshmallow cookies
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients, then add in the rest and mix together to cookie consistency.
Drop from teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
When done, remove from oven and top each cookie with a half of a marshmallow with cut side down.
Return to oven for 1 minute.
When cool, ice with frosting and decorate with candy, if you want.

title: golden carrot cake
directions: Sift the dry ingredients together, then add sugar, oil and eggs.
Mix well.
Blend thoroughly.
Add carrots, pineapple, coconut and nuts.
Bake in prepared pan (3 layers) at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: sponge cake
directions: Beat egg yolks 5 minutes until thick.
Combine water, sweetener, vanilla and lemon juice; add to yolks.
Beat 10 minutes until thick and fluffy.
Beat egg whites until fluffy.
Add cream of tartar and beat until stiff peaks form.
Fold carefully into yolk mixture.
Combine sifted flour and salt.
Sift a little at a time over mixture, folding in gently.
Pour into ungreased 9 or 10-inch tube pan.
Bake in slow 325° oven for 1 1/4 hours.

title: chicken stew
directions: In large pot, shred cooked chicken and return to broth. Add onion,
diced
potatoes, tomatoes and pepper.
Cook until potatoes are
done,
about
minutes,
then
add remaining ingredients and simmer 1 1/2 hours.

title: grandmother's barbecue meat balls
directions: Mix ingredients well and form into small balls.
Brown in skillet.

title: plain cake and applesauce topping
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together.
Cook until thick.
Add vanilla and applesauce.
Serve hot over slice or square of plain cake.

title: quick and easy pecan rolls
directions: Heat first 4 ingredients together.
Pour 1/4 of this mixture into greased Bundt pan.
Separate rolls.
Stand on edge in pan. Pour remaining mixture over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool 3 minutes and then turn out on plate.

title: kansas 24 hour layer salad
directions: Line a 13 x 9 x 2-inch glass dish with bite size pieces of iceberg lettuce.
Over this sprinkle the green pepper and red pepper.
(If red pepper is not available, use the whole green pepper.)
Then add a layer of celery and Spanish onion (an ordinary onion is too strong).
Next, add frozen green peas, uncooked.

title: stained glass mold
directions: Prepare lime, orange and strawberry jello separately, using 1 cup boiling water and 1/2 cup cold water for each.
Pour each flavor into an 8-inch square pan or use 9-inch round cake pans. Refrigerate until firm, about 4 hours.
Cut into 1/2-inch cubes. Dissolve lemon jello in 2 cups boiling water; stir in 1 cup cold water.
Refrigerate until slightly thickened.
Fold 3 cups whipped topping and the jello cubes into slightly thickened lemon jello. Pour into 9-inch tube pan that has been lightly sprayed with no-stick cooking spray.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: pecan pie
directions: Line unbaked pie shell with pecans.
Mix all ingredients well. Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 325° about 45 minutes.

title: chocolate chip oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift together flour, baking soda, and salt and set aside. Cream shortening until soft.
Add sugars and beat.
Add eggs one at a time, beating until fluffy.
Add hot water and vanilla.
Add flour mixture.
Beat until flour disappears.
Add nuts, chocolate chips, and oatmeal.
Mix well.
Drop from teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 375 degrees for 8-10 minutes.
Makes 8 dozen.

title: poulet
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Combine all ingredients except cheese and potato chips.
Place in greased casserole.
Spread cheese and potato chips on top.
Bake uncovered about 1/2 hour, until heated and browned on top.
Garnish with parsley.

title: secret kiss cookie
directions: At medium speed on mixer, beat butter, sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Add sifted flour and nuts.
Beat on low speed until well blended.
Chill dough.
Remove foil from Kisses.
(Do not eat.)
Heat oven to 375°.
Using approximately 1 tablespoon of dough; shape around chocolate Kisses completely and roll to make a ball.
Be sure to cover Kiss completely.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 12 minutes or until set but not brown.
Cool slightly; remove to wire rack.
While still warm, roll in confectioners sugar.
Cool.
Store in tightly covered container and roll in sugar again before serving, if desired.
Makes 4 dozen cookies.

title: betty's strawberry pie
directions: Mix with hands the flour and oleo.
Press into a 10-inch pie plate.
Add broken pecans.
Bake at 350° about 20 minutes.

title: ann cobb's crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and stir.
Put in oven at 325° and in 5 minutes stir again.
Repeat this 3 times.
Serve with bacon flavored crackers or club crackers.

title: plain salt pickles
directions: Can the same way as previous recipe.

title: apple and nut cake
directions: Mix everything in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread evenly.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Be sure to use a tart green apple, otherwise, it will not have enough liquid.

title: twinkie cake
directions: Slice Twinkies	lengthwise in bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Add ingredients as listed.	Refrigerate.

title: beef and vegetable fajitas
directions: Place steak, onion and red peppers in shallow dish.
Combine garlic, lime juice, vinegar, coriander, cumin and salt; pour over steak and vegetables.
Toss.
Cover and refrigerate 1 to 2 hours.

title: jalapeno corn casserole
directions: Cook rice according to pkg. directions. Set aside.
Saute onions, green pepper and parsley in butter until vegetables are tender.
Combine rice, sauteed vegetables and next 4 ingredients. Stir well.
Spoon into lightly greased 12 x 18 x 2 dish. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Garnish as desired.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: quick chocolate cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, cocoa, salt, and soda into mixing bowl. Form a well in your dry ingredients and add melted shortening, water, vinegar, and vanilla.
Mix well and pour in lightly greased and floured 9 inch cake pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: cream of carrot soup
directions: In food processor fitted with steel blade, blend all ingredients except milk.
Slowly add milk.
Blend 30 seconds. Pour into saucepan; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 3 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: sweet and sour beef and cabbage
directions: In skillet cook beef, onion, celery and peppers until meat is browned.
Drain off fat.
Sprinkle meat mixture with rolled oats, parsley, 2 teaspoons salt, garlic powder and 1/2 teaspoon pepper.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour 1/2 of batter in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Take remaining batter plus 1 cup brown sugar and 3 teaspoons cinnamon.
Pour over mix in pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Debone	and
remove
skin
from chicken breasts.
Pound until 1/4-inch
thick.
Rub with garlic powder.
Place Danish ham, Swiss cheese and 1 teaspoon bread crumbs on each breast. Roll from
small end, secure with toothpicks.
Place bread in buttered casserole
dish.
Melt
butter;
add sherry in small saucepan. Pour
over breasts in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: refrigerator yeast rolls
directions: Pour cold water over yeast and 1 tablespoon sugar and let stand to soften.
Combine shortening/oil and sugar; add eggs. Beat well and add boiling water and 2 cups whole wheat flour.
Add yeast, making sure boiling water mixture has cooled down sufficiently.
Mix and add remainder of flour and salt gradually. Cover and refrigerate.
When ready to use, punch down dough; knead lightly.
Shape into balls and place in lightly greased pan. Let rise until double in size.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 18 to 22 minutes.
Yield:
3 dozen.

title: key lime pie(servings:  8; 180 calories)
directions: In large bowl, dissolve gelatin in boiling water. Stir in yogurt with wire whisk. Fold in whipped topping with wooden spoon. Spread in crust. Refrigerate overnight or at least 2 hours. Garnish as desired. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: apple cake with caramel topping
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Grease and flour a 9 or 10 inch tube pan. Mix together sugar and oil. Add eggs and beat well. Blend in flour, cinnamon and vanilla. Stir in apples, coconut and pecans. Spoon batter into prepared pan. Bake 1 1/2 hours or until wooden toothpick inserted in center of cake comes out clean. Remove cake from oven and immediately pour the hot caramel topping over the hot cake and allow to soak in.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Wash chicken and place in baking pan or dish.
Mix remaining three ingredients together.
Spread over chicken.
Do not add any liquid; will cook in own juice.
Cover pan with foil or lid.
Bake for 45 to 60 minutes or until chicken is done.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Mix Rice Krispies and flour well.
Add grated cheese and margarine.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on cookie sheet. Flatten with hand or fork.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Turn oven off and leave them in oven until cool.
This make them crispier.

title: honey cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: sausage rice casserole
directions: Brown sausage in large skillet.
Pour off excess fat; add green pepper, onion and celery.
Saute in skillet.
Combine soup mix and boiling water in large saucepan; stir in rice.
Boil 7 minutes.
Add sausage mixture and salt; stir well.
Pour into baking dish; bake at 350°, uncovered, for 1 hour or longer.

title: no bake chocolate cookies
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, margarine and milk in heavy saucepan. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture reaches a slow boil.
Cook 2 additional minutes.
Remove from heat; add peanut butter and stir until smooth.
Stir in oats (nuts and coconut) and vanilla.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Cool.

title: beer biscuits
directions: In a bowl, mix biscuit mix and sugar.
Add beer and stir with a spoon.
Spoon into greased muffin tins and let stand while heating oven (about 15 minutes).
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into square baking dish. Bake at 425° until done.

title: chicken stew
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Saute onions and potatoes in bacon drippings.
Debone and cut chicken into small pieces.
Mix in chicken, broth, onions, potatoes and tomatoes.
Simmer about 2 hours.
Add corn, ketchup and milk.
Salt and pepper to taste. Turn off and let stand for 10 minutes.

title: cheesecake cookies
directions: In large bowl, combine flour, butter and brown sugar.
Blend with mixer until particles are fine.
Stir in walnuts.
Set aside 2 cups for topping.
Press remaining in bottom of ungreased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned, about 12 to 15 minutes.

title: triple layer chocolate bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine crumbs, 1/4 cup cocoa, sugar and butter.
Press firmly on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
In large mixing bowl, beat sweetened condensed milk, flour, remaining 1/4 cup cocoa, egg, vanilla and baking powder.
Stir in nuts. Spread evenly over prepared crust.
Top with chips.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes, or until set.
Cool; cut into bars.
Store, tightly covered, at room temperature.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix squash, onion, pepper, and carrot. Add soup & sour cream. Mix stuffing with melted butter. Add 1/2 to squash mixture. Mix well and pour into baking dish. Top with rest of stuffing mixture. Bake at 350 degrees 30-40 minutes.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Mix in crackers and sugar.
Press this evenly in pan.
Add other ingredients (chips, coconut, nuts and milk last).
Bake about 25 minutes (don't brown too much); edges will become hard.

title: company vegetable casserole
directions: Combine corn, green beans, soup, sour cream, cheese, celery, onion and green pepper in a greased 2-quart casserole. Bake in preheated oven at 325° for 30 minutes.
Blend cracker crumbs and butter. Sprinkle over casserole; bake 10 minutes longer. Serves 8 to 10.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll into small balls.
The secret is to squeeze through fingers real good.
Put on greased cookie sheet.
Heat oven to 375°.
Cook until golden brown.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti as directed.
Drain well.
Peel and cube cucumbers.
Dice onions.
Add cucumbers and onions to salad.
Add 1 small bottle of Italian dressing.
Stir well.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serve with bacon bits sprinkled on top.
Add tomato wedges to garnish.

title: broiled fish
directions: Melt butter over medium heat and season with the garlic cloves.
Place onion rings in bottom of pan.
Season both sides of fish with garlic salt, onion salt, paprika and pepper.
Place fish into pan on top of onion; pour butter over fish and onion.
(Cover approximately 1/2 fish fillets with butter).
Baste with butter. Broil 15 to 18 minutes.
After about 5 minutes of cooking, baste approximately every 2 to 3 minutes.
Check fish by using fork and see if fish flakes apart easily.
If desired, sprinkle Parmesan cheese over fillets.
Bake fish on rack in middle of oven.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs with oleo to make crust.
Press in pan and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Mix corn syrup, sugar and salt in heavy saucepan.
Cook over medium heat stirring constantly until mixture comes to a boil, about 2 minutes.
Gradually pour syrup over popcorn, stirring constantly, until evenly coated.
Shape into balls, using as little pressure as possible (you may want to butter your hands). If popcorn mixture cools during shaping, place over low heat.

title: country mustard chicken
directions: Spray medium skillet with cooking spray and heat over med-high heat 1 minute. Add chicken and cook 10 minutes or until browned. Set chicken aside. Add gravy, mustard and garlic powder. Heat to a boil. Return chicken to pan. Reduce heat to low. Cover and cook 5 minutes or until chicken is no longe pink. Serve with noodles if desired.

title: paprika fish
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients.
Brush over both sides of fish.
Broil 5 minutes or until fish flakes easily.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Pour salt over sliced cucumbers, onions and green peppers. Cover with ice and soak 3 hours.
Mix together, then drain.
Set aside.
In a large pan, mix sugar, vinegar, turmeric and celery and mustard seeds together and bring just to a boil, but do not boil.
Add to cucumber mixture, then pack into sterile jars and seal.
Yields 8 pints.

title: banana bread
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt and soda together.
Cream sugar, shortening, eggs and orange peel.
Combine mashed bananas and milk.
Add bananas and flour alternately to the shortening mixture. Fold in pecans.
Pour mixture into greased loaf pan (either 1 regular loaf pan or 12 miniature loaf pans) and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: weight watchers congealed salad
directions: Heat applesauce.
Add jello and mix.
Add Knox gelatine.
Add drained pineapple.
Makes 8 servings on Weight Watchers.
Each serving equals 1 fruit and 10 calories.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix sugar and peanut butter together until crumbly.
Put 2/3 of mixture in bottom of crust.
Beat milk, pudding and 1 tablespoon peanut butter until blended.
Pour in shell over sugar and peanut butter mixture.
Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle remaining sugar and peanut butter crumbs.

title: chicken marsala
directions: In skillet, heat oil.
Tenderize and dust chicken with flour. Lightly brown chicken on both sides.
Remove chicken.
Saute onion and mushrooms.
Remove excess oil.
Add all wine, butter, 1 teaspoon flour, garlic salt, onion powder, salt and pepper (amount varies upon taste).
Add chicken and heat on slow simmer for 10 minutes.

title: german chocolate sheet cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Use sheet cake pan.
Mix 1/2 cup of boiling water with chocolate until chocolate melts.
Mix flour, salt and baking soda.
Beat margarine and sugar until smooth; add one egg yolk at a time and beat.
Stir in chocolate mixture with vanilla; add flour mixture, alternately with buttermilk, beating after addition until smooth.
Beat egg whites until they form a stiff peak.
Gently stir in egg whites into batter.
Pour batter into pans and bake about 30 minutes or until done.

title: chile con queso dip
directions: Melt cheese in top of double boiler over hot water.
Add remaining ingredients and cook 30 or 40 minutes, stirring occasionally. Serve hot with taco chips. Freezes well.

title: yummy chocolate chip cupcakes
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and set aside.
Mix all other ingredients well and fill muffin tins 1/3 full.
Top with cream cheese mixture and bake 25 to 35 minutes.
Makes 20 to 24 cupcakes.

title: scalloped eggplant
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
On medium size, heatproof platter, arrange eggplant slices, then tomato and onion slices on top. Drizzle with 1/4 cup melted butter.
Sprinkle with salt and basil. Bake, covered, 20 minutes.
Cut Mozzarella slices and arrange over the top.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake, uncovered, 10 minutes.

title: chocolate scotcheroos
directions: In a 5-quart saucepan, cook sugar and corn syrup together until mixture boils.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter. Stir in crispy rice and press into a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan. Let harden.
Melt morsels over hot (not boiling) water.
Spread over mixture and chill.
Cut in squares.
Yield: 40 (1-inch) squares.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Layer pork chops in baking dish.
Peel and dice up potatoes and layer over meat.
Pour mushroom soup over the top. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to
2 hours.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Form into balls.
Brown in hot oil; drain off most fat.
Prepare 2 cups gravy using 3 cups water; pour over meatballs and simmer for 30 minutes.
Makes about 50 meatballs.

title: weight watchers soup
directions: Mix together; bring
to a boil and simmer until vegetables are tender.
Don't overcook.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all together.
Put in a bowl and chill.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook sugar, water and cornstarch on medium or high until thick and clear looking.
Take off burner and add dry strawberry jello. Stir and let cool (after steam has gone).
Add quart of sliced strawberries.
Pour into cooled cooked pie shell.
Set in refrigerator to jell for 30 minutes to an hour.
Slice and add Cool Whip for topping.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Put rhubarb in unbaked pie shell.
Pour custard over rhubarb. Add small cuts of butter on top.
Bake in hot oven at 425° until custard sets, 30 to 40 minutes.

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: Mix together in large pot 2 sticks oleo, sugar, egg and milk. Let it come to boil for 1 or 2 minutes, stirring.
Remove from heat and add immediately broken pecans, graham cracker crumbs and Angel Flake coconut.
Mix all together and pour over layer of 12 whole graham crackers.
Add a layer of crackers on top, press lightly.
Cover with icing made of 3/4 stick oleo, powdered sugar and vanilla. Chill several hours, then cut into squares.
(Add milk to moisten spread.)

title: pennsylvania red cabbage
directions: Heat oil in skillet; add remaining ingredients and 1/4 cup of water.
Cook, covered, over low heat.
Stir occasionally.
Cook to desired crispness, 15 minutes or, for more tender cabbage, 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.
Colorful side dish with pork.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Beat eggs.
Add milk and combine with remaining ingredients. Put into casserole.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: "zesty" grilled pork chops
directions: Clean pork chops.
Sprinkle both sides with garlic powder and lemon pepper.
Place chops in gallon size storage bag.
Pour in salad dressing and shake.
Place in refrigerator at least 2 hours. (Shake about every 15 to 20 minutes.)
Take out; place on medium grill.
Keep turning until done.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Preheat
oven
to
Grease and flour 10-inch tube pan or 9 x 13-inch loaf pan.
Sift dry ingredients together.

title: breakfast casserole(prepare the night before.)
directions: Brown sausage and drain on paper towel.
Put sausage in bottom of large baking dish prepared with Pam.
Cover sausage with croutons.
Blend milk, eggs, salt and pepper.
Pour in dish.
Top with cheese.
Let set in refrigerator overnight, then bake for 30 to 45 minutes at 325°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: old fashioned egg custard
directions: Melt margarine. Add sugar and flour. Mix well. Add eggs and beat. Then add milk and flavoring and mix well. Pour into a Pyrex pie plate and cook at 350° until brown, about 35 minutes. Let cool and cut into wedges.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Mix together the first 7 ingredients; shape into 1-inch balls. Cook meatballs in shortening until brown.
Remove from skillet and drain well.
Heat chili sauce and jelly in skillet.
Stir constantly until jelly is melted.
Add meatballs; stir until coated.
Simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: zucchini relish
