directions: Grind zucchini squash and do not peel.
Take large seeds out. Add onions and salt.
Let stand overnight.
Next morning, drain and rinse with cold water.
Grind green and red pepper.
Add all ingredients.
Cook slowly for 30 minutes.
Fill jars and seal. Yield: 8 pints.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients; set aside.
Blend eggs, oil and sugars. Add dry ingredients; mix lightly until well blended.
Add zucchini, bananas, nuts and vanilla; mix well.
Spread into 2 greased loaf pans (9 x 5 x 3-inch) and bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes, or 3 greased loaf pans (7 7/8 x 3 7/8 x 2 1/2-inch) for 1 hour.
Bake at 350° (or 325° if glass pans).

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Melt butter over low heat, add flour gradually and stir in sugar.
Beat well.
Add eggs one at a time and beat until fluffy. Add vanilla and buttermilk, stir well.
Pour into 8 inch or 9 inch pie shell.
Bake at 325 degrees for 50 minutes (or until done).

title: baked beans
directions: Fry bacon and onion until bacon is cooked.
Drain some of the grease but keep some for flavor.
Add brown sugar and stir until dissolved.
Add ketchup, mustard, molasses and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix in beans.
Bake at 350° in 9 x 13-inch pan or a casserole dish for 1 1/2 hours.
Stir every 1/2 hour.

title: lemon-soy marinade for fish steaks
directions: Whisk together all ingredients.
Pour over fish steaks (use swordfish, halibut or shark) in a shallow dish and marinate for 1 to 6 hours, covered, in the refrigerator.
Broil or grill the fish steaks, brushing often with the marinade.

title: josephinas(ho-se-fee-nas)
directions: Blend butter and chiles.
Spread on rounds of French bread. Blend cheese and Miracle Whip.
Spread on top.
Bake or broil until melted.

title: daddy's orange sherbet ice cream
directions: Mix together well. Pour into freezer can of electric or hand crank ice cream freezer.
Freeze as usual.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream peanut butter and shortening together.
Add sugar and beat until light and fluffy.
Add beaten egg and then flour and baking soda.
Mix well.
Make a big ball of the dough with the hands.
Then pinch off small pieces and roll in hands to make about a 1-inch ball.
Then put on a cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: amazin' raisin cake
directions: Grease and flour 2 (9-inch) round baking pans or tube pan.
In large bowl, with mixer on low speed, beat first 9 ingredients for 2 minutes, scraping bowl frequently.
Stir in apples, raisins and nuts.
Pour into pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes (for the 9-inch pans), about 12 minutes longer for the tube pan or until tester inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes. Remove.
Cool.
If desired, fill and frost with 2 cups whipped cream.

title: taco casserole(teen favorite)
directions: Break up tacos in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan, reserving half. Brown beef slowly in pan, then add tomato sauce and taco seasoning.
Cook slowly for 10 minutes, stirring.
Add half of meat mixture to pan with tacos; add refried beans, then remainder of meat mixture, topping with grated cheese and rest of tacos. Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes and serve with sour cream.

title: tangy barbecue sauce
directions: Saute onion in butter in a large saucepan until tender; stir in remaining ingredients.

title: corn and bean casserole
directions: Mix beans and corn together (drained) and put in casserole dish.
Saute onion in oleo and mix with sour cream; spread on top of beans and corn.
Crush crackers and mix with 1/4 stick melted oleo and put this on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: baked broccoli chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Bake chicken with soup and broccoli pieces for 45 minutes.
Spread cheese over top and bake until melted.
Serve with rice, pasta or potatoes.

title: corn meal muffins
directions: Combine corn meal, flour and baking powder.
Add shortening, egg and enough milk to make a soft dough.
Stir well.
Spoon into oiled muffin tin.
Bake at 325° for approximately 30 minutes. Makes 1 dozen.

title: champagne dessert
directions: Blend cream cheese and sugar until smooth.
Blend together other ingredients, then fold in cream cheese mixture.
Place in freezer for at least 12 hours.

title: cocoa snowballs
directions: In the medium mixing bowl, put the cereal, coconut and nut topping. Stir with the wooden spoon to mix.

title: crab salad
directions: If necessary, remove cartilage from crabmeat.
In medium bowl, combine mayonnaise, parsley, chives, Worcestershire and lemon juice.
Mix well.
Add crabmeat and cucumber; toss.
Refrigerate covered until well chilled, about 1 hour.
To serve, arrange lettuce cups on 4 serving plates.
Fill with salad; garnish with egg.
Makes 4 servings; 232 calories each.

title: hot cross buns
directions: Use very warm water for yeast.
Sprinkle yeast into water; let stand a few minutes, then stir until dissolved.
Pour hot milk over salt, sugar and shortening to cool to lukewarm.
Add yeast and 2 cups of flour; beat well and let rise about 1/2 hour.
Add egg yolks, then remaining flour mixed with cinnamon.
Add raisins. Knead.
Put in a large, greased bowl.
Brush top of dough with melted butter.
Cover and let rise about 1 1/2 hours.
Shape into small, round buns and place close together in greased pan.
Let rise until doubled in bulk.
With a very sharp knife, cut a cross just through the top surface of each bun.
Bake in preheated oven at 400° for 15 minutes.
Brush with melted butter and continue to bake for 5 minutes more.
Cool on a rack.
If desired, brush each bun with a simple frosting made of confectioners sugar, moistened with water.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix ground beef, oatmeal, salt, pepper and onion together. Make small balls.
Fry in pan with melted butter until brown. Drain.
Combine catsup, Worcestershire sauce, vinegar and brown sugar.
Pour over meatballs.
Simmer on low heat for 30 minutes.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Mix brown sugar, flour and salt with beaten egg yolks and 1/2 cup milk.
Add 1 cup milk and cook until thick.
Add butter.
Fill baked crust.
Add meringue and brown.

title: cherry dessert
directions: *Twelve ounces of nondairy whipped topping may be used instead.

title: easy potatoes
directions: Overlap potato slices in greased pan.
Combine next 5 ingredients and pour over potatoes.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: salmon souffle ala pittaluga
directions: Melt butter, stir in flour and seasonings.
When well blended, slowly add milk, stirring constantly over low heat until mixture thickens and boils.
Remove from heat and stir in well-beaten egg yolks.
Fold in salmon; cool.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites. Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 425°
for 20 to 25 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: hot holiday appetizer
directions: Blend cheese and milk. Stir in dried beef, onions, & green pepper.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream Parkay and sugar.
Add eggs and bananas.
Add dry ingredients.
Bake in greased and floured loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lenora's sloppy joes(servings:  8)
directions: Cook beef and onion until pink is gone and drain.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer until hot and thick.
May add salt and pepper to taste.
Put on broiled hamburger buns.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Add mayonnaise and beat until blended.
Stir in crab meat.
Pour into 1-quart baking dish.
Top with almonds.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve with crackers, Triscuits or party size bread pieces.

title: oyster soup
directions: Wash oysters and boil with other ingredients until all substance is out of the oysters.
Strain the liquid from the ingredients and pour back into pot.
Add big spoonful of butter mixed with flour.
Remove oysters from shells and add to mixture. Stir up to egg yolks with a cup of cream and cook in pot.
Don't let soup boil.

title: cranberry jello mold
directions: Dissolve jello with boiling cranberry juice.
Add cold water. Chill until partially set, 1 hour.
Add cranberries to jello and fold Cool Whip in lightly.
Spray mold with Pam.
Let set.

title: deep-dish corn bake
directions: Melt butter.
Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Place in a greased deep-dish casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fruit dip
directions: Combine and serve with fresh fruit.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour with baking soda, baking powder and spices. Stir into butter mixture alternately with pumpkin, ending with flour.
Stir in milk, walnuts and raisins.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 10-inch Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours or until toothpick inserted in middle comes out clean.
Cool in pan 30 minutes, then turn out onto a cake rack to finish cooling.

title: best ever strawberry pudding
directions: Combine strawberries, gelatin, and sugar in a saucepan. Mix well. Cook until sugar melts, stirring constantly. Cool. Combine milk, pudding mix, sour cream, and whipped topping in a bowl. Mix well. Layer vanilla wafers, pudding mixture and strawberry mixture alternately in glass bowl until all ingredients are used. Chill overnight.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Pour pecans in bottom of pie shell with 3/4 cup chocolate chips.
Pour mixture of remaining ingredients over nuts and chips. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken and veggies made simple
directions: In large skillet combine chicken and about 1/3 of Italian dressing. Saute until chicken starts to brown.
Add vegetables and remaining dressing. Cover; simmer 7 to 12 minutes, until vegetables are crisp-tender; stirring frequently.
Serve over pasta.
Sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese if desired.
Quick, easy and healthy.

title: chocolate covered peanuts
directions: Put all ingredients in crock-pot. Stir together. Cook on low heat for 2 hours, stirring occasionally. Drop by teaspoon onto Saran Wrap. When cool, peel off Saran.

title: pork chops in sauerkraut
directions: Trim fat from chops.
Brown both sides lightly.
Remove. Brown onions in drippings.
Remove from heat and add applesauce. Mix well.
Spread well drained sauerkraut on bottom of a baking dish or electric frypan.
Put in chops, then applesauce mixture. Bake for 1 hour at 240° in frypan or 1 1/2 hours at 350° if in oven.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: appetizer meatballs
directions: Combine ingredients for meatballs.
Roll into small bite size balls.
Brown meatballs in 1/4 cup margarine.

title: ambrosia
directions: Mix concentrate and pineapple together. Grate apples directly into this to prevent browning. Mix well. Add sugar, frozen coconut and gelatin. Just before serving, add the ginger ale or Sprite. Also, if using bananas, add just before serving.

title: sri lankan fried rice
directions: Cook rice and allow to cool. Saute vegetables in margarine. Add beaten eggs and scramble and mix it together with ginger and garlic.
Add rice to vegetable/egg mixture and add salt and soy sauce to taste.

title: bubbas cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour in two 9 x 13-inch pans, sprayed with Pam.
Cook in a 375° oven for 25 to 30 minutes until browned on top.

title: ravioli with rosemary cream sauce
directions: Combine the cream and rosemary in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil, reduce the heat and simmer until reduced to 1/2 cup, about 15 minutes.
Cook the ravioli in boiling salted water until done. Drain and return to the pan.
Pour cream sauce into the pan. Squeeze 2 teaspoons juice from the lemon and add to pasta along with the salt and pepper.
Toss.
Serve sprinkled with the chives. Add plenty of Parmesan cheese.

title: pineapple pudding
directions: Mix pudding and milk; add sour cream and 1/2 Cool Whip.
Add drained pineapple.
Layer pudding mix and vanilla wafers.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.
Cool.
Serve.

title: chicken corn soup
directions: Cover chicken with water; add salt and saffron.
Boil; simmer, covered, until tender, about 2 hours.

title: shrimp etouffee
directions: Split shrimp and season with salt, pepper and cayenne pepper (be careful with the cayenne!); set aside.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Beat milk and egg.
Put cooked macaroni into a greased 9 x 12-inch baking pan.
Pour milk and egg mixture in, refrigerate a couple of hours.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: speedy little devils
directions: Mix cake mix and margarine until crumbly.
Save some for topping and press remainder into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Soften marshmallow cream in microwave (30 to 40 seconds on High) and mix with peanut butter.
Spread over crumbs and top with reserved crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chicken with pineapple
directions: Dust chicken with flour and spices.
Brown on all sides in margarine.
Remove chicken when browned and place skin side down; line baking dish.
Add syrup from pineapple, soy sauce and sugar to margarine in skillet.
Stir all chicken pieces and drippings into sauce.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour, turning chicken after 30 minutes.
When turning the chicken, add the pineapple pieces and baste.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream the sugar and butter well. Add eggs, flour and flavoring.
Mix well with electric mixer at high speed.
Pour into a well-greased and floured tube pan and bake 1 1/4 hours at 325°.

title: garden fresh pork chops
directions: In skillet, melt butter and brown chops.
Add vegetables, basil and Cup-a-Soup blended with water.
Simmer, covered, 45 minutes or until chops and vegetables are tender.
Makes about 2 servings.

title: snowball cake
directions: Mix gelatine, sugar and pineapple.
Set in refrigerator until jelled.
Cut brown off of angel food cake.
Tear into pieces. Prepare 2 envelopes of Dream Whip.
Fold into gelatine-pineapple mixture, etc.
Set in refrigerator.
Put whipped cream or Cool Whip all over this.

title: baked ziti
directions: Heat the oven to 350°.
Bring a large pot of salted water to boil and add the ziti.
Cook until tender, about 8 minutes.
Drain the pasta.
Place ziti in a large bowl.
Mix with the Ricotta and half the Mozzarella.

title: potato casserole
directions: Defrost potatoes. In a large bowl, combine the potatoes, 1/2 cup melted margarine, salt, pepper, onion, soup, sour cream and cheese. Place in a buttered 13 x 9-inch pan. Mix crushed cornflakes with 3 tablespoons melted margarine. Sprinkle over mixture. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: shortcake biscuits
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Cut in butter.
Add the milk; mix only until the dry ingredients are moistened.
Dough will be lumpy.
Drop by spoonfuls into an 8-inch round greased glass baking dish.
Bake with microwave energy for 5 minutes on High.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Beat egg and add rest of ingredients.
Pour into 1-quart lightly greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: syrup cookies (1)
directions: Homemade Cookie Syrup:
Heat 2 c. sugar in a pan (iron skillet works best).
Cook until dark and bubbles are clear.
Take from heat, let cool for awhile, then slowly add 1 c. water.
Boil hard for 1 minute (longer for thicker syrup).
Yields about 2 c. syrup.

title: three week cole slaw
directions: Combine cabbage, pepper, onion and sugar.
Mix well.
In a pan, mix oil, vinegar, celery seed and salt. Bring to a boil. Pour over cabbage mixture and mix well. Store in an airtight container.
Refrigerate.
Let stand 2 to 3 days before serving. Will keep for about a month.

title: meat loaf
directions: Beat egg into milk.
Break up bread into small pieces and soak in the milk mixture.
In a large bowl, salt and pepper the meat and add onion, tomato sauce, green pepper and milk mixture; mix well with your hands.
Place mixture in a baking pan and form into a loaf.
Spread ketchup over the loaf and arrange bacon slices over the loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: lottie gardner's gingerbread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients and add margarine and 1/2 of water and syrup, beat; then add egg and add rest of water and syrup.
Bake at 350° in greased and floured pan.

title: tomato juice cocktail
directions: Remove stems, ends and blemishes from the tomatoes and cut into pieces.
Do not peel.
Cook all ingredients together.
Let simmer for one hour.
Strain.
Add 1/4 cup mild vinegar to strained juice and heat to boiling point.
Seal in sterilized jars.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix well.
Bake about 35 minutes.
Casserole will brown. Serves 6.

title: ham and cheese chips
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Shape into a 9-inch roll. Chill well. Cut into 1/4-inch thick slices.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheet. Bake at 425° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool on wire rack and store in an airtight container.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: date cake
directions: Pour water over dates and soda; let stand while mixing batter. Mix batter and pour into the date mixture.
Bake in a loaf or tube pan.
Bake at 275° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: parmesan rice
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Add rice and continue to saute until rice is slightly golden.
Add chicken broth and bring to a boil. Remove from heat and cover.
Let stand 5 minutes (moisture should be absorbed).
Stir in parmesan cheese.

title: raspberry yo-yos
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg, milk and vanilla.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt; add to creamed mixture.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls; put on cookie sheet and press down slightly.
When cooled, spread raspberry preserves between 2 cookies.
Let preserves squeeze out of cookie.
Roll sides in shredded coconut.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Mix 1/3 cup of sugar with cornstarch; add juice from the pineapple.
Cook in a heavy 10-inch skillet over direct heat, stirring constantly, until sauce boils and becomes clear.
Add drained pineapple and butter.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Cook green beans until tender.
In skillet, melt butter and place sliced onion rings in melted butter.
Cook until tender, but not brown.
Add mushrooms and pimentos.
Simmer for 10 minutes. Add cream of mushroom soup and Old English cheese; mix well.
Add drained green beans; mix together well.
Put in casserole (9 x 3-inch baking dish).
Sprinkle cracker crumbs over the top.
Slice butter and put on top of crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: marinated tomatoes and cucumbers
directions: In 2-quart shallow baking dish, arrange tomatoes, cucumber and onion.
In a small bowl, combine remaining ingredients except lettuce and bacon bits.
Pour over tomatoes.
Chill several hours. Line platter with lettuce.
Arrange tomatoes, cucumber and onion on top and sprinkle with bacon bits.

title: chewy oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl and mix well.
Place on greased and floured cookie sheet one teaspoon at a time.
Preheat oven to 250°.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Let cool before removing from cookie sheet.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil until soft ball stage.
Remove from heat; cool until lukewarm.
Add 1 cup peanut butter and 2 tablespoons vanilla. Beat until creamy.
Pour into greased 9-inch pan.

title: zesty barbecued chicken
directions: For Sauce:
In a saucepan, combine everything, except chicken. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Boil macaroni in 2 quarts of water for 10 to 12
minutes or until tender, stirring occasionally, then drain.
Return to pan and add cheese sauce.
Then add milk, sour cream and chopped ham. Put in 1 1/2-quart casserole and top off with Cheddar cheese. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: tasty meat balls
directions: Mix the first six ingredients together well and make into meat balls.
Put in baking dish.
Mix together the catsup and water and pour over meat balls.
Cover with foil and bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: hearty spanish soup
directions: Start the meat in cold water.
Make a rich broth by cooking it slowly with garlic, onion, pepper and salt.
When the meat is tender, strain off broth.
Add the vegetables (corn last) and cook slowly until done.
Add the meat, cut in cubes, to the soup.
If extra piquancy is desired, you may serve this with jalapeno sauce. Pick the corn up with fingers.

title: chili con queso
directions: Cut up cheese in small blocks.
Brown ground beef or turkey with garlic and A.1. and drain.
Put everything in crock-pot on high.
Stir frequently.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Add more or less peppers to adjust temperature.

title: corn soup
directions: Seasonings can be put in a food chopper.

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown sausage in skillet with onions and peppers.
Drain.
Add tomato sauce and salsa and simmer on low.
Cook rice as indicated on package.
Serve sausage mixture on top of rice and sprinkle with cheese.

title: stuffed melongene (eggplant) with meat
directions: Wash melongene (eggplant) and cut off a slice from top.
Scoop out pulp, leaving a thin shell.
Dice pulp and cook in butter in a covered pan over low heat until soft.
Add onion and chives to pulp while being cooked.
Add all other ingredients, except dry bread crumbs.
Fill eggplant with meat mixture.
Sprinkle top with bread crumbs and brown quickly in hot oven.

title: 2 flavor fudge
directions: Combine in saucepan the brown sugar, granulated sugar, evaporated milk and 1/2 cup butter or margarine and bring to a full boil over moderate heat. Stirring occasionally, boil for 15 minutes. Remove from heat.
Add the marshmallow cream, butterscotch morsels and chocolate chip morsels.
Stir until morsels are melted and mixture is smooth. Blend in the nuts and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Pour into greased 9-inch pan (square pan). Chill until firm.
Yields 2 1/2 pounds.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix boiling water with jello.
Chill until thickening.
Whip chilled milk; fold into jello.
Cream the cheese, sugar and vanilla; add cheese mixture to jello.
Melt oleo; add to crushed crackers; form lining on the bottom and sides of large bowl. Reserve some crumbs to sprinkle on top.
Pour mixture into bowl lined with cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle reserved crumbs on top. Chill.
Best after 24 hours.

title: sausage and cheese biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Use ungreased cookie sheet.
Mix all ingredients together well.
Form into small bite-size balls.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach as per instructions; drain well and squeeze until dry.
Mix spinach and remaining ingredients.
Make 1 1/2-inch diameter balls.
Bake on cookie sheet 15 minutes at 350°.
If freezing, freeze before baking.

title: mom's orange sponge cake
directions: Beat egg whites, salt, sugar and cream of tartar until fluffy. Beat
remaining ingredients in another bowl.
Fold yellow mixture into white mixture and put into a greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: berner eier zuepfe (swiss egg braid)(makes 2)
directions: Soften the yeast in lukewarm water.
Let stand 5 minutes. Combine butter, sugar, eggs, salt and scalded milk in a large bowl. Blend well.
Let cool to lukewarm, then add yeast.
Blend in the four gradually to form a stiff dough.
Knead on well floured surface until smooth and shiny, about 5-7 minutes.
Place in a greased bowl, cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled in volume, about 2 hours.
Place dough on floured surface and divide into 8 parts, mold into 8 balls.
Cover with inverted mixing bowl and let stand for 15 minutes.
Then shape each ball into a 12-inch rope.

title: pumpkin delight cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In large mixing bowl, combine oats, flour, baking soda, cream of tartar, cinnamon, ginger, cloves, nutmeg and allspice.
In medium bowl, mix honey, applesauce, pumpkin puree and 2 unbeaten egg whites.
Gently stir into flour mixture and mix until just blended.
Stir in raisins and dates. Gently stir in 2 lightly beaten egg whites.
Do not overmix.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix oil and sugar; add egg yolks.
Mix carrots and water; add to mixture.
Sift flour with cinnamon, nutmeg, baking soda and salt; add to mixture.
Add nuts.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour in greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°. Cool.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting and store in refrigerator.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except for 2/3 cup of the cheese. Pour into a 2-quart casserole dish and top with remaining cheese. Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Remove foil and bake for another 5 to 10 minutes.

title: apple butter
directions: Pare apples thinly; quarter, core and slice.
Should be about 11 quarts sliced apples.
Put in large kettle and add cider.
Cook until there is sauce.
(If fine butter is wanted, put through food mill.)
Turn sauce into a large roasting pan.
Bake in a preheated 325° oven for 1 hour or until sauce is reduced, about half.
Stir occasionally.
Add sugar and stir until it is thoroughly mixed with apples.
Bake another hour, stirring frequently.
Add spices, tied loosely in cheesecloth bag and bake 1/2 hour or until mixture is a reddish amber color.
Stir several times.
Remove bag and pack in hot sterilized jars; seal.

title: orange sherbet
directions: Mix ingredients and freeze according to freezer instructions.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and rice by directions.
Pour into large bowl and add all remaining ingredients except cheese.
Mix thoroughly and pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with cheese and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cheese roll
directions: Mix well. Sprinkle with parsley.

title: taco dip
directions: Combine sour cream, cream cheese and taco seasoning mix, blending until smooth.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with beef, lettuce, cheese and tomatoes.
Cover and refrigerate.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: burnt butter ziti(italian)
directions: Boil a saucepan full of water and add ziti.
Cook until soft. Heat large skillet with 1/2 pound butter until burnt.
Add ziti, salt, pepper, garlic, parsley and grated cheese.
Mix well and serve.
Preparation time:
30 minutes.
Cooking time: 30 minutes.

title: spiced beef roast
directions: Melt margarine in skillet; brown beef. Add flour and mix well. Add onions, garlic, spices, sugar, water and broth.
Place casserole dish in 350° oven. Cook 1 1/2 hours until meat is tender, adding mixed vegetables 15 minutes before completion. Remove whole bay leaf and serve.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Mix strawberries and glaze.
For best results, refrigerate overnight.

title: canadian war cake
directions: Boil all these ingredients for five minutes after they begin bubbling.
When cold, add 3 cups flour and 2 teaspoons of soda, dissolved in a little hot water.
Bake slowly 1 hour.

title: micro scalloped potatoes
directions: Place butter in 1 1/2-quart bowl.
Microwave on High 30 to 45 seconds until melted.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper until blended.
Gradually whisk in milk until smooth.
Microwave on High 8 to 10 minutes stirring twice until boiling and slightly thickened.
Lightly grease shallow 2-quart casserole.
Arrange half of potatoes in bottom, sprinkle with half the onions, then pour half the white sauce on top.
Repeat layers. Cover with vented plastic wrap.
Microwave on High 16 to 18 minutes, rotating dish half turn, until potatoes are tender and sauce is set.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: jello pies
directions: Boil sugar, water and cornstarch until clear.
Add jello. When cool, add 3 to 4 cups of fruit.
Put in baked pie shell. Refrigerate. Top with Cool Whip.

title: des' rolls
directions: Warm together shortening, milk, sugar and potatoes;
set aside.
Dissolve
yeast
in
1/4 cup warm water, then add other warm
ingredients.	Add flour as you stir.	Let rise in refrigerator;
keep
covered.
Punch
down, knead, roll out and shape into rolls.
May keep part of dough in refrigerator.	Will keep a week.
Bake in a 350° oven until brown as desired.

title: cheese spread
directions: Allow cheeses to soften.
Grate Cheddar and mix with cream cheese.
Mix in all other ingredients.
Serve on crackers.

title: double delicious cookie bars
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, melt butter in oven.
Sprinkle crumbs evenly over butter.
Pour Eagle Brand evenly over crumbs.
Top with chips.
Press down firmly.
Bake at 350° (325° for glass) for 25 to 30 minutes until lightly browned.
Cool and cut.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Chop shrimp.
Add all the other ingredients.
Stir.
Chill in refrigerator 1 hour before serving.

title: chunky fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients; chill.
Makes 12 servings.

title: blueberry sour cream corn muffins(sugar-free dessert, great for diabetics)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 12 muffin cups or line with paper liners; set aside.
Combine dry ingredients in medium bowl. Add combined egg, sour cream and apple juice concentrate; mix just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Gently stir in blueberries. Spoon batter into prepared cups, filling each cup 3/4 full.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Let stand in pan or wire rack 5 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool slightly.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: chicken livers and bacon
directions: Cut strips of bacon in half.
Cut chicken livers into fours and water chestnuts into thin slices.
Roll chicken livers and water chestnuts and roll strips of bacon around.
Place in pan and bake on 350° until bacon is crisp!

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Beat eggs frothy; add powder, cream, salt and sugar.
Beat until sugar dissolves; add flavoring.
Blend.
Pour in freezer, 3/4 full.
Freeze until ice cream is hard.
Yield:
1 1/2 gallons.

title: karen's million dollar pie
directions: Mix everything together; pour into graham cracker pie crusts. Sprinkle with nuts.
Chill for 1 hour before serving.

title: two minute microwave fudge
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 3-quart mixing bowl.
Microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Stir until well blended.
Pour into a buttered 8-inch baking dish.
Cover and refrigerate until set. Cut in 1-inch squares.
Makes 64 pieces.

title: ethel salad
directions: Dissolve lime jello in 1 cup water.
Add marshmallows.
Cover and let cool.
Add the pineapple to this and set aside.
Mix cream cheese, whipping cream and salad dressing; whip together.
Add jello mixture.
Pour in shallow pan to set.
When set, dissolve orange jello and 1 cup water.
Cool and pour over first layer.

title: granny's hash
directions: Place beef roast in covered pot.
Cover with water.
Cook 2/3 done.
Remove, let cool and cut in small strips with kitchen shears.
Replace meat and onions in broth and cook at gentle boil until meat begins to fall apart.
Add salt, pepper and Worcestershire to taste.
Serve over stiff rice or egg noodles.

title: applesauce meat loaf
directions: Mix and spread on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: noodle salad
directions: Cook and drain noodles; coat with oil.
Add parsley and pimentos.
Set aside.
Chop vegetables and set aside.
Mix vinegar, sugar, mustard, garlic salt, salt and pepper.
Pour sauce mix over noodles mixture and mix well.
Add vegetables to mixture and mix well.
Refrigerate for at least 3 hours.
It is better if it is refrigerated overnight.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Fry bacon, drain and crumble.
Chop broccoli and onion.
Core, peel and chop apple.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Cook celery, carrots and green peppers in salted water until crisp and tender; drain.
Cook tomatoes, salt, oregano and garlic to a chunky sauce (if not thick enough, stir in 1 tablespoon cornstarch).
Remove and stir all vegetables together into sauce (including pinto beans).
Put layer of mixed vegetables in bottom of casserole.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Repeat, ending with cheese on top.
Bake at 375° until cheese is melted.
Serve hot.

title: aunt violet's caramel corn
directions: Pop corn.
Remove all unpopped kernels.
Heat sugar, butter, Karo and salt in saucepan until bubbly around edges.
Continue cooking for 5 minutes. Remove from heat and add baking soda.
Stir until foamy.
Pour over popcorn until well coated.
Add nuts if desired, stirring well.

title: quick brownies
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 9-inch pan.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add eggs and melted butter.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Mix.
Pour in pan. Bake 20 minutes in 350° oven.

title: baked fish with herb stuffing
directions: Blend stuffing mix, water and 1 teaspoon thyme.
Spread evenly in large, shallow, greased baking dish.
Arrange fish fillets over stuffing.

title: seafood pasta salad
directions: Step 1:
Pour 2 gallons of hot water into Groen kettle.
Bring to a boil.
Add 1 1/2 ounces vegetable oil and 1 tablespoon salt to boiling water.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 3 tablespoons cool water.
In pot, soften cream cheese and tomato soup over low heat.
Add gelatin and blend well.
Remove from heat; add mayonnaise, shallots, celery, shrimp and Tabasco.
Use as a dip with crackers or chips.

title: lemon supreme pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend all ingredients in a large bowl. Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Do not overmix.
Bake in a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes, until center springs back when touched lightly.
Cool, right side up, for about 25 minutes, then remove from pan.
Be sure to use Crisco oil.

title: broccoli-mushroom-cauliflower casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and cauliflower and cut into 2-inch pieces. Heat oven to 350°.
Spread broccoli and cauliflower in large baking dish.
Heat mushroom soup.
Add 1/2 cup milk and sauteed mushrooms.
Pour this mushroom sauce over vegetables.
Sprinkle with cheese and paprika.
Bake 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: salsa
directions: Wash all vegetables well. Dice tomatoes, green pepper, onion and
jalapeno in small cubes. Cut and dice cilantro (discard stems). Combine all ingredients in large mixing bowl, except lime juice. Mix well and then add lime juice.

title: lemon jello cake
directions: Mix cake mix, oil, eggs, water and lemon jello together and bake in a tube cake pan at 350° for 45 minutes to an hour.
Mix a small cup of lemonade and 3/4 cup of confectioners sugar to pour over cake when cool.

title: veggie bites
directions: Unroll crescent rolls and place in bottom of an ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch jellyroll pan, pinching edges together to seal.
Brush dough with beaten egg.
Bake at 375° for 11 to 13 minutes, and cool completely.

title: white frosting
directions: Mix all together on low speed for 3 minutes.
Then beat 5 minutes on high.
This is enough frosting for two cakes.
Also good on cookies and keeps well in the refrigerator for several weeks.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: In skillet, brown ground beef and onion; drain.
In kettle, combine meat and cream of mushroom soup; let simmer about 10 minutes (low heat).
Deep fry Tater Tots and drain grease.
In 9-inch round pan, place Tater Tots on the bottom of the pan; cover with 3 slices of cheese.
Cover cheese with meat mixture and then top with remaining cheese.
Melt cheese in oven.

title: mom's mississippi mud cake
directions: Mix cream or milk, sugar, shortening, eggs, and salt.
Next, beat in flour, cocoa, vanilla, and nuts.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes. Spread marshmallow cream evenly over top and bake another 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and let cool.

title: pomander
directions: Stick whole cloves in mandarin peel, covering mandarin.
These are especially decorative around the holidays.
The fragrance is especially appreciated when pomanders are place in a confined area, such as a closet or bathroom.
These pomanders will stay attractive for 3 to 6 months.
When the fruit is no longer attractive, rinse pomander off, let dry.
Discard mandarins, recycle the cloves.

title: creamed spinach
directions: Thaw and then cook spinach for 4 minutes in salted boiling water.
Drain and set aside.
In a skillet, brown the bacon and onion.
Add salt and pepper to bacon and onion.
Set aside.
Bring the half and half to a boil in a cooking pot.
Melt the butter in a saucepan and add flour.
Mix thoroughly and combine with the half and half.
Cook until mixture thickens.
Add the spinach, bacon and onions to the half and half.
Stir thoroughly and heat. Serves 4.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Layer broccoli on bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Layer chicken over broccoli.
In saucepan, melt the 6 tablespoons of butter.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Gradually stir in milk and continue stirring until white sauce is smooth and comes to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Combine mayonnaise and lemon juice with white sauce.
Pour over chicken and broccoli.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Melt 2 tablespoons of butter.
Stir in bread crumbs and sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: curried crab
directions: Mix curry powder in a little water.
Mix all ingredients, except crab, and cook until thick.
Add crab and serve over rice.

title: best mac 'n' cheese
directions: Cook and drain macaroni. Spray dish with nonstick cooking spray. Put macaroni in dish over 1/2 stick margarine. Pour over the 3 cans milk. Put cheese on top. Bake about 30 minutes.

title: hot pole bean-potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes and beans, covered, in boiling salted water in a large pan until tender; drain vegetables. Fry bacon until crisp; remove from skillet and drain, reserving 2 tablespoons drippings in pan. Crumble bacon. Saute onion in drippings; stir into vegetables. Combine remaining ingredients and pour over vegetables, stirring well. Add bacon. Toss gently. Serve warm. Yields 6-8 servings.

title: pesto pinwheels
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Unroll dough into 2 long rectangles. Firmly press perforations to seal.
Spread rectangles with pesto to within 1/4-inch of edges; sprinkle with bell peppers.
Starting at shortest side, roll up each rectangle; pinch edges to seal. Cut each roll into 8 slices.
Place, cut side down, on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 13 to 17 minutes or until golden brown.
Immediately remove from cookie sheet.
Serve warm. Makes about 16 pieces.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients except 1/4 cup of cheese.
Pour into a well-greased baking pan.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Bake at 450° for 30 minutes.

title: deviled crab
directions: To crab meat, add lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, pepper sauce and salt and pepper to taste.
To make the sauce, mix flour, mustard and milk.
Add evaporated milk and cook and stir until thick and smooth.
Remove from heat and stir in melted butter. Pour over crab meat and mix lightly.
Place in individual shells. Crush crackers and toss with 2 tablespoons melted butter.
Sprinkle on top of crabs.
Bake in a 375° oven for 15 minutes or until brown.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: barbecued corn
directions: Pull shuck back carefully.
Remove silk.
Brush on melted oleo.
Put shuck back into place.
Place ears of corn on outer edges of fire.
Roast, turning now and then for 45 minutes.

title: chimichangas
directions: Cook ground beef; season with salt, pepper and oregano.
Place large spoonful of ground beef in flour tortillas.
Sprinkle with grated Jack cheese and roll.
Place rolled tortillas in baking pan; butter tops.
Bake at 350° until butter melts and they are very light brown.
Remove from oven and coat tops with tomato sauce and grated Longhorn cheese.
Place back into oven and bake until cheese melts.
Serve with chilies and taco sauce or salsa.

title: green beans
directions: Saute celery until tender-crisp.
Combine the cornstarch with the chicken broth and soy sauce.
Add to celery and cook, stirring until translucent and thickened.
Add beans and sliced water chestnuts, if desired, and heat through.
Add sliced scallions (green onions) and sesame seed.

title: creamed spinach
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese in 1 1/2 quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven, stir and top with cheese.
Bake 5 to 10 minutes longer.

title: asparagus blue cheese appetizers
directions: Remove crusts from bread and roll each slice with a rolling pin.
Spread each slice with about 1 teaspoon of cheese spread. Put an asparagus spear along one edge and roll up bread with asparagus inside.
Cut each bread roll into quarters crosswise. Dip each roll in melted butter and place, seam side down, on a baking sheet.
Cover and refrigerate about 1 hour. (At this point, rolls may be wrapped and frozen until ready to heat.)
Heat oven to 375°.
Bake 5 minutes; turn and bake 3 minutes longer, until crisp and brown.
Transfer to a serving dish.
Makes about 68 appetizers.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix ingredients together and press into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape into 2 balls or logs.
Roll in the remaining 1 1/2 cup nuts.

title: spanish rice
directions: Is leftover rice taking up refrigerator space?
Saute onion and green pepper in the oil until soft.
Add ground beef and seasoning, stirring until meat loses its pink color.
Stir in the cooked rice, tomatoes and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix thoroughly. Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 15 minutes.
Yields 8 servings.
Contains 255 calories.

title: impossible coconut pie
directions: In large bowl, beat eggs, coconut, milk, vanilla, sugar, flour and margarine until all ingredients are well-combined.

title: shrimp butter
directions: Cream together butter and cream cheese, then add the rest of the ingredients; mix well.
Good on almost any snack cracker (if you like shrimp).

title: potato chowder
directions: Combine potatoes, celery, onion, salt, and pepper.
Add water.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Do not drain.
Make cream sauce with margarine, flour, and milk.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
Add bacon and undrained vegetables.
Heat - do not boil.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and vanilla; add eggs.
Stir in peanut butter and add dry ingredients.
Form into small balls.
Bake at 375° until done.

title: cookies while you sleep
directions: Preheat
oven
Line a cookie sheet with foil. Beat egg whites until frothy; gradually beat in sugar and beat until stiff.
Add
vanilla
and
almonds flavorings.
Fold in chips
and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet.
Put in oven.
Close and turn oven off.
Leave overnight.
Remove from cookie sheet and store in covered container.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: cheesecake
directions: Let cream cheese soften at room temperature.
Mix in sugar and vanilla flavoring.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Put in shell and refrigerate overnight. Garnish with chopped strawberries about 30 minutes before serving.
